title: banana split cake
directions: Make crust of graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick of butter. Press into 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
In a medium bowl, beat confectioners sugar and 2 sticks of butter.
Add eggs for 15 minutes.
Must beat 15 minutes.
Pour over crust.
Slice bananas over filling.
Put pineapple, other bananas and then cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts and maraschino cherries.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add and beat sugar, flour and salt.
Add and beat together remaining ingredients except nutmeg.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: spanish casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain fat.
Add Spanish rice.
Put in casserole dish and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: lemon love notes
directions: Mix butter, 1 cup flour and confectioners sugar.
Press into ungreased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes or until golden.
Cool in pan or rack.
Combine sugar, 2 teaspoons flour and baking powder.
Add eggs, lemon juice and peel.
This will pour evenly over baked, cooled mixture in square pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool in pan on rack.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix soup and sour cream and set aside.
Mix potatoes and cheese.
Pour melted butter over potatoes.
Fold in soup mixture. Place in 2-quart casserole.
Crumble crackers over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Uncover last 10 minutes.

title: reuben hors d'oeuvres
directions: Rinse and drain sauerkraut.
Put first 3 ingredients through food chopper.
Put on rye crackers or chips.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients; roll into a ball; chill.
Roll in chopped walnuts or pecans or parsley or both.

title: chilli con carne
directions: Broil bacon until done.
Remove bacon and saute onion in the dripping until tender (7 to 10 minutes).
Add meat and cook and stir until gray in color.
Chop bacon and return to mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer until flavors are well blended (about 20 minutes).
Serve hot.
If desired, serve meat mixture over hot cooked rice.
Approximately 5 servings.

title: grandma dula's roast beef
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Cut about 1 or 1 1/2-inch holes all over in roast.
Stuff ingredients in holes and bake in oven for about 1 1/2 or 2 hours at 350°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese to room temperature.
Blend together all ingredients with a mixer, food processor or by hand until cheeses are well blended.
Chill, then roll into a ball.
Allow it to set for 24 hours before serving to allow flavors to blend.
May be rolled in finely chopped nuts, fresh chopped parsley or in paprika for added color.
Let stand at room temperature 1 hour before serving.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease oblong pan.
Mix all ingredients. Spread in pan.
Bake until golden brown, about 25 minutes.
Cut into small squares.
May be frozen before reheating.
Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese before reheating.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Make up 12 hours in advance.
Serve with cut up raw vegetables.

title: harvest fruit and nut pie
directions: Mix all together and dump into pie shell.
Put butter on top and cover.
Bake 45 minutes at 400°.

title: anise almond biscotti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease large cookie sheet. In a large bowl, add first 6 ingredients. Blend, using an electric mixer on low speed. In a separate bowl, whisk together eggs and vanilla. With mixer running, slowly pour egg mixture into bowl. Mix just until the dough comes together. Do not overmix. Divide dough in half. Shape each half into a 12 x 2-inch log. Place logs on cookie sheet. Bake 30 minutes or until slightly risen and firm to touch. Remove cookie sheet from oven. Cool logs on wire rack 15 minutes. Transfer to cutting board. Using a sharp serrated knife, cut logs diagonally into 1/4-inch slices. Place slices in single layer on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 13 minutes or until crisp and golden. Cool on cookie sheet. Store in a covered container.

title: chicken biscuits
directions: Open biscuits and put a nugget in each.

title: oven cruellers
directions: Mix margarine and flour as for pie crust.
Add yolks and vanilla to sour cream, mixing well.
Then add to flour mixture and mix well.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight.

title: holiday cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Add water to make one cup and heat to boiling.
Dissolve gelatin in hot liquid and stir in cranberry sauce.
Cool.
Stir in ginger ale, nuts, pineapple and cream cheese.
Pour into mold and chill.

title: "nite before company" eggs
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with quartered bread slices. Sprinkle bread with cheese, then ham.
Mix milk, eggs, mustard and salt together in a blender, then pour over the ham layer.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until firm.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook sugar, milk, butter and cocoa for 1 1/2 minutes.
Start counting when mixture has reached full rolling boil.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, oats and peanut butter.
Stir well until blended.
Spoon onto waxed paper to cool.

title: coney island hot dogs
directions: Brown meat; add remaining ingredients except hot dogs and buns.
Simmer until thick, about 1 hour.
Cook hot dogs.
Place in buns; top with hot sauce.
Makes about 3 cups sauce, enough for 12 to 16 dogs.

title: old fashion lemonade
directions: Gently boil sugar, 1 cup water and lemon peel in small pan, 8 to 10 minutes, until sugar is dissolved and mixture syrupy. Remove lemon peel and cool to room temperature.

title: breakfast pie
directions: Use a glass 9-inch pie dish.
Form crust into dish.
Brown loose sausage with chopped onion, green pepper and mushrooms. Drain grease well.
In a bowl, beat eggs, whipping cream, salt and pepper.
Add cheese.
Add sausage mixture.
Pour into pie dish. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve with home fries.

title: garlic baked chicken
directions: Dredge chicken in flour, seasoned with salt and pepper.
Melt 1 stick of margarine in frypan; stir in 2 cloves garlic.
Brown chicken in garlic butter.
Melt 1 stick of margarine in baking dish with 1 clove chopped garlic.
Add browned chicken and drippings to baking dish.
Pour in broth.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil and remove meat from fryers, saving broth.
Saute in oleo the following: onions, bell pepper and chopped celery.
Then add pimentos and soups.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Do not drain.
Pour in casserole.
Add all ingredients, then top with hoop cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tapioca cream pudding
directions: In saucepan, bring 1 quart of water to a boil and add tapioca to boiling water; simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Drain water.
In double boiler, put milk, salt and drained tapioca.
Cook until tapioca is transparent (about 1 hour).
Stir occasionally.
Beat sugar into egg yolks and slowly stir into tapioca.
Mix stiffly beaten eggs and add vanilla.
Serves 4.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs with fork until fluffy. Add melted margarine and all other ingredients.
Pour into two unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 45 minutes.

title: quick turtles candy
directions: Arrange 3 pecan halves into a cluster.
Place clusters 2-inches apart on a Pam sprayed baking sheet.
Top each cluster with one caramel, slightly flattened.
Bake at 300° for 8 minutes. Top each cluster with 1/2 square of a 1/2 pound Hershey bar while still warm.
Spread chocolate when melted.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together the butter and Crisco.
Add sugar and eggs. Sift dry ingredients together.
Add vanilla and dry ingredients alternately with milk to the creamed mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: refrigerator date roll
directions: Set aside 1 cup crumbs.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Spread the 1 cup crumbs on wax paper.
Form a long roll with the mixture.
Punch holes with finger all down log.
Put cherry in each hole.
Then pinch together.
Roll in crumbs, then wrap tightly in wax paper and refrigerate at least 12 hours.
Slice and serve.

title: zucchini ham pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a mixing bowl, combine evaporated milk, egg substitute and nutmeg.
Stir in zucchini and deviled ham.
Combine cornstarch and cheese; add to mixture.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: pineapple delight cream pie
directions: Blend milk and juice.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crusts and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: sweet and sour dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients; shake well.

title: carmen's crock-pot chili
directions: Brown meat; drain fat.
Put in crock-pot in order given. Stir, cover and cook on low for 4 to 5 hours or high for 2 1/2 hours.

title: toni's chili
directions: Brown beef.
Drain well.
Mix with other ingredients.
Simmer for one hour or longer.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Lightly butter bread and cut into cubes. Place in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Fry bacon.
Crumble pieces and sprinkle over bread cubes.
Spread cheese over all.
Beat eggs and milk.
Pour over all. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: fish kabobs
directions: Combine the oil, juice and mustard in an 8 x 8 inch glass baking dish. Stir to blend. Cut the fish into sixteen 1 inch cubes. Add in one layer to the marinade. Cover and marinate in the refrigerator for 5-10 minutes. Turn the fish cubes to coat evenly and chill 5 minutes longer. Preheat the broiler. Drain the fish cubes, reserving the marinade. Separate the onion layers slightly. Thread the fish and vegetables onto four skewers, alternating fish cubes with onions, peppers and tomatoes. Brush kabobs lightly with the reserved marinade. Place the skewers on a broiler pan and broil 4 inches from heat source, about 3 minutes. Turn the kabobs and brush again with the marinade. Broil for 3-4 minutes longer or until the fish is no longer translucent and the vegetables are crisp tender. This has 6 grams carbohydrates.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix and pour over ice.

title: sand art brownies(gift in a jar)
directions: Place all ingredients in a wide mouth jar in order from top to bottom.
Include a decorative tap with instructions for making brownies:
Combine contents of jar with: 1 tsp. vanilla, 2/3 cup vegetable oil and 3 eggs.
Pour into a greased 9x9 pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 27-32 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: block party beans
directions: In large Dutch oven, brown beef and drain off fat.
Add onion and celery.
Cook until tender (may need to add a little water). Stir in soup, tomato paste and catsup.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes. Spoon into large kettle or roaster.
Add remaining ingredients (drain all beans), and stir well.
Bake uncovered at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine spinach, sour cream, mayonnaise and mustard in a large bowl.
Stir in envelopes of spring vegetables, water chestnuts and green onions.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
To serve, stir well and spoon into hollowed bread round.
Arrange bread cubes, crackers or fresh vegetable pieces around bread for dipping.

title: applesauce cake roll
directions: In a small mixer bowl, beat eggs until thick.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add 1 cup of the applesauce.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon, salt and cloves.
Fold into egg mixture.
Spread in greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, or until done.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Cook meatballs in skillet; remove and drain fat from skillet. Mix brown sugar and cornstarch in skillet.
Stir in pineapple (with syrup), vinegar and soy sauce.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly; reduce heat and add meatballs.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, 10 minutes.
Stir in green pepper.
Cover. Simmer until crisp and tender, 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: old-fashioned pound cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually and cream after each addition, using low speed on mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat after each addition.
Add salt and mace to measured flour and sift approximately 6 times.
Add flour gradually to egg mixture and beat after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Pour in large-sized tube cake pan, lightly floured.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, soda and vanilla in bowl.
Add flour slowly, then add nuts.
Pinch and roll in palm of hand into little balls; flatten by pressing both hands together.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: apple lasagna
directions: Cook noodles in large pot of boiling water. Drain. Spread 1 can pie filling in greased 9 x 13 baking pan. Layer 4 noodles over filling. Combine next 5 ingredients in large bowl. Mix well. Spread evenly over noodles. Layer remaining noodles over mixture. Spoon remaining pie filling over noodles. Combine remaining ingredients in small bowl. Sprinkle on top. Bake for 45 minutes. Let stand for 15 minutes. Yields 12 servings.

title: coconut raspberry jam cake
directions: Prepare and bake the cake mix for 2 (9-inch) round cake layers, adding 2/3 cup of the flaked coconut to batter.
Cool and remove from pans.
Reserve 1 tablespoon of raspberry jam.

title: cracklin bread
directions: Cut cracklins in small pieces; pour 1/2 cup hot water over them.
Add to the meal.
Add additional water and the salt to mix into a dough.
Let stand 5 minutes and if too stiff, add more water.
Put in an iron greased skillet that has been heated on top of stove.
Then put in hot oven and bake at 400° until brown.

title: crocodile dumplings
directions: Cut up hotdogs 1 to 1 1/2 in long pieces. Place in saucepan with jelly and mustard. Bring to a boil and boil 10 min. Can add cola or BBQ sauce to thin.

title: lime salad
directions: Add boiling water to gelatin.
Stir until dissolved; do not cool.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Fold in ice cream until it melts. Pour in loaf pan and chill until set.
Slice and serve on lettuce or as a dessert.

title: orange sherbet punch
directions: Whip slightly softened ice cream and sherbet until blended and smooth.
Gradually stir in ginger ale.
Spoon into small glass cups.

title: seven day sweet pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and cover them with boiling water; let stand 24 hours and drain.
Repeat each day for 4 days using fresh water each time.
On the fifth day, cut cucumbers in 1/4-inch rings.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix butter, Crisco and sugar.
Cream together. Add eggs.
Add flour, baking powder and milk.
Mix well and add vanilla flavoring.
Mix well.
Cook 1 1/2 hours at 325° in a tube pan that has been floured and greased.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Dough will be soft.
Do not add more flour. Mix all ingredients and chill several hours.
Roll into walnut sized balls and flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
(You can sprinkle extra sugar on them if you like.)
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown on edges.
Makes 80 to 100 cookies.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer over low heat until cream cheese is melted.
Serve with vegetables or chips.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems of mushrooms; wash and drain.
Place on foil of lined cookie sheet.
Stuff mushrooms and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: roast beef barbecue
directions: Brown hamburg with onion.
Add to other ingredients (use gravy from roast beef, do not drain).
Add water or 1 (8 ounce) tomato sauce if too dry.
Heat and serve on hamburg buns.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a food processor fitted with a steel blade; blend until smooth.
Chill for at least 1 hour. Makes 3 1/2 cups or 10 servings.

title: shrimp cheese ball
directions: Blend everything except crushed nuts together; place in covered bowl (with Saran Wrap and tinfoil).
Set in refrigerator overnight.
Next day, roll in crushed nuts.
Refrigerate overnight to firm.
Makes 2 balls.
Serve with crackers.

title: peking shrimp
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients.
Heat corn oil in skillet; add shrimp and cook for about 3 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add sauce and remaining ingredients.
Boil for 1 minute, stirring gently.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: berry good hawaiian upside down cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Butter a 9-inch pie pan.
Combine the crushed cookies with the melted butter and mix well.
Set aside.
Spoon the blueberry pie filling into the prepared pie pan. Combine all the remaining ingredients and beat with an electric mixer until well blended.
Spoon over the blueberry pie filling and top with the cookie crumbs.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until cheesecake is set in center.
Cool.
When ready to serve, spoon into small dessert bowls and top with a dollop of whipped cream or Cool Whip, if desired.

title: delmonico potatoes
directions: Melt butter.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk. Cook and stir until thick.
Mix sauce with diced potatoes.
Turn into a greased 12 x 18-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cut up cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: taco salad
directions: Marinate beans, chopped onion and 1/3 jar Wish-Bone at room temperature for 2 to 3 hours.
Add browned meat, chopped tomatoes, chopped olives, lettuce and grated cheese.
When ready to serve, crush chips in their bag and pour into salad.
Add rest of Wish-Bone dressing and toss entire mixture.

title: 7 can soup
directions: Note:
You can use another can of vegetable soup instead of chili without beans.

title: sue's chess pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk and melted butter.
With mixer, beat in the eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Pour into a deep-dish pie shell and bake in a 350° oven until set, about 45 minutes.

title: salsa dip
directions: Combine ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with tortilla chips

title: rhubarb marmalade
directions: Simmer until sugar dissolves.
Turn up heat and boil 20 minutes or until thick.
Just before it is done, put in nuts. Seal in jars.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour; set aside.
Combine eggs and the next 3 ingredients.
Add sugar mixture, stirring well.
Stir in 2/3 cup coconut; pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining coconut.
Shield edges of pastry with aluminum foil to prevent overbrowning.
Bake an additional 30 minutes, or until set.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Flour board.
Work up ingredients and put in bowl.
Cut as desired and bake as normal biscuits, at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, soup, sour cream, onion and cheese together. Place in a greased casserole.
Melt some butter and pour over enough cornflakes to make a thin layer on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Cool and add 7-Up and pineapple.
Chill until firm.

title: baked chicken
directions: Cut
chicken into serving pieces. Melt margarine

roll chicken in oleo, then in cracker crumbs and flour. Place in baking dish (greased and skin side up). Bake 1 hour at 350 degrees. If not tender. reduce heat to 200 and cook 10 minutes longer. Do not cover chicken and do not turn chicken.

title: pickled okra
directions: Bring water to boil. Add salt and vinegar until salt is dissolved. Fill jars with okra; pour water mixture over okra. Add 1 dill head and 1 clove of garlic to each jar. Seal.

title: pork chops
directions: Layer pork chops into slow cooker.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour over meat.
Cook until chops are done.

title: chicken 'n noodles
directions: Cook chicken and cut into bite-sized pieces.
Cook noodles in the chicken broth.
Place half of noodles in baking dish.
Top with half of the chicken.
Slice three of the eggs over chicken. Add 1 can undiluted soup.
Sprinkle with half the pimento and cheese.
Add a dash of Worcestershire sauce and salt and pepper. Repeat, ending with cheese.
Heat at 300° for 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: quick peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all four ingredients together good.
Drop on cookie sheet by teaspoon.
Dip each one in sugar as you drop them.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Let come to a boil, stirring all the time, and boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal; mix.
Drop on wax paper by teaspoonfuls.
Let cool.

title: mexican chili
directions: Brown onions, green peppers and garlic.
Add chili powder and paprika mix.
Add canned tomatoes; mash and let cook down some. Add ground beef and let cook about 2 hours, then add kidney beans. Cook about 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers or rice.

title: spicy beef turnovers
directions: Make 1/2 pie crust package according to directions.
Roll out as directed.
Use small round glass or cookie cutter to cut out as many circles as you can.
Keep cool until ready to use.

title: carrots casserole
directions: Melt oleo in warm mashed carrots.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to carrots, mixing well.
Beat eggs and add to other ingredients.
Pour into Pyrex baking dish and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for an additional 45 minutes.

title: italian love cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Grease and lightly flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour cake mix into pan and set aside.
At medium speed blend Ricotta, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Spoon mixture evenly over cake batter.
Do not mix (the cake rises above the cheese mixture).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool in pan on a rack.

title: hush puppies
directions: Heat 2-inch deep oil to 375°.
Combine remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls into hot oil, frying a few at a time until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: german potato salad(serves 25 people)
directions: Cook potatoes in skins until soft.
Peel and slice (not diced) into large container.
Cut bacon in pieces and fry until crisp. Keep drippings to use later.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put in blender.
Mix.
Pour into deep pie pan (ungreased). Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: christmas butter cookies
directions: Cream together oleo, sugar and 2 teaspoons water; set aside. In bowl, beat eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend all together, then chill.

title: cherry chiffon dessert
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Spoon into individual serving dishes or large serving bowl.
Chill at least 30 minutes.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Place in prepared pie shell and top with cheese.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes, or until set.
Let set 10 minutes or more before serving.
Can be made ahead and reheated or frozen.
Also may be baked in casserole without pie shell.

title: spicy pumpkin sheet cake
directions: Beat eggs in a large mixer bowl.
Add pumpkin, sugars and oil. Beat well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat well until well blended.
Spread into a greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: hand cream
directions: Mix the Unibase in the 2 cups of boiling water and glycerine. Mix well, then beat in bath oil and mix again.
Add perfume (not cologne) as desired.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package.
Grease and flour two 9 x 13-inch cake pans.
Split batter between the two pans.
Bake at about 325°.
Watch carefully, because cakes will get done sooner in shorter amount of time than usual, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: john benghetti
directions: Discolor meat in a little shortening. Add onions, peppers, salt and pepper.
Combine ingredients except noodles.
Put meat mixture in dish. Add noodles.
Put grated cheese on top.
Heat and serve.
Serve with green salad and French bread.

title: ice cream sundae dessert
directions: Stir together and press into a 13 x 9-inch pan the crushed cookies and margarine. Spread over crust the ice cream and salted peanuts.
(May use Schwans vanilla or chip and mint flavors). Freeze.

title: squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook squash per package instructions; drain.
Add onion soup mix, shredded carrots, sour cream, Cheddar cheese soup, 1/2 bag seasoned stuffing and 1/2 cup melted margarine to drained squash.
Mix.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix remaining seasoned stuffing and 1/2 cup melted margarine together.
Spread on top of squash mixture.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes, until bubbly and topping is golden brown.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Crush cheese, onion and garlic.
Add oil, mayonnaise, sour cream, lemon and lime juice and salt.
Whip until smooth.
Makes 1 pint.

title: sweet and sour meat balls
directions: Heat to boiling point.
Pour over meat balls and bake.

title: date cookies
directions: Cook diced dates in 1 cup water and cool.
Mix shortening, sugar, flour, beaten egg, vanilla, salt and baking soda.
Drop from spoon onto ungreased pan. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: party mix
directions: Melt butter in large roaster.
Add Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt.
Mix all ingredients together (melting butter first). Roast in a 250° oven for three hours, stirring every 20 minutes. Store in large glass containers with tight lids.
Will keep indefinitely.

title: peter paul mounds cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed in 2 round cake pans; cool.
Slice each in half with thread.
Combine sugar, milk, stick butter and boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add marshmallows and coconut.
Stir until melted.
Divide into thirds and cool.
Spread between layers.

title: leaf lettuce and mandarin salad
directions: Combine lettuce, celery, parsley, green onions and oranges in salad bowl.
Mix salt, sugar, oil tabasco, vinegar and mix well. Toss with salad just before serving, sprinkle almonds over top to garnish.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Beat water, eggs, peanut butter and 1/2 cake mix until well mixed.
Add rest of cake mix.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets for 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: pumpkin pancakes
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in medium bowl. Set aside. In another small bowl, mix the milk or buttermilk, egg, pumpkin, sour cream or yogurt, melted butter and vanilla. Add slowly into dry mixture. Mix until combined (will rise). Stir before cooking.

title: quick cobbler pie
directions: Melt margarine in a pie dish.
Mix remainder and pour in the dish.
Spoon the fruit filling in the dish, middle and corners. No need to stir.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cook all ingredients in saucepan for 10 minutes (except potatoes).
Place 1/2 potatoes in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour 1/2 sauce over potatoes and add rest of potatoes and remainder of sauce over them.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle pecans on top.

title: easy spaghetti and meatballs
directions: Make meat balls.
Put in large skillet.
Add chopped onion and garlic to ground meat; drain.
Add tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Simmer about 40 minutes in a large saucepan. Bring to a boil and add salt and spaghetti.
Cook about 12 minutes.
Serve meatballs over spaghetti and sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.

title: old-fashion stack cake
directions: Sift flour with baking powder, molasses, salt, soda and ginger. Mix well.
Add vanilla.
Make a roll out of dough with enough buttermilk to which the well beaten eggs have been added, to give you the consistency you can handle.
Roll as for pastry to fit 9-inch cake pans or heavy iron skillet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: creamy cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and butter; press firmly on bottom of spring-form pan.
In a large bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in condensed milk.
Add eggs and lemon juice; mix well.
Pour into prepared pan and bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until center is set.
Top with sour cream and bake 5 more minutes.
Cool and chill.
Top with favorite topping.

title: fruit cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll in ground pecans.
Serve with cinnamon graham crackers.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain well.
Add other ingredients to spaghetti and mix.
Pour salad dressing over mixture and toss. Let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Combine.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with sugar while still warm.

title: "chocolate cream pie"
directions: Melt Hershey bar over double boiler.
Add coffee, dissolved in water.
Fold in 16 ounces Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crust. Chocolate shavings on top, if desired.
Place in freezer at least 2 hours.
Remove 10 minutes before serving.

title: gourmet apple-walnut cobbler
directions: Mix together 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon and 1/2 cup walnuts. Place apples in bottom of a greased 8 1/4 x 1 3/4-inch round cake dish.
Sprinkle apples with cinnamon and nut mixture.

title: shrimp bubba
directions: Rinse shrimp in cold water; do not remove shells.
In a large casserole pan (at least 9 x 12-inch), spread shrimp evenly.
In a saucepan, melt butter over medium heat.
Add whole bottle of Italian dressing, pepper (more for a spicier dish) and juice of 1 lemon.
Heat through and pour over shrimp.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes at 350°.
Peel and eat, serving sauce in individual ramekins for dipping.
This recipe is so simple and always a hit! It's messy, so supply lots of napkins.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground chuck and corned beef; add chopped onion and green pepper.
Cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: baked beans with meat
directions: Mix good and bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cream sugar and lard.
Add remaining ingredients with enough flour to stiffen and roll out.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake until firm.

title: dottie bars
directions: You will need a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan, mixing bowls, mixing spoons, measuring cups and spoons, a spatula and waxed paper.

title: microwave creamed corn casserole
directions: *Can substitute 1/4 cup egg substitute.

title: codfish cakes
directions: Soak salted cod overnight or boil cod the day of purchase.
If you choose to boil the cod, halfway through cooking, drain water and replace with fresh water.
Continue to boil until cod falls apart.
If you choose to soak cod overnight, the next day, drain off water.
Add fresh water and boil until cod falls apart.
Drain and remove the bones.
Set cod aside.

title: green peas
directions: In a small amount of water, cook frozen peas until tender. Drain and set aside. Saute mushrooms and onions in butter. Stir in flour, sugar, paprika, salt, Worcestershire sauce and evaporated milk. Stir and cook until smooth and thickened. Add your peas and serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Prepare pie shells.
Beat eggs, sugar, salt, butter and syrup with mixer.
Stir in nuts.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: quick chili
directions: In medium size skillet, brown the ground beef.
Drain, then stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, 10 minutes.
You may use 2 envelopes of onion Cup-A-Soup, if desired.

title: blue cheese apple toasts
directions: In a small bowl, mix Blue cheese, cream cheese and milk until well combined.
Set aside.
Core apple.
Cut in half and cut into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Toss with lemon juice.
Toast bread. Spread with Blue cheese mixture and top with apple slices. Sprinkle with walnuts, dill and pepper.
Makes 6 servings.

title: 1 # rice
directions: Saute onions and mushrooms and then add rice.
Put the soup in deep dish.
Add rice mixture.
Cook at 400° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, until rice soaks up liquid.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix and pour into an unbaked pie shell at 350° until done.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Place 1 layer of uncooked noodles in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown ground beef with salt and pepper.
Spoon beef over noodles.
Spread spaghetti sauce and water over beef.
Place another layer of noodles on sauce, pressing them into sauce. Cover with foil; bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove foil.
Add all the cheese.
Replace foil and bake 15 more minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Layer crushed saltines, oysters and butter in 2-quart casserole.
Pour milk over all to cover.
Season with black pepper. Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in strawberries, pineapple and pecans.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: no crust apple pie
directions: Grease pie pan.
Dice apples, enough to fill pan.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.
Melt oleo; add 2/3 cup sugar.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Add to oleo sugar mix.
Beat egg slightly.
Add to batter and spread over apples.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: never fail peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, Karo and water until it spins a thread.
Add peanuts, stirring continuously, until it turns light golden color. Remove from heat.
Add butter, salt and soda and stir vigorously. Pour into buttered pan.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add milk, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Blend ingredients on low speed for 30 seconds. Beat on medium speed for about 3 minutes.
Spray 2 (9-inch) pans or a 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes for layers and 35 to 40 minutes for large cake.
Cake is done when tester comes out of center clean.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pans.
Cool completely.
Frost with Mocha Cream Frosting.

title: deep fried catfish
directions: Mix together flour, cornmeal, salt and pepper.
Dip fillets into milk, then dredge in flour and cornmeal mixture.
Pour corn oil into a heavy 3-quart saucepan or deep fryer, filling no more than 1/3 full.
Heat over medium heat to 375°.
Fry one layer of fish at a time, turning once, for about 1 1/2 minutes on each side.
Drain on paper towels and serve with hush puppies and coleslaw.

title: cranberry slush
directions: Mix the ingredients.
Freeze.
Serve plain or with white or 50/50 soda.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into desired loaf shape. Rub with fat and place in a heavy skillet. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: kraut and burger balls
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; form into meat balls.
Place sauerkraut in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Arrange meat balls on top of kraut.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over meat balls. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: taco casserole
directions: Cook hamburger meat with diced onion and bell pepper.
Drain. Add taco seasoning mix and prepare according to directions on back of package.
Layer tortillas, meat, beans, cheese and green chilies.
Continue to layer until all ingredients are used.
Mix soup with 1 can water.
Pour over casserole.
Top with plenty of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve topped with sour cream and black olives.
Feeds an army!

title: aunt carmen's 7-up cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs slowly and mix until light and fluffy.
Do not overmix. Reduce mixer to lowest speed and add flour, 1/4 cup at a time. Add extracts and zest of lemon rind.
Stop mixer and fold in 7-Up by hand.
Pour batter into greased and lightly floured Bundt pan or tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done (toothpick test).
Let cool on rack.

title: dena's peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar, butter and milk to a boil in a heavy pan.
Boil for exactly 3 1/2 minutes.
Do not scrape pan sides.
Remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallow cream and peanut butter.
Stir well and pour into buttered 9 x 13 inch pan.
Refrigerate for 3 or more hours.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook macaroni in boiling water for 7 to 8 minutes; drain.
Brown hamburger and onion.
Mix hamburger and macaroni.
Add pizza sauce, tomato sauce, garlic salt, sugar and oregano; mix well.
Pat 1/2 of mixture in casserole dish and top with Mozzarella cheese, then add remaining mixture.
Top with Parmesan cheese and thinly sliced pepperoni.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream of cabbage soup
directions: Combine cabbage, celery, onion, broth, salt, seed and white pepper in a large saucepan.
Heat to boiling over medium heat; simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir to keep from sticking.
Remove from heat.
Do not drain.
In second large pan, melt butter or margarine.
Blend in flour.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and reaches a boiling point.
Add cabbage mixture with liquid.
Season as desired with salt and pepper.
Makes about 2 quarts.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together in a large bowl.
Mix wet ingredients together in a smaller bowl.
Stir liquid mixture into the dry mixture.
Turn into a 9 to 10-inch heavy skillet that has been preheated and greased with drippings.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: hashwee (chicken rice dressing)
directions: Brown meat, pine nuts and seasonings in large saucepan.
Wash and drain rice.
Add rice to meat mixture and stir.
When rice attains dry appearance, add chicken broth and water.
Stir once; bring to fast boil and reduce heat to low.
Cook for 15 minutes (or until rice is done).

title: breakfast surprise
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Add cheese and margarine.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Slice muffins in half.
Spread mixture on muffins.
Put on cookie sheet and freeze.
When frozen, pack into plastic bag and keep in freezer.

title: "party" chicken
directions: Chop beef and layer in a 9 x 13-inch casserole. Wrap each breast with bacon strip.
Put wrapped chicken on beef.
Mix sour cream and soup.
Pour on top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line bottom of pan with white bread. Brown sausage.
Drain sausage on paper towel.
Crumble sausage over bread.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over sausage.
Blend 8 to 10 eggs with a little milk and 2 tablespoons mustard.
Pour eggs over sausage.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: jello candy
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, vanilla and water.
Cook to a soft ball stage.
Beat two egg whites and add box of Jell-O.
Add syrup to egg whites and Jell-O.
Beat until stiff.
Drop on waxed paper.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Dredge chicken in flour mixture: (3-4 Tbsp. of flour, dashes of salt and pepper to taste).
Brown floured chicken in 1 stick of butter in skillet.

title: low-fat broccoli rice casserole
directions: Prepare rice as directed.
Add cooked broccoli, mushrooms, chestnuts and broth.
Mix all together.
Add seasoning and cheese. Spoon in casserole dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Top with crushed croutons.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Contains 1 gm fat per serving.

title: banana blueberry pudding pie
directions: Line pie plate with vanilla wafers. Top with bananas and blueberries. In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth. On low speed, beat in water and pudding mix until smooth. Chill 10 minutes. Fold in whipped topping. Pour into prepared pie plate. Chill. Garnish with blueberries and banana slice, if desired. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: sweetened dill pickles
directions: Drain liquid from pickles.
Quarter pickles.
Bring other ingredients to a boil and pour over pickles.
Let stand 24 hours. Put pickles back in jar and pour hot liquid in over them.
Seal.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Boil hen in 3 quarts salted water until tender.
Remove from broth.
Set chicken aside and reserve broth.
Take cornmeal and salt.
Add enough water until smooth and slightly soupy.
Grease iron skillet.
Add cornmeal mixture and bake at 400° until lightly brown.
Add to broth and allow to set awhile to absorb broth.
Cook diced onion and celery in 2 tablespoons margarine and enough water to cover.
Done when clear and tender.
Add all to chicken broth and bread.
Crumble crackers fine and add to broth mix.
Beat eggs until frothy.
Add slowly to broth mix to prevent quick-cooking or clumping of eggs.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Use potato masher to make mixture soft and slightly soupy.
May add canned broth if necessary.
Grease well one large baking pan.
Pour in mixture. Then add corn oil on top for browning.
Cook at 400° until brown, but soft in center.
Best served hot.

title: any berry ice cream
directions: Soften gelatin in water; dissolve in warm evaporated milk; add 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla.
Stir until dissolved.
Add Cool Whip. Combine crushed berries with sugar to taste, lemon juice and rind; let this mixture set for 30 minutes.
Chill and freeze first mixture, adding berry mixture in final minutes of churning. Yields 2 quarts.

title: summer coleslaw
directions: Combine oil, vinegar, salt, pepper, celery seed, mustard seed, sugar and dry mustard.
Shake or beat well.
Pour over cabbage and let it stand for about 1 hour.

title: monkey bread
directions: Break or cut biscuits into thirds, fourths, or sixths depending on the sizes you want; layer in a heavily buttered Bundt pan, alternating with mixture of margarine, sugar, cinnamon, vanilla and nuts.
Top with extra nuts and sugar mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° until golden brown on top.
Let stand 5 to 6 minutes; remove from pan.
Tear off pieces with fingers.
It's a gigantic cinnamon roll!

title: cheap chicken
directions: Brown chicken in butter. Add scallions and tomatoes.
Simmer for 10 minutes. Remove solids and leave juices in pan. Raise heat to medium.
Add wine and scrape pan. Add sour cream.
Do not boil now or it will separate. Blend well.
Pour over chicken on platter and serve. Serves 2 to 4.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: In bowl, combine cake mix, margarine and eggs. Stir by hand until well combined. Press in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan. Prepare frosting with boiling water as directed on package. Spread frosting on fudge mix, keeping about 2 inches from pan edge. Sprinkle pecans and chocolate pieces over frosting. Bake in 250° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: walnut squares
directions: Mix until crumbly.
Press mixture in pan.

title: bruce's beef stew
directions: Brown meat, then put in stew pan.
Combine other ingredients with water.
Cook 3 to 4 hours on slow to medium.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add salt and boiling water.
Beat egg and add.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water; add.
Add flour and mix.
Cover and put in icebox.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften at room temperature.
Add sharp Cheddar, Ranch dressing and parsley.
Mix all together and form into a ball.
Roll in pecans.
Serve with party crackers.

title: mano's special gravy
directions: Season meat and fry until brown.
Remove meat; add flour and stir until brown.
Add onions, bell pepper and garlic.
Add meat, tomatoes and enough water for gravy.
Cook until done.
Will make a thick gravy.

title: taco salad
directions: Cut cukes, tomatoes and lettuce.
Crush chips (not too small). Mix with vegetables and cheese.
Put dressing on 15 to 20 minutes before serving.

title: banana muffins
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add egg, soda and vanilla; mix well.
Put mashed banana into a 1 cup measuring cup; add milk to make 1 cup.
Alternate banana-milk mixture and flour, 1/2 cup flour at a time, into sugar/margarine mixture.
Fill muffin tins 1/2 to 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 to 15 muffins.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Beat eggs, pumpkin filling, sugar and oil until fluffy.
Mix flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt, and baking soda.
Blend well with first mixture.
Grease and flour a jelly roll pan.
Pour mixture in jelly roll pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes; cool.

title: golden puff
directions: Cover the bottom of a 12 x 8-inch baking dish with half a "stack pack" of crackers.
Cover the crackers with the sliced Velveeta.

Top with the chopped onion and the remaining crackers. Over this, pour a mixture of the eggs, milk, mustard and pepper. Set the casserole aside for 1 hour, then pop it into a 325° oven for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika, and there's your fluffy light cheese main dish!
Serve it at once.

title: egg-vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill until ready to serve.
Serve with vegetables or crackers.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake in greased pan for 25 minutes in 300° to 325° oven.
Cool and dust with powdered sugar.
These are good.
I usually double this recipe.

title: strawberry goody
directions: Layer all except Cool Whip in large bowl or small serving glasses.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: sunday dinner carrots
directions: Place carrots in ungreased 9-inch baking dish.
Add water; dot with butter.
Sprinkle with oregano and salt.
Cover and bake at 325 degrees for 1 1/4 hours or until tender.
Yields:
8-10 servings.

title: chile rellenos squares
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Beat eggs in large bowl.
Blend in sifted flour with baking powder and salt.
Add chiles, cottage cheese and shredded Jack cheese.
Mix together and put in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake 35 to 40 more minutes.
Recipe may be halved for smaller size.

title: pudding cake
directions: Bake cake and cool in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together cream cheese, pudding mix, milk and pineapple.
Spread on cooled cake. Top with Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Beat eggs and mix with milk.
Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper; dip in egg mixture and dredge in flour.
Melt butter or margarine in frying pan with the oil.
When hot, but not smoking, add 4 or 5 pieces of the chicken at a time and cook just until brown.
Do not use a high heat or the flour will burn.
Place chicken in a pan large enough for one layer.
Fry rest of chicken and place in oven pan.
Put into a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mushroom sauce
directions: Put soup
in a saucepan over low heat.
Add mustard and lime juice.
Heat
sauce
and
mix well.
What you want is the tang of the
mustard and a hint of lime juice.
Do not use too much lime juice,
it is overbearing.
This sauce is excellent over asparagus and grilled shark meat.

title: bran muffins(diet)
directions: Mix together all dry ingredients.
Add the rest of ingredients.
Bake at 375° or until done.

title: nappa cabbage salad
directions: Saute almonds, noodles and seeds in butter; set aside.

title: spinach swirl turkey loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with nonstick cooking spray.
In small bowl, blend tomato sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
In medium bowl, combine turkey, bread crumbs, onion, egg white, oregano and tomato sauce (reserve 1/3 cup tomato sauce); mix well.
On foil, form turkey mixture into a 12 x 8-inch rectangle.
Spoon spinach on turkey mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Roll up tightly, starting at short end.
Place in pan, seam side down.
Press to seal edges.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes or until turkey is browned.
Spoon remaining sauce over loaf.
Bake 5 minutes more.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar together.
Add pumpkin and vanilla; mix well.
Sift the next 6 ingredients together and add to batter.
Mix together well.
Add raisins.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Makes 9 dozen small cookies.

title: boston cream candy
directions: Cook all except vanilla and nuts to soft boil stage.
Beat until thick.
Add vanilla and nuts, beating until thick.
Pour into greased dish (9 x 13-inch).
Cut into squares.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water; set aside.
In a large bowl, mix 1/2 cup sugar, 1 cup warm water, the oil, eggs and salt. Add yeast mixture.
Add 4 cups flour; mix with spoon.
Let stand overnight on counter.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix together. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: grandma's lime cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs, powdered sugar and butter. Place 1/2 of mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cheese (room temperature), sugar and vanilla.
Dissolve jello in boiling water and add to cheese mixture immediately.
Stir with fork until combined.
Beat chilled evaporated milk until fluffy.
Fold into jello-cheese mixture. Pour into crumb lined pan, add remaining crumbs to top and refrigerate overnight.

title: manicotti(power level: high, 100%; total cooking time: 13 to 16 minutes)
directions: Place ground beef in a 1-quart casserole.
Add onion, salt, garlic, parsley, basil and oregano.
Microwave on High (100%) for 3 to 4 minutes or until meat is no longer pink.
Stir halfway through cooking time.
Drain off excess grease.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain all cans of beans.
Place in large bowl.
Add green pepper, celery, pimiento and green onion.
Set aside.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil in heavy saucepan.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and immediately pour over vegetables. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add caraway seed and raisins.
Beat eggs; add milk to them.
Mix with dry ingredients.
Grease and flour 2 small round pans or 1 large round pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes; turn oven to 325° and bake for 15 minutes.

title: ozark apple pudding
directions: Beat egg and sugar together until very smooth.
Mix together flour, baking powder and salt; stir into egg mixture.
Stir in walnuts, apple and vanilla.
Turn into greased and floured 1-quart baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes four servings.
Good with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Mix caramels and 1/3 cup milk.
Melt over low heat.
Mix cake, 1/3 cup milk, 1 1/2 sticks Parkay and pecans.
In a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan, place 1/2 of cake mixture.
Bake 6 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Place chocolate chips on top, then pour the melted caramel on.
Add remaining cake mixture. Bake 16 minutes.
Remove and cool before cutting.

title: frosty apple salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add mayonnaise and lemon juice. Beat with a wire whisk until blended.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in undrained pineapple, apples, celery and nuts. Chill until firm.
Use a 6 cup mold.

title: golumpki
directions: Prepare the cabbage by coring it, then pour boiling water into it.
Carefully remove leaves, using the tough outside and any broken pieces to line the pot.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
You may pour tomato juice over the leaves before baking.

title: greens
directions: Wash greens thoroughly.
Strip leaves from stems.
Put greens in a pot and add water, salt pork and salt.
Cover tightly, bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer until tender.
The longer they cook - the better they taste.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Put beef, chicken and pork in a pot covered with water.
Cook at slow boil until meat slides off bone.
Take meat up.
Save broth and remove the bones.
Run through a meat chopper or cut up in fine pieces.
Add 2 cups of water (hot) to broth and bring to a slow boil.
Add potatoes, cabbage and onion.
Cook 20 minutes. Stirring with a wooden fork, add corn, ketchup and tomatoes and cook for 10 minutes.
Add 2 teaspoons salt; add meat slowly, stirring.
Add pepper, vinegar and remaining salt.
Cook 10 minutes longer.
Add butter and milk last and pour milk slowly.

title: french toast
directions: Mix eggs, milk and salt.
Dip bread in egg mixture.
Fry in butter, 2 to 3 minutes per side.
Serve with syrup, jelly, honey or sugar.

title: light moussaka soup
directions: Brown lamb shank in oven for 1 hour at 325°.
Remove meat from bone.

In large pot, place beef broth, shank bone and all other ingredients. Bring to a boil and simmer for 30 minutes. Meanwhile, cut up the meat removed from the shank into small pieces, removing fat and grizzle.
Add meat to the soup at end of simmer time, first removing the shank bone.
A small piece of toast may be put in bottom of each soup bowl, topped with 1/2 teaspoon grated Gruyere cheese.
This adds additional flavor. Serves 4 to 6.

title: lemon refrigerator cake
directions: Line a 9 to 10-inch spring-form pan, bottom and sides, with split ladyfingers (round side to outside).
Whip the Pet evaporated milk in bowl 1 and set aside.
In bowl 2, mix together:
lemon jello, boiling water, sugar, and the grated zest and lemon juice of the 3 lemons.
In small bowl or measuring cup mix unflavored gelatine with 1/4 cup cold water until dissolved.
Mix into bowl 2. Fold bowl 2 into bowl 1 and pour into prepared pan.
Whip the whipping cream and top cake.
Garnish with grated lemon zest. Chill at least 6 hours.

title: ground beef porcupines
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and shape into balls.
Brown in 2 tablespoons oil.
Place in casserole.
Dissolve bouillon in water. Add soup, Worcestershire sauce and sour cream.
Bake covered 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve topped with Chinese noodles.

title: whipped cream cake
directions: Mix the ingredients all together and put in cold oven.
Set oven at 325°
and bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: buttermilk jello salad
directions: Place jello and pineapple with juice in saucepan.
Heat over low heat until jello is dissolved.
Cool.
Add buttermilk.
Stir well and add Cool Whip and nuts.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill overnight.
Great served on lettuce leaves or in stuffed tomatoes.

title: broccoli casserole (1)
directions: Cook broccoli according to package, except not as long.
Drain and place in buttered baking dish.
Place stuffing mix on top of broccoli.
Drain mushrooms and put on top of stuffing mix.
Mix chicken soup with not quite one can of water (or use half water/half milk).
Pour over top of stuffing.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: avocado dip
directions: Mix sour cream and soup mix well.
Put avocado through blender or mash with fork.
Add avocado to sour cream and soup mix and stir well.
Serve with veggie sticks or corn chips.

title: nacho dip
directions: Mix bean dip, sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning well. Spread this mixture into the bottom of a glass or Tupperware square dish.
Layer green onions, tomatoes, olives and cheese. Serve with nacho chips.

title: chili manicotti
directions: In a skillet, saute onion and garlic in hot oil until tender; stir in black beans, tomato sauce and oregano; heat through.
Cook manicotti in boiling water 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain; set aside.

title: arroz con mariscos y lomo(rice with shellfish and pork)
directions: If lobster tails are used, cut into thirds, right through shell.
Cut pork into 1/2-inch cubes.
In heavy skillet, heat oil with garlic; when browned, discard.
Add pork to oil; cook until lightly browned.
Add pimento and onion; cook until onion is soft. Add lobster; cook until shell begins to turn red.
Add rice; stir to coat with oil.

title: vegetable salad - marinated
directions: In a small bowl, stir together the olive oil, lemon juice, oregano, garlic, salt, pepper, minced onion, celery seed and parsley.

title: frozen fudge fun day sundae
directions: Combine crushed cookies and melted margarine for crust.
Press lightly into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2 pan.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello with hot water. Add cranberry sauce.
Mix well. Stir in pineapple and nuts.
Let congeal.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Combine butter, water, salt, cumin, syrup and pepper or Tabasco sauce in a saucepan and bring to a simmer.
Toss mixture with one pound of pecan halves.
Spread a single layer of coated pecans on a foil lined cookie sheet and bake at 250° for 1 hour, turning every 15 minutes.
Bake an extra 15 minutes for crispier pecans.

title: betty salad
directions: Put first 6 ingredients in blender and blend.
Pour over the remaining ingredients, mix and serve.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Use large oblong 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Grease pan; spread pineapple over the bottom.
Spread blueberries next. Sprinkle half the sugar, then cake mix over sugar.
Next sprinkle the pecans.
Drizzle melted margarine.
Sprinkle last half of sugar.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Pierce the top of crunch 4 to 5 times.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: j.f.g. brownies
directions: Cream mayonnaise and sugar.
Add vanilla; blend alternately flour and coffee, blend until smooth.
Pour into a buttered and floured 9 x 13-inch baking sheet.
Top with pecans.
Bake 40 minutes in 350° preheated oven.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a small mixing bowl; beat well. Add milk, corn and salt, stirring well.
Melt butter in a 1 1/2-quart casserole; pour in corn mixture.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 60 minutes or until firm and golden brown.
Yields 4 servings.

title: recipe for friendship
directions: Stir together until lumps and bumps are dissolved, then carefully pour into heart-shaped containers.
Sprinkle abundantly with patience, understanding, tolerance, humor, caring, compassion, tenderness, and dependability.
Warm gently and serve generously.

title: pumpernickel dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill several hours.
Scoop a round hole in bread and slice the bread without cutting through the bottom.
Put dip in center of bread.
Break bread off and spread dip with cocktail knife.

title: oh so good pie(1920)
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding eggs last.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 5 minutes in 450° oven.
Lower heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together, then add the rest.
Cook on top of stove until it gets thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: quick and messy-less pie crust
directions: Mix until it forms a ball. Roll out and put in pan.
Makes only 1 crust.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Combine in saucepan tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt, oregano, onion, salt and pepper.
Simmer mixture uncovered.
Brown ground beef, drain fat and add to sauce.
Simmer for 2 1/2 hours.
Cook lasagna noodles.
One-half teaspoon oil added to water prevents noodles from sticking.
Drain.
Mix cottage cheese with beaten egg. Grate Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Layer items in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Start with 1/4 of meat sauce.
Add 1/2 of the noodles, then add 1/2 cottage cheese mixture, 1/3 of the Mozzarella cheese and 1/2 of the Parmesan cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with meat sauce topped with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake until bubbly, 30 to 35 minutes, covered.
Remove from oven; let stand 15 minutes. Yield:
8 servings.
Carbohydrate 31 g, protein 33 g, fat 20 g, calories 436.
One serving = 4 meat low-fat exchange, 2 bread starch exchange, 2 fat exchange.

title: bacon bagel snacks
directions: On bagel, put 1 teaspoon dressing.
Spread.
Sprinkle with bacon and onion.
Put in pan.
Broil until hot and bubbling. Serve hot.

title: mexican chicken and rice
directions: Bring chicken, salsa, taco seasoning mix and water to boil in a large skillet; cover. Simmer 10 minutes. Return to boil. Stir in Minute rice. Sprinkle with cheese (and olives, if desired); cover. Cook on low heat 5 minutes. Serves 4.

title: icebox cheesecake
directions: Mix Jell-O, hot water and 1/2 cup sugar. Chill in refrigerator until partially congealed. Mix 1/4 cup sugar, vanilla, juice of 1 lemon and grated lemon rind (or 1/4 cup lemon juice) with 1 package cream cheese. Chill and whip evaporated milk. Add Jell-O mixture and beat. Add cream cheese mixture.

title: crawfish fettucini
directions: Saute all seasonings in butter.
Add soup.
Stir in flour. Cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Add crawfish.
Cook on low fire 10 minutes. Add parsley, cheese, milk and sprinkle Parmesan on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
You may freeze and bake when ready to serve.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or celery

title: ozark pudding
directions: Beat eggs and sugar for considerable time, until it is very smooth.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt and then stir into egg sugar mixture.
Add apples, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in buttered casserole in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.
(This sometimes falls, but does not hurt the pudding.)

title: cowboy supper
directions: Brown onion and ground beef and drain. Add corn, Ro-Tel and tomato sauce. Boil rice separately. Add rice to mixture. Cover with cheese and simmer until cheese has melted.

title: white fudge
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add sugar, milk and salt.
Cook until it begins to boil.
Time it for 10 minutes, stirring constantly. After 10 minutes, test a small amount in cold water; if it rolls into a ball, it is done.
If it's not done, cook 1 more minute. Take off fire.
Add vanilla morsels and marshmallow cream.
Mix well, then add nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been greased with butter.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter until fluffy; beat in eggs, 1 at a time.
Add milk and vanilla wafers alternately.
Fold in coconut and pecans.
Spread batter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.
This cake freezes well.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Pound chicken breasts flat; top with cheese and ham slices. Cut these 2 1/2-inches smaller than chicken breasts.
Fold in half and press edges together.
Lightly coat with flour and dip into 2 beaten eggs with a pinch of salt.
Coat with bread crumbs; press on firmly.
Saute in butter or margarine until lightly browned, 3 to 4 minutes or until done.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients to make the amount of salad desired.
Wash the juices from the can of Ranch Style beans; drain well and add to salad.
Crunch Fritos and taco chips; mix with salad.
Dress with Catalina dressing.

title: white crumb cake
directions: Mix and then spread mixture in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Poke holes in batter about 2 inches apart.
Put small dabs of margarine in holes.
Bake at 350° for about 25 to 35 minutes.

title: monster bubbles
directions: Gently mix all ingredients in a bucket.

title: peach crisp
directions: Cut margarine into first 4 ingredients.
Slice peaches and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon and place in 9 x 9-inch buttered pan.
Sprinkle flour mixture over peaches and pour over this cold water.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple rolls
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening; add milk.
Roll in oblong sheet 1/4-inch thick.
Brush with melted butter.
Cover with apples.
Sprinkle with 1 cup sugar and cinnamon which has been mixed.
Roll like a jelly roll.
Cut in slices 1 1/2-inches thick.
Place rolls, cut side down, in pan.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: easy and quick meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in muffin tins or a loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or less in muffin tins.
Loaf pan may take longer.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into casserole dish. Sprinkle Ritz crackers on top with butter pats.
Bake at 350° until crackers brown.

title: spicy apple walnut loaf
directions: Mix and sift flour, baking soda and spices.
Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Stir in flour mixture, alternating with the apples and the 3 tablespoons of cider vinegar, mixed with the water to make 3/4 cup of the vinegar liquid.
Stir in walnuts. Pour into greased 11 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Cool.
Makes one loaf.

title: deep dish chicken pot pie
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter until tender.
Add flour and mix well.
Gradually add stock, stirring and cook slowly until medium thick.
Season to taste and set aside to cool.

title: kielbasa bake
directions: Cut kielbasa in 4-inch pieces and place in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Put sauerkraut around meat.
Put shredded cabbage on top. Add pepper to taste. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Good with parsleyed potatoes.
Serves 4.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Add enough flour to other ingredients to make a stiff dough (approximately 1 1/2 to 2 cups).
Knead and roll into biscuits or crescents.
Let rise until doubled in size.
Bake at 375° to 400° until lightly browned.
Butter tops.

title: taffy tan fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk in large saucepan.
Bring to boil. Stirring, cook for 5 minutes over medium heat until soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallow cream, peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch buttered pan and cool.

title: mama's sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter till light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Add sour cream.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla; pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 325° for 50-60 minutes or until cake test done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Yield:
24 servings.

title: shrimp steaks
directions: Mix well with water until a paste.
Add shrimp and pour into small patties into frying pan.
Cook on medium heat until brown.

title: white fruitcake
directions: Cream the butter. Add sugar and cream until fluffy. Beat eggs with rotary beater. Add to butter and sugar mixture; mix well. Chop nuts and fruit.
Mix with a portion of sifted flour.
Sift remaining flour with baking soda together. Add butter and egg mixture.
Add fruit, nuts and flavorings. Pour into a greased paper lined tube pan.
Put in cold oven and bake at 250° for 3 hours for a large cake.
Cool in pan on cake rack.
Make 5 pounds when baked.

title: cheese ball with everything
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Form ball.
Cover with 1 tablespoon poppy seed, 1/2 cup snipped parsley and few pecans.
Roll in all three.

title: barbecued green beans
directions: Fry bacon and set aside; crumble.
Saute onion in bacon grease.
Add brown sugar and ketchup to skillet of onions and simmer for 15 minutes.
Drain beans.
Mix sugar mixture and beans together, then pour into a casserole dish.
Put crumbled bacon on top.
Bake at 300° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: curried peanut dip
directions: In small bowl, combine all ingredients.
Serve at room temperature or chilled.
Garnish with peanuts.
Serve with wedges of fresh pears and apples for dipping.
Makes 2 cups.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of chicken soup

title: pudding pops
directions: Mix together. Freeze in molds.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press cookie dough into pizza pan and bake according to directions.
Blend cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla; spread on top of cooled crust.
Layer fresh or canned, drained fruit on top of this and cover with glaze.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: In a resealable plastic bag, combine the first 6 ingredients. Pound chicken to 1/2-inch thickness and cut into 1 to 1 1/2-inch pieces (or use chicken tenderloins). Place a few chicken pieces into bag and shake to coat. Heat oil in skillet; cook chicken, turning often until browned and juices run clear, about 6 to 8 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add milk, then mashed bananas. Beat eggs separately.
Add yolks then flour.
Then fold in egg whites.
Bake in loaf pan at 375° for 1 hour, then check for doneness.

title: mrs. john martin's sponge cake
directions: Beat together egg yolks, water and flavoring, then add sugar and beat again.
Sift together remaining ingredients.
Add last 5 egg whites, beaten until very stiff.
Bake at 350° or lower.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Drain fat. Mix in soup and green beans.
Pour into a baking casserole dish. Lay cheese over top.
Pour Tater Tots over the cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place broccoli in baking dish.	Follow with chicken.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
I sometimes boil the chicken and cut up into small pieces.
Sometimes I leave chicken uncooked and put on top of rice and broccoli in whole pieces.
Put rice in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put cooked broccoli on top, then chicken.
Mix soup with water and spices.
Pour over mix.
Cook at 350°
until rice (and chicken) is done, 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sugar coated peanuts
directions: Mix all four ingredients and cook until all the liquid evaporates, stirring constantly, about 30 minutes.
Spread on cookie sheet and bake at 225° for 1 hour.

title: snowflakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C). In a medium bowl, cream together shortening, cream cheese and sugar. Beat in egg yolk, vanilla and orange zest. Continue beating until light and fluffy. Gradually stir in flour, salt and cinnamon. Fill the cookie press and form cookies on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in preheated oven for 10 to 12 minutes. Remove from cookie sheet and cool on wire racks.

title: chocolate chip coffee cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add 1 cup sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder and soda.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix after each addition. Stir in vanilla.
Spread half of the batter in a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate morsels. Combine 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle half of the cinnamon and sugar over morsels. Top with remaining batter. Sprinkle with remaining cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Place chicken skin side up on top of rice mixture.
Melt 1/4 pound butter and drizzle over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
If using a glass dish, bake at 325°.
May use whole chicken or parts as desired.

title: mock lasagna
directions: Brown
ground
beef; drain.
Add onion and celery; cook until tender.
Add
spaghetti
sauce, salt and pepper; simmer for approximately 1 hour.
Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.	Add
sauce; mix well.
In a greased casserole, alternate	layers of macaroni and sauce, beginning with macaroni and
ending
with
cheese.	Bake in a 350° oven until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco, using 2 tablespoons hot water, then add the well beaten egg.
Stir in applesauce.
Mix the soda in the applesauce; add raisins and nuts.
Sift dry ingredients (pastry flour, salt, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg).
Add to mixture and mix well.
Add 2 more tablespoons hot water.
If you use spring wheat flour, use only 2 cups.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 1 hour.
Check with toothpick to see if it's done.

title: pink champagne wedding punch
directions: In a chilled punch bowl mix lemonade, cold water, champagne and soda. Stir gently.
Dip ice ring in warm water and unmold. Float flower-side up in punch.
Serves 28 (5 ounce) servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream with beater the cream cheese, peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Add milk gradually and vanilla.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour in baked pie shell.
Freeze.
Serve frozen.
Easy to cut and eat.
If left out too long it will become soft.
Use regular pie crust or graham cracker crust.

title: spinach salad
directions: Dice, fry and drain bacon.
Mix bacon fat, vinegar, water, sugar, salt and egg.
Bring to boil and cook about 1 minute or until slightly thickened.
Cool.
Pour over the spinach and onions and toss along with bacon.

title: punch
directions: Mix jello and sugar together.
Add 1 quart of boiling water, then stir well.
Add 1 quart of cold water; stir well.
Add pineapple juice and lemon juice.
Mix and freeze.

title: chicken soup
directions: Prepare leek soup according to box directions.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook all day in crock-pot or simmer on stove until veggies are tender.

title: german apple cake
directions: Combine ingredients to a pastry.
Do not overwork.
Let rest in refrigerator for a while.
Makes 1 cake crust.

title: creamy green bean soup
directions: Cook green beans and onions in water flavored with beef bouillon cubes.
Cool and put through blender.
Use 1/4 cup margarine and 1/2 cup flour per quart of blended material. Combine and cook.
Add bean puree; bring to boil.
Add evaporated milk.
Heat to serving temperature.
Serve topped with cheese and croutons.
This is an excellent way to use the green beans that have gotten too large.
Use fewer bouillon cubes to cut down on salt!

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil the first 4 ingredients 2 minutes, then stir in oatmeal and coconut or nuts.
Drop on waxed paper and refrigerate.

title: chicken narragansett
directions: Place chicken close together in shallow 2-quart casserole. Cover with dressing; cover and marinate 5 hours to overnight. Discard dressing and roll chicken in stuffing mix.
Place in casserole or cooking sheet.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Add flour and stir until smooth. Add soup and cheese.
Cook until cheese melts, stirring constantly.
Layer half each of eggs, asparagus and sauce in lightly greased baking dish (10 x 6 x 2-inch).
Repeat.
Sprinkle with breadcrumbs.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: lazy man stuffed cabbage
directions: Chop cabbage (half into pan; I use roaster pan, medium).
Top with hamburger, rice, green pepper, onion (chopped), salt and pepper to choice.
Then cover with remaining chopped cabbage, then mix soup with little water or as is and pour over everything.
Cook about 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix all together.
Place in a greased casserole dish and bake at 350° until it bubbles and browns slightly.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: taco platter
directions: Cream the softened cream cheese together with the taco sauce. Spread this on a large plate/platter.
On top, sprinkle your lettuce, tomatoes, cheese, peppers and onions.
Surround this with taco chips.

title: williamsburg inn honey dressing
directions: Mix the vinegar, sugar, honey, mustard and paprika together. Boil 3 minutes and cool.
Add the celery seed, celery salt, onion juice and vegetable oil. Beat or shake vigorously.
Serve with any fruit salad.
If kept under refrigeration, shake well before using.

title: marco polo casserole
directions: Mix all together except noodles.
Put in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish, covered.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Take out of oven and sprinkle with noodles.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes more.

title: french cream with raspberry sauce
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over the water to soften it.
Meanwhile, combine light cream and 1/2 cup sugar in small saucepan over low heat.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Add the softened gelatin and continue to stir until gelatin dissolves.
Remove from heat.
Add the orange rind and vanilla.
Cool to room temperature.
Spoon in sour cream and whisk until thoroughly blended.
Pour into a 3 cup mold, or 6 individual custard cups.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken, onions and garlic in oil.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, seasonings and green pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir before serving.

title: white chocolate sauce
directions: Heat the heavy cream in a 2 1/2-quart saucepan over medium-high heat.
Bring to a boil.
Place the white chocolate in a stainless steel bowl and pour the boiling cream over the chocolate.
Tightly cover the top with film wrap and allow to stand for 5 minutes.
Remove wrap and whisk until smooth.

title: potluck special(casserole)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in casserole dish.
Bake 40 minutes in preheated oven at 350°.

title: zucchini nut loaf
directions: In mixing bowl, beat together zucchini, sugar and egg; add oil and mix well.
Stir together flour, cinnamon, baking soda, nutmeg, baking powder and salt.
Stir into zucchini mixture.
Fold in walnuts.
Pour into a greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° until done, 60 to 65 minutes. Remove from pan and cool thoroughly on rack.
Wrap and store overnight before slicing.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter, oil and sugar; add eggs and vanilla and mix well. Combine flour, cocoa, soda, powder and spices together. Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk; and mix well. Stir in the zucchini. Pour into greased 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle with chocolate chips. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat; add onions; add all soups, sauce, chilies.
Arrange casserole:
tortillas, mixture, cheese (3 layers).
Top with cheese.

title: hamburger roll
directions: Grease 2 cookie sheets.
Brown ground beef and onion until tender.
Add other vegetables and some Worcestershire sauce.
Add soup and hot water.
Salt to taste.
Mix biscuit mix as directed. Roll dough out to 3/16 inch into a rectangle.
Set 1/2 cup meat mixture aside.
Pour meat mixture on dough.
Roll up and cut into 1 inch to 1 1/2 inch slices.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pesto ala vulcan
directions: Cook pasta (al dente); save some water after draining.
Put garlic, olive oil and basil into blender.
Blend until mixed (add water gradually, if dry).
Add 1/2 cup cheese to mixture and blend 2 minutes until thoroughly mixed.

title: hummingbird cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix well and frost cake.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth. Makes six cups.

title: sausage surprise
directions: Beat the eggs well and then add the milk.
Mix all together. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
May be made the night before and refrigerated.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: trifle
directions: Use your prettiest 1 1/2-quart bowl.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter, margarine, sugar, egg yolks and sour cream. Then add flour and beat well.
Slightly beat in egg whites a little at a time.
Do not beat batter again.
Pour in greased tube pan and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Stir together in a 2-quart glass pitcher and microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Add salted peanuts.
Stir well.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla; stir well.
Microwave on High 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Add baking soda.
Stir gently until light and foamy (quickly and carefully as it is very hot and hardens rapidly).
Pour mixture at once onto buttered cookie sheet.
Cool 1/2 to 1 hour, then break into pieces and store.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Work Crisco into flour.
Add buttermilk.
Roll out; pat tops with oil and bake in 400° oven.
You can brown the top by using the broiler after they have cooked if you would like.

title: stromboli
directions: Microwave ground meat and onion in plastic colander set in a bowl (to catch draining fat) until brown, stirring to crumble.

title: stuffed hot mushrooms
directions: Brown sausage and drain off fat.
