Add a little cayenne pepper. Stir in grated cheese.
Place mushrooms on buttered pan.
Salt lightly.
Stuff with sausage mixture and bake for 20 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: backyard potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes and eggs. Cook bacon and onion and leave a little grease to mix. Mix all together and put salad dressing on.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour in graham cracker crust pie shell.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Cut and serve.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook the vegetables until tender (about 20 to 25 minutes). The water should be cooked down. Add chicken bouillon and spices. In another pan, melt the margarine.
Add two tablespoons flour very slowly.
To this, add milk slowly.
Add cheese. Stir until melted.
Add vegetable mixture.
Warm and serve.
If you like a cheesy sauce, add more cheese.

title: german apple cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar; add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients; add to wet mixture; add nuts, apples and vanilla.
Bake in 13 x 9 inch pan for 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: graham cracker chocolate pudding
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa, butter, eggs, vanilla, water and salt. Cook on medium heat until thick.
This mixture will not be real thick when it is done.
As it cools, it will thicken.
Pour it up.

title: double orange salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and dry Jell-O until blended.
Add oranges and pineapple.
Fold in cool whip.
This recipe can be served immediately, but handles better if it can set at least 15 minutes in the refrigerator, can also be made the night before.

title: blender crab dip
directions: Place sour cream, crabmeat, garlic salt and lemon peel in blender.
Blend on medium/high for about 45 seconds, stopping to scrape sides, until smooth.
Pour mixture into a serving bowl, cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: cranberry crumb bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour and milk in with the butter.
Spread peaches over the batter.
Bake at 350 degrees for about 1 hour.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into pie crust. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until done in center.
For 1 pie use 3 eggs and half the other ingredients.
Delicious and easy. Makes two.

title: meat balls with mushroom gravy
directions: Mix ground beef with seasoning to taste and form into balls. Brown in skillet.
Place in crock-pot.
Cut up onion over meat balls.
Pour mushroom soup and water over balls.
Cook on high for about 3 hours, then turn on low or cook on low all day until ready to serve.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except fried onion topping (or potato chips).
Place in baking dish, covering with fried onion topping or potato chips.
Bake for 20 minutes at 325°.

title: pimento cheese that even kevin likes
directions: Place cubed Velveeta in blender along with pimento and Equal, if desired.
Blend in the salad dressing to desired consistency.

title: quick meat spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground chuck in large skillet over moderate heat until it loses its pink color, breaking up with large spoon as it cooks. Stir in rest of ingredients.
Bring to a boil, stirring.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.
Makes 6 cups sauce. Serve over cooked spaghetti.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add all other ingredients except corn bread batter and simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour into greased casserole pan and spread batter on top.
Bake at 425° for 20 or 25 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Heat
oven
to
Combine
all
ingredients except ground beef; mix well.
Add beef.
Mix lightly but thoroughly. Press into 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour.
When meat loaf has been
in oven about 20 to 25 minutes, take out and spread ketchup on top. Put back into oven.
Finish baking.

title: date loaf cake
directions: Cut the dates up; sprinkle soda over them.
Add boiling water. Stir them until cool and mushy.
Add butter, sugar and vanilla. Add the beaten eggs; stir well.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Cook in a Bundt pan at 350° until done.

title: chicken crescent rolls
directions: Heat cheese, soup and milk.
Put chicken in large end of crescent roll and roll up.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan, cover with sauce and bake 30 minutes at 375° or 400°.

title: zucchini marmalade
directions: Bring sugar and zucchini to a rolling boil (10 minutes). Stirring constantly, add pineapple and boil 6 minutes more. Remove from heat; add jello and stir until dissolved.
Put in jars and seal.

title: chicken salad
directions: Blend mayonnaise, lemon juice, curry powder and soy sauce. Mix with all other ingredients and chill.

title: make-ahead lemon dessert
directions: Prepare and bake cake according to package directions. Cut cooled cake into 1 1/2-inch cubes. In a bowl, sprinkle gelatin over cold water; let stand for 1 minute. Add boiling water and stir until gelatin is dissolved. Add orange juice concentrate, sugar substitute, lemon juice, lemon peel and salt; mix well. Refrigerate for 20 to 25 minutes, until partially set. Fold in 2 cartons of whipped topping.

title: tea cakes
directions: Flour
enough
to
roll out and cut with cookie cutter. Bake in a 350° oven until golden brown.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch; add beet juice and vinegar.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add butter and salt.
Add beets and bring again to boiling point.
Remove from heat and serve.

title: lasagna
directions: Saute onion and garlic in hot oil.
Add ground beef to crumble; cook until lightly browned.
Add tomato paste and water, mixing well.
Simmer uncovered 5 minutes.
Cook noodles and drain. Spoon 1/3 of sauce into 13 1/2 x 8 3/4 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish. Add half noodles and half of Ricotta.
Repeat layers and spoon on remaining sauce.
Arrange Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: cheese and meat dip
directions: Cook ground beef.
Drain well.
Melt two kinds of Cheez Whiz over low heat.
When completely melted, add ground beef.
Serve with Ruffles style potato chips.

title: sour cream pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs with brown sugar until thoroughly blended.
Mix in pumpkin, sour cream or yogurt, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg, black pepper and salt until batter is smooth.
Pour into pie shell. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour, until custard is barely set in middle.
Cool at least one hour on wire rack before serving.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: cherry oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening, butter, eggs and sugars until fluffy. Add vanilla. Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg. Add sifted dry ingredients, cherries, coconut, nuts and oatmeal. Mix well. Chill 1 hour. Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10-12 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix corn, eggs, fat, and milk.
Season with salt and pepper. Pour into greased baking dish and set in a pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° (moderate oven) until set (50 to 60 minutes).
Yield:
4 servings.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix potatoes, egg, onions and cheese.
Pack mixture on bottom and sides of 9-inch pie plate to form crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until golden.

title: chicken burritos
directions: Put small amount of salsa in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish. Mix soup, salsa, chilies and 3/4 of cheese.
Wrap pieces of chicken in burrito shells with a small amount of cheese.
Lay burritos on top of salsa in pan.
Makes about 8 burritos.
Pour soup and salsa mixture over burritos and cover with remaining cheese.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Can top with sour cream.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
Pour half of batter into greased and floured 13 X 9 pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.

title: italian style meat loaf
directions: In large bowl combine all ingredients; mix well.
Place in 4 1/2 x 8-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour; drain.
Yields 6 servings.
Preparation time:
10 minutes.
Cook time:
1 hour.

title: quick noodle burger bake
directions: Add chopped onion to hamburger; cook until tender.
Add cream of chicken soup and water; simmer while noodles are cooking.
Mix noodles into meat and soup mixture.
Pour into a casserole dish; cover with potato chips and bake until chips are hot and beginning to brown.
Or just crush chips and place on top after baking.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain on paper towels.
Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Line 8x10-inch baking sheet with 1 package crescent rolls, unrolled flat.
Layer browned sausage, green chiles and cream cheese.
Unroll remaining package of crescent rolls and place flat on top and cook according to directions on crescent rolls. Yield:
12 to 15 servings.

title: easy stuffed eggs
directions: Slice eggs in half lengthwise and carefully remove yolks.
Mash yolks; add sandwich spread and next 3 ingredients, stirring until smooth.
Spoon or pipe into egg whites.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cut peeled eggplant into 1-inch cubes and place in saucepan. Cover with water and cook until tender.
Drain thoroughly.

title: easy swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into serving-size pieces and brown in skillet.
Mix soup, Worcestershire sauce and catsup together.
Pour over steak and simmer at very low heat for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: self filled cupcakes
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on package.
Fill cupcake liners 2/3 full.
Cream together the remaining ingredients in a small bowl. Drop rounded teaspoonful on top of each cupcake.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: margaret's macaroni & cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook macaroni according to package directions until almost done.
(Completely done macaroni makes a mushy casserole.)
Drain macaroni and rinse with cold water. Grease a deep, 8-inch round baking dish with 1/3 of the softened butter.
(I use a 1-1/2 qt round casserole dish.)
Pour half of macaroni into dish.
Spread 2/3 of the cheese over macaroni.
Dot with 1/3 of the butter.
Repeat with remaining macaroni and cheese. Lightly beat eggs with fork while slowly pouring half a can of evaporated milk into mixture.
Pour egg and milk mixture over macaroni in baking dish.
Pour remaining evaporated milk over mixture until milk is level with macaroni.
Dot remaining butter over top.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350° or until sides pull away from pan.
Mixture should not be wet in the center.
Take out and cool for 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: khrusciki (bow ties)
directions: Beat egg yolks well; add other ingredients.
Roll dough paper thin; cut in strips, about 2 x 3-inch slit down center towards one end and tuck one end into the slit.
Fry in deep fat until slightly golden brown.
Drain and cover with confectioners sugar.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt margarine in 13 x 9 pan. Add ingredients in layers. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: zucchini frittata
directions: Mix together; pour into a 9 x 13-inch lightly oiled baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Can be served hot or cold, cut into squares as an appetizer.

title: brown betty cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Mix in eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, mixing well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or done when tested.

title: debby's cheesy spaghetti bake
directions: Brown the meat and onion.
Drain; add spaghetti sauce.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Cook spaghetti, drain and add to the meat mixture.
Melt butter in saucepan, stir in flour and salt.
Slowly add Milnot and water; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add 1/2 cup American cheese and Parmesan cheese, stir until melted.
Spread 1/2 spaghetti mixture in bottom of baking dish, spoon all cheese sauce over spaghetti.
Top with remaining spaghetti mixture and 1/2 cup American cheese.

title: strawberry angel food cake
directions: Dissolve jello in water and add strawberries.
When it starts to set up add cool whip and mix well.
Pour over cake that has been broken into bite sized pcs. and in a 9 by 13 in. cake pan. Refrigerate, keeps well if made the day before.

title: failproof pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs gradually.
Add milk and flavorings.
Add flour, one cup at a time.
Mix for 4 to 5 minutes.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Yields 1 tube pan and 1 loaf pan.

title: saucy vegetable baked potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Use one tablespoon Crisco oil to rub on all 8 potatoes.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done. Blend remaining 3 tablespoons oil, flour and pepper in large saucepan until smooth.
Stir in milk gradually.
Cook and stir on medium or medium-high heat until mixture comes to a boil and is slightly thickened and smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Stir in vegetables.
(Reheat on low, if necessary.) Cut open potatoes.
Top with vegetables and sauce.
Makes 8 servings.
Contains 380 calories, fat 10 g (90 cal or 24% of total calories), sat fat 3 g (7% of total calories), carb 60 g, protein 15 g, chol 10 mg and sodium 360 mg.

title: sausage balls
directions: Heat together cheese and sausage in large saucepan.
Stir with wooden spoon until cheese has melted.
Add biscuit mix and stir until smooth.
Cool, then chill for about 1 hour for easier handling.
Form into balls about the size of a nickel.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove and place on paper towels to drain.
Serve warm.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: cornmeal muffins
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a medium bowl, mixing well. Combine egg and buttermilk, mixing well. Add to dry ingredients, stirring until batter is smooth.
Place a well-greased cast-iron muffin pan in a 500° oven for 2 minutes or until very hot. Remove pan from oven; spoon batter into pan, filling 3/4 full.
Bake at 500° for 9 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yields 16 muffins.

title: veggie dip
directions: Cut up all kinds of veggies to dip into this or any kind of chips, etc.

title: taco pizza
directions: Brown meat; drain well.
Add onion, sauce, beans and seasoning.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Spread over crust.
Top with peppers, tomato, lettuce, then cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Sift flour into bowl.
Add soft (not melted) butter and sour cream.
Blend together by hand.
Roll out on wax or foil paper generously sprinkled with flour.
Cut with small cutter and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes on
greased cookie sheet.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve the
yeast
and
sugar
in
warm water.
Cream Crisco and sugar;	then
beat in the egg, salt and warm water. Add the flour, enough to make a firm dough.
Cover tightly and store overnight in refrigerator.

title: the captain's chicken
directions: Saute onions, garlic, green pepper and curry powder in the oil until the vegetables are tender.
Add the thyme, cayenne, parsley and tomatoes.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour over low heat. Meanwhile, sprinkle the chicken pieces with salt and pepper and dredge in the seasoned flour.
Fry the pieces until just done, about 10 to 15 minutes, in deep fat which has been heated to 375° or until a 1-inch cube of bread browns in 1 minute.
Place the cooked chicken in a roasting pan, add the water and sprinkle with currants.
Pour the simmered vegetables over, cover tightly and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Garnish with the roasted almonds and serve over very hot cooked rice.
Very good, I left out currants and almonds and it was still good.

title: impossible pie
directions: Place all ingredients in blender, blend for 3 minutes.
Pour into ungreased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: almond peach sundae
directions: Drain peaches and place liquid in saucepan; stir in cornstarch, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Stir in extract, almonds and peaches.
Heat through; serve warm over ice cream.

title: fresh banana cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter and lightly flour a 9-inch square cake pan.
Cream the butter slowly. Add sugar and beat until light.
Add the bananas, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well. Mix flour, baking soda and salt. Add to the first mixture and blend well.

Add the buttermilk and beat until well blended. Spread in pan and bake for about 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool in pan for 5 minutes before turning out. Split the cake and add a light cover of Cool Whip and sliced bananas. Cover with more Cool Whip.
Put top layer on and cover it, too.

title: eggplant with herbs
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve at room temperature.
Sprinkle with additional fresh herbs.

title: pastor's peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water.
Heat until sugar melts.
Add peanuts and cook until nuts begin to pop.
Turn off burner and add baking soda.
Stir well.
Pour onto a buttered pan, spreading thin.
Allow to cool.
Then remove from pan and break.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken.
After chicken is done, remove chicken and add spaghetti to chicken broth.
Chop chicken.
In large pan, melt butter, then add onion and pepper.
Cook for 1 minute.
Add peas, pimentos, tomatoes, Ro-Tel, mushrooms and cheese.
Allow cheese to melt.
Remove spaghetti from broth when done.
Add spaghetti and chicken to mixture.
Serve.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: e z apple butter
directions: Simmer apples, water and lemon juice for 30 minutes; cool. Blend well.
Add apple juice, nutmeg, cinnamon and cloves. Simmer 40 more minutes; stir often.

title: old fashioned homemade mincemeat to can
directions: Drain tomatoes in sieve to remove juice after grinding.
Boil brown sugar, water, vinegar, salt and pepper, stirring often for 2 hours, then add beef, sausage, cloves, raisins, allspice, apples, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Boil all ingredients 1/2 hour.
Put in quart jars and seal with 2 piece lids.
Put in cooker and bring to full boil.
Remove from canner.
When open for use in pies, add 1 1/2 cups water, 1/2 cup sugar and more cinnamon.
Each quart will make 2 pies.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Beat eggs well; add milk, shortening and salt.
Mix well. Then add flour and baking powder.
It may be sticky.
Flour the board well and pour mixture out.
Pat it out, then cut biscuits and bake on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: "lo-cal" pumpkin pie and diabetic
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly spray a 9-inch pie pan with vegetable spray.
Place all ingredients in blender, food processor or mix by hand in bowl.
Mix well and bake about 50 minutes or until center is puffed up.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add cheese.
In a large casserole mix together vegetables.
Add cheese mixture.
Spread bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix altogether and bake in a casserole dish for 1 hour at 375°, covered.

title: raspberry slush
directions: In blender, puree raspberries and blend with soda. Strain to remove seeds. Return to blender. Add lime juice, frozen lemonade concentrate and sugar to taste. Add ice cubes and whip until ice is crushed.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apple crunch pie
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Put into greased casserole dish. Sprinkle white sugar over apples.
Mix the flour, brown sugar and margarine until it resembles coarse meal.
Sprinkle over top of apple mixture.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pepperoni pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased cookie sheet/jelly roll pan.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cut into small squares.

title: sparkle punch for 100
directions: Mix and put in punch bowl.
Very good.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop tender parts of broccoli.
Chop onion.
Add cheese, sugar and sprinkle vinegar over broccoli and onion.
Add mayonnaise and sprinkle some bacon bits on top of salad.
Mix well.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Add rice and salt to the 5 cups boiling water and reduce heat to medium.
Cook rice for 20 minutes until water is cooked away. Mix eggs, milk and sugar in bowl.
Add cooked rice and stir.
Add vanilla, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Pour rice mixture into a greased (butter) baking dish.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until center is done.

title: fruit soup(serve as a dessert)
directions: Cook fruit. Add juice, lemon, cloves, tapioca, salt and cinnamon.
Cook until thickened. Serve cold.

title: sweet and easy pickles
directions: For 4 days, cover the whole cucumbers with clean, boiling water.
On the 5th day, drain and cut into 1/2-inch slices. Combine remaining ingredients; boil and let stand over cucumbers for 2 days.
On the third day, bring to a boil again and pour over cucumbers in jars.
Seal jars in boiling water bath.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix Jell-O and hot water until dissolved.
In blender, mix pineapple and strawberries.
Add to Jell-O and mix.
Spread in baking dish and chill overnight.

title: swedish brownies
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, butter and almond extract together until smooth.
Add flour and salt.
Beat or blend together.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: In large baking dish put cooked chicken.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cut up margarine and place around top of ingredients.
Bake at 350° until brown and crust forms on top.

title: the original red velvet cake
directions: Grease and flour two 8-inch cake pans.
Heat oven to 350°. Cream butter with sugar and add eggs.
Beat until well blended. Make a paste of food coloring and cocoa.
Add to creamed mixture. Sift flour with salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour.
Add vanilla.
Place vinegar in a small measuring bowl and add soda, holding bowl over the batter bowl as vinegar mixture foams.
Then add soda and vinegar to batter, blending, instead of beating.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Remove from oven.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool completely on wire racks.
When cool, split each layer into 2 layers.

title: 94th aero squadron quiche lorraine
directions: Saute bacon with onion and ham until onion is transparent. Mix with all other ingredients and pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: easy spoon bread
directions: Boil the corn meal and water together until thick. Add the butter and sugar and mix well. Beat the eggs and add to the milk. Stir into corn meal mix.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes in pan of water. Serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate oatmeal no-bake cookies
directions: Mix oleo, cocoa, milk and sugar.
Boil hard 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Mix and drop on waxed paper.
Cool.

title: blt salad
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese.
Add other ingredients.
Chill. Serves 4 to 6.

title: pecan rolls
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, mixing well with hands.
Shape mixture into 5 (4 x 1-inch) rolls.
Mixture will be very dry. Chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir. Chill.

title: venison stroganoff
directions: Cut meat in thin strips and wrap in foil.
Bake 1 hour.
Add to soup and sour cream.
Bake 30 minutes.
Saute mushrooms in butter before adding to mixture.
Serve on wild rice. Half brown rice may be used in place of the wild rice.

title: strawberry sparkle punch
directions: Combine strawberries and lemonade concentrate in blender. Process until well blended.
Pour into well-chilled bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Add ice, garnish with lemon slices.
Makes 18 cups.

title: watermelon rind
directions: Cover watermelon rind with cold water and set in refrigerator overnight.
Drain and rinse.
Put in boiling water and cook until clear (about 10 minutes); drain.

title: eggplant souffle
directions: Soak eggplant in salt water for 1 hour.
Drain well and cook until done.
Mash eggplant and add remaining ingredients.
Pour into buttered casserole and bake for 30 to 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: easy pot roast
directions: Put roast and vegetables in roaster pan.
Mix mushroom soup, onion soup mix and water; pour over meat and vegetables.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for approximately 2 hours.

title: spinach souffle(quick and easy)
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Mix sour cream and dry soup together. Stir into spinach. Pour into casserole.
Top with crumbs and dot with butter.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook ingredients 10 minutes.
Add raw shrimp, cut in pieces. Cook additional 20 minutes until shrimp is tender.
Serve over steamed rice.

title: coconut pecan delight
directions: Combine flour, butter and 1/2 cup chopped pecans until moistened.
Press evenly into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Allow to cool.
Toast remaining pecans and 2/3 cup coconut on baking sheet for about five minutes or until lightly browned, stirring occasionally.
Beat cream cheese until very soft.
Gradually add 1/2 cup milk and blend until smooth.
Add remaining milk and pudding mix.
Beat slowly until well blended, about 2 minutes.
Pour in remaining coconut and pour immediately over crust.
Spread whipped topping over pudding.
Sprinkle with toasted pecans and coconut.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.
Cut in rectangles.
Makes 12 servings.

title: oil vinegar sauce
directions: Put all ingredients in a glass jar.
Seal lid tightly until oil and vinegar are well mixed, 15 to 20 minutes.
Let sauce stand several hours.
Shake well a few minutes before using.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain.
Mix soup to hamburger; place in casserole dish.
Top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until potatoes are brown.
Serve hot with vegetables for complete dinner in less than 45 minutes.

title: hamburger-pasta casserole
directions: Saute meat until no longer pink.
(Sliced onions can be added, if desired.)
Add tomatoes and tomato paste; let bubble.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
(Mushrooms can be added at this point.) Place in casserole in following order:
a layer of cooked pasta; layer of meat sauce; layer of cheese, sliced.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used, ending with cheese.
Place Pepperidge Farm stuffing on top and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes, or until cheese bubbles.
Serves 8.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour with sugar and soda.
Stir butter to soften; add flour mixture, buttermilk, vanilla, eggs and chocolate.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cheese melts
directions: Cut bread in half lengthwise, then into quarters.
Top with cheese and broil until cheese melts.
Shake on one or any combination of seasonings.

title: dip for fresh strawberries or fruit
directions: Mix with mixer and serve at room temperature.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil the chicken until tender.

Remove from bones and cut into bite size pieces. Saute onion and bell pepper in a little oil. Cook spaghetti in broth from chicken. When the spaghetti is done, add chicken, soups, onion, bell pepper and pimento; let simmer. Put in a large casserole dish.
Add cheese and mix well. Cook at 350° until bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: no cook pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions into large jar.
Mix all the other ingredients together to make a syrup.
Do not boil.
Pour over onions and cucumbers.
Refrigerate for 5 days before tasting. Will keep in refrigerator for 9 months.

title: banana pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well after each addition.
Add dry ingredients alternately with bananas and milk.
Add vanilla.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes in 325° oven.

title: cathy's microwave bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix ingredients in 2-quart microwave bowl.
Microwave on High 7 to 8 minutes, stirring twice.
Ladle into hot jar.

title: jalapeno jelly
directions: Blend peppers and 1/2 cup vinegar in blender. Place in large saucepan. Add sugar and remainder of vinegar. Bring to boil. When you can't stir down the boil, remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes. Skim, then add Certo and food coloring. Stir until liquid starts to thicken. Pour into sterilized jars. Seal.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Place all ingredients in large bowl in order given, stirring well with large spoon.
Do not beat.
Pour into greased and floured 8 x 10-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serve warm or cold, plain or topped with whipped cream or orange butter frosting.
Cake will keep for long time and may be frozen.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: mexican wedding cake(do not use mixer)
directions: Stir together in mixing bowl the flour, sugar, salt and baking soda.
Add pineapple, eggs, vanilla and 1 cup chopped pecans.
Pour into 15 x 11 greased and floured sheet cake pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool slightly and frost.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream first three ingredients.
Add the next four ingredients. Roll into balls.
Roll balls in mixture of the last two ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.
Let cool.
Eat and enjoy.

title: broccoli casserole (1)
directions: Mix together broccoli and soup, then layer with slices of Velveeta cheese.
Make stuffing as directed on package.
Place stuffing on top of cheese then put another layer of cheese on top of stuffing.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Wash and separate cauliflower.
Mix Ranch dressing, milk and sugar; set aside.
Slice olives; chop onion, celery and green pepper.
Combine all ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: chiffon cake
directions: Mix and sift first four ingredients.
Make a well and add in order:
oil, egg yolks, water, lemon rind and vanilla.
Beat with spoon until smooth.
Add cream of tartar to egg whites.
Beat until whites form stiff peaks.
Gently fold first mixture into whites until well blended.
Put batter into ungreased tube pan (10 minutes).
Bake at 325° for 70 to 75 minutes.
Invert pan over bottle until cake is cool.
Loosen sides of cake.
Use with or without icing.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Pour over cereal.
Mix in enough powdered sugar to coat all pieces without breaking up cereal.
Store in refrigerator.

title: tiger butter
directions: Melt white chocolate and mix in peanut butter.
Spread in a foil-lined 9 x 12-inch pan.
Melt milk chocolate; pour on top of the white chocolate and peanut butter mixture.
Swirl through with a knife.
Let air dry until ready to cut.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Mix together all ingredients with noodles and bake in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: hot cabbage
directions: Sprinkle cabbage with salt and set aside for 30 minutes.
Heat oil in skillet until very hot.
Add the cabbage and stir-fry about 2 minutes.
Remove and add Italian dressing.
Serves 4.

title: ripe tomato relish
directions: Cook until thick and seal hot.

title: baked halibut
directions: Butter a large 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Shred fresh fillet of halibut or any fresh fish that you may have (salmon, trout, etc.) and layer into cake pan.

title: peach pie filling
directions: Cook down until very thick.
Stir to keep from sticking.
Pack into jars.
Heat lids to seal.
(Takes several hours.)

title: aunt mabel henry's sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine, then add the eggs.
Blend the vanilla, buttermilk and baking soda together.
Stir the baking powder into the flour.
Alternately mix the buttermilk and flour mixtures into the creamed mixture.

title: classic cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Mix the graham cracker crumbs, sugar, and butter together and press into an even layer on the bottom and sides of an 10 inch springform pan.
Sides do not need to be completely covered.
Bake in the preheated oven until slightly toasted, about 5 minutes.
Remove from the oven and cool. Reduce the oven temperature to 300 degrees.
With an electric mixer or a wooden spoon, cream together the softened cream cheese and sugar.
Add the lemon juice, vanilla and salt, then add the eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.

Pour the batter into the cooled crust and bake in the preheated oven until the center of the cake is no longer wobbly, about 1 1/2 hours. When the cake is cooked, turn off the oven, partially open the oven door, and let the cake cool for 2 hours before removing.
The gradual reduction in temperature will help prevent cracking. Remove the cake from the oven and cool completely at room temperature.
Run a sharp knife around the inside of the springform pan to loosen the cake, then remove the ring and transfer the cake to a serving plate.
Serve plain or top with fresh fruit or pie filling.

title: cold cherry soup(hideg meggyleves)
directions: In a large saucepan, mix pie filling and water.
Add all remaining ingredients, except cream, and stir well.
Bring to a boil over medium-high heat.
Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Cool to room temperature and add cream.
Stir and refrigerate.
Serve cold.
Serves 6.

title: smoked sausage
directions: In skillet, saute onion in 1 teaspoon oil.
Add sausage, cut in pieces.
Brown sausage.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, salt and pepper.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Cook 1 package twist or shell macaroni according to directions.
Serve sausage mixture over macaroni.

title: white pine bark candy
directions: Cover a 9 x 15-inch cookie sheet with foil.
Place single layer of crackers to cover cookie sheet.
Melt butter in saucepan. Add brown sugar and boil for 3 minutes.
While hot, pour over crackers.
Bake at 400° for seven minutes.
Watch closely.
Do not burn.
Remove from oven.
Immediately spread chocolate chips over crackers, then top with nuts.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Remove from foil and break into pieces.
Store in refrigerator.

title: scottish eggs
directions: Wrap sausage meat around hard-boiled eggs.
Roll in flour, then egg yolk and bread crumbs.
Cook in frying pan in about 1-inch cooking oil.
You can also use a deep fryer.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cook peppers in
enough boiling water to cover for 5 minutes. Cut off tops and clean inside.
Brown hamburger and onion; drain. Stir in salts, rice and 1 cup of tomato sauce.
Heat through. Stuff each pepper with hamburger mixture.
Stand upright in ungreased baking dish.
Pour remaining sauce over peppers.
Cover and cook in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Uncover; sprinkle with cheese and bake 15 minutes more.

title: bacon fried rice
directions: First, boil water, then add the rice. Cook the rice completely; drain any extra water and cover. Next, cut the bacon into small pieces. Fry the bacon until crisp, but be careful not to burn it. Drain most of the bacon grease out of the skillet. Add the bacon to the rice. Next, scramble the eggs and add them to the remaining grease. Then add them to the rice and bacon. Add salt, pepper and parsley. Mix all the ingredients together. Finally, add the soy sauce. Mix together well and serve.

title: cole slaw-stuffed tomato
directions: Dip tomatoes in boiling water for 1 minute.
Drain, peel and chill.
Hollow out a large center and fill tomatoes with cole slaw. Chill until serving time and serve on a bed of freshly shredded lettuce.
Serves 6.

title: caramel fudge
directions: Cook in heavy boiler until soft ball stage (except nuts). Beat until thick and loses gloss.
Add nuts and pour on large platter.
Cut when cool.

title: egg casserole
directions: Spread cheese in a 9 x 13-inch pan; dot cheese with butter. Combine half and half, salt, pepper and mustard.
Pour 1/2 of mixture over cheese.
Add slightly beaten eggs.
Pour other 1/2 over mixture.
Set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cover cookie sheet with brown paper
or foil.
Beat egg whites, salt and vanilla until soft peaks form. Add sugar gradually until peaks are stiff and glossy and sugar is dissolved.
Fold in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto prepared cookie sheets.
Place cookies in preheated oven. Turn heat off immediately.
Bake overnight.
"Do not open oven door." Cookies will "peel" from paper when done.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onion, garlic, mushrooms and pepper in large skillet sprayed with vegetable spray.
Add beans, tomatoes and chili powder.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Spray 1 1/2-quart casserole dish with vegetable spray.
Layer the tortillas, cheeses and sauce until all used.
End with a layer of the sauce.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: old fashioned honey wheat loaf
directions: Heat water, cottage cheese, honey and butter until warm. Combine liquid, 2 cups flour and remaining ingredients.
Beat well.
Gradually add remaining flour and knead well.
Let rise to double size.
Makes 2 loaves.
Let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Brush with butter.

title: good and easy fudge
directions: Microwave in a one quart glass container.
Cook on high for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes until all is melted.
Stir after each minute. Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Spread into a buttered 1 1/2 quart dish.
Takes quite a while to harden enough to cut smoothly.
This never sugars.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook pasta shells according to pkg. directions; drain. Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray bottom of 13x9x2 inch glass baking dish with non-stick cooking spray.
In large bowl, beat egg.
Stir in ricotta, 1-3/4 cups mozzarella, 1/2 c. of the Parmesan and the parsley.
Spread 1 c. sauce in bottom of baking dish.
Fill cooked shells with ricotta mixture.
Arrange filled shells in baking dish.
Pour remaining sauce over shells.
Top with remaining mozzarella and parmesan.
Bake, covered, until bubbly, about 45 minutes.
Uncover and cook until top cheeses are brown.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Yields:
6 servings.

title: bavarian casserole
directions: Cook hamburger and onion together, then stir in soup, sauerkraut, rice, sugar, salt, caraway seed, basil and water. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix sugar and margarine; add one egg at a time.
Add coconut, flour and baking powder.
Blend in pecans and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
While cake is hot, pour marshmallow cream over cake and spread.
Let stand for 15 minutes.

title: broccoli and cauliflower bake
directions: Melt butter and cheese. Cook broccoli and cauliflower by package directions.
Pour half of the cheese mixture over the vegetables in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Crumble crackers over the vegetables and cheese. Cover completely.
Pour the rest
of the cheese mixture over the crackers. Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: drop sand tarts
directions: Drop by 1/2 teaspoon on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 9 1/2 dozen.

title: frozen grape salad
directions: Soften cheese.
Add mayonnaise and syrup.
Mix. Add the marshmallows and drained pineapple. Fold in whipped cream and grapes.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan and cover. Freeze until ready to cut and serve on a bed of lettuce.

title: hamburger noodle casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add onions.
Brown some more.
Mix in noodles and all other ingredients (except reserving the extra 1/2 cup of cheese).
Place mixture in casserole dish and top with the 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake for about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: lunchbox favorite!  pepperoni rolls
directions: When the dough has thawed enough to tear apart, call the kids into the kitchen.
Have them form small, 2-inch balls.
When they finish, have them stick 2 to 3 slices of pepperoni in the center of each roll.
(Make sure the pepperoni is well covered with dough.) Place rolls in greased muffin pans.
When double, bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: supreme de volaille
directions: Coat chicken with flour; shake off excess.
In large skillet, heat oil and butter until hot.
Add chicken; saute over medium heat until browned and cooked through, about 20 to 25 minutes. Remove chicken to serving platter; keep warm.
Drain off all but 1 tablespoon drippings.
Add onion to skillet; saute until tender. Stir in vinegar and tomato paste.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Blend in cream; cook and stir until thickened, about 3 minutes.
Stir
in Worcestershire sauce and salt; heat until hot.
Spoon over chicken.
Yields 4 servings.

title: caesar salad
directions: Make garlic butter according to your favorite recipe and instead of slicing the French bread into slices, cut the long way down the middle.
Set on foil and spread with garlic butter.
Bake in 400° oven until golden brown.
Slice to serve.

title: pumpkin crunch
directions: Mix pumpkin, milk, sugar, eggs and cinnamon.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle 1 box yellow cake mix over pumpkin mixture.
Sprinkle pecans over cake mix.
Cover pecans with pieces of margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cool and top with cream cheese mixture (1/2 of Cool Whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar).
Use rest of Cool Whip on each serving.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Melt butter.
Pour over crushed crackers.
Salt and pepper chicken, roll in crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop onto baking sheet.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottoms only of 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) pans.
In large bowl, cream butter, sugar, vanilla and lemon extract.
Add Egg Beaters.
Add salt, cream of tartar and baking soda.
Blend together jam and cottage cheese.
Add to mixture. Add dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into pans and bake for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chex muddy buddies
directions: Combine chocolate, peanut butter and margarine.
Microwave 1 to 1 1/2 minutes until smooth.
Stir in vanilla. Pour over cereal, then into a large bag with powdered sugar.
Shake well. Lay on a pan to dry.

title: sweet and sour cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage 8 minutes.
Fry bacon and remove from drippings. Add sugar and flour to bacon fat.
Add water, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Cook until thick.
Add onion and heat thoroughly in sauce.

title: mixed bean salad
directions: Drain liquid off vegetables and save for soups, etc.
Marinate Vinegar and Oil Solution and pour over vegetable mixture.
Allow to stand overnight in refrigerator until flavors are absorbed.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onion, celery and green pepper.
Mix other ingredients together in small bowl; add to ground beef mixture.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve on hard roll buns or hamburger buns.
Yields 12 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until done.
Mix together with egg, soup, mayonnaise, onion and grated cheese.
Put in a casserole dish. Melt margarine; mix with crackers.
Put on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: chow mein
directions: Brown chicken in melted fat.
Add all ingredients except soy sauce and bean sprouts.
Cover and simmer for 40 minutes.
Add soy sauce and bean sprouts and heat thoroughly.
Thicken with 4 tablespoons of cornstarch, mixed in 1/2 cup cold water.
Stir this into hot mixture until smooth and thickened.
Serve over noodles.

title: hollandaise sauce(one serving)
directions: Melt butter in Pyrex bowl in skillet containing hot, not boiling, water.
Beat egg, lemon juice, salt and cayenne.
Add to butter.
Stir until thickens.
If too thick, add a little hot water from skillet.
Double or triple as needed.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in pie crust.
Keep in refrigerator.
Ready to eat in 1 hour.

title: pasta pizza
directions: Cook pasta; drain.
Rinse with cold water; drain again.
For pasta crust, in large mixing bowl, combine egg, milk and Parmesan cheese.
Stir in pasta.
Spread mixture evenly in greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: creamy yogurt potato salad
directions: In large bowl, stir together first 5 ingredients.
Add potatoes, onions, celery seed and pickle.
Toss to coat well. Sprinkle parsley over top and sliced hard-boiled eggs (optional). Cover and chill 4 hours.

title: baked shrimp-crab salad
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease a medium casserole dish or medium glass baking dish with butter.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops on all sides.
In shallow dish, mix rice, water, salt, pepper, onion and undiluted soup. Arrange chops in dish and cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: viva la chicken
directions: Bone and cut up chicken.
Cut tortillas into 1-inch strips. Mix soups, milk, chilies and onion.
Grease 13 x 9-inch casserole pan.
Add 2 to 3 tablespoons water or chicken broth to bottom of casserole.
Place 1/2 tortillas in pan, 1/2 chicken and 1/3 sauce. Repeat, ending with the remaining 2/3 sauce.
Cover with grated cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 300° for 1 to 2 hours uncovered until brown and bubbly.
Serves 8.
Great dish to double and freeze one for later!

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Spread stuffing mix in bottom of 1 (8 x 8-inch) casserole dish.
Reserve some stuffing mix for later.
Add oleo and broth (enough to moisten stuffing).
Add a layer of chicken over stuffing mix, then spread cream of chicken soup over chicken.
Now add another layer of chicken, then cover this layer with cream of celery soup.

title: aunt ruby quick dinner roll
directions: Mix sugar, Crisco and salt with hot water.
Set yeast aside in cup of warm water.
When yeast is ready, mix with eggs and pour into sugar and Crisco, then mix in flour and put in refrigerator at least 1 hour.
Afterward, take out and let rise and bake.

title: no foolin' homemade supper
directions: Brown meat.
Add onions and cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until heated.

title: brownies
directions: Melt shortening in large saucepan over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cocoa and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add vanilla, flour, baking powder and and salt.
Beat well.
Add 1 cup chopped nuts (if desired).
Turn into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: puffy corn fritters
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Blend milk and egg.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir in corn and drop from a tablespoon into deep, hot oil until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: orange-ginger carrots
directions: Cook carrots and drain.
Cook rest of ingredients together until thickened.
Pour over carrots.
Stir and serve.

title: greek pasta salad
directions: Prepare noodles according to package. Mix all ingredients together. Chill for several hours. Makes approximately 5 cups.

title: cinnamon frosted zucchini bars
directions: Cream margarine and sugars until fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add the zucchini.
Slowly mix in the flour and baking powder.
Fold in the coconut and walnuts until well blended. Spread in a greased 9 x 15 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake for 30 minutes, or until done.
Frost when cool.

title: mary crowley's yummy cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal and butter.
Let stand 10 to 20 minutes.
Add remaining cake ingredients and stir gently.
Do not use mixer.
Pour into buttered pan and bake 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: keenan kobbler
directions: Spray an 11 3/4 x 9 3/8 x 2 1/2-inch foil pan with a nonstick spray.
Line bottom and sides with crust.
Preheat oven to 400°.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: Heat water to boiling.
Add grape jello.
Stir to dissolve. Remove from heat.
Add pie filling and pineapple.
Stir to blend. Pour into a rectangular glass dish.
Cover and chill until firm. Finish with topping.

title: fruited cream cheese spread for quick bread
directions: Beat cream cheese and your choice of preserves in small bowl on medium speed until fluffy.
Makes 1 1/4 cups spread.

title: danish puff
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients like pie crust (pea size chunks). Divide dough in half.
Pat dough with hands to form 2 long (12 x 3-inch) strips on cookie sheet 3-inches apart.
Mix butter and water in saucepan; bring to rolling boil.
Add flavoring; remove from heat.
Add at once the flour and salt.
Stir quickly to form dough.
When smooth, add eggs, stirring constantly.
Beat until smooth and velvety.
Spread half of mixture over each.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 (12-inch) loaves.
Cool.

title: coke cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar; set aside.
Heat together in saucepan the cocoa, butter and Coke to boiling.
Pour over flour and sugar mixture.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost while hot.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into two loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: quick spoon rolls(children's)
directions: Combine baking mix, yeast and sugar in bowl.
Add egg and water, mixing well.
Spoon into greased muffin cups.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°.
Batter can be stored in covered container for up to one week in refrigerator.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken breast; mix soup, sour cream and sherry.
Place in casserole dish and pour soup mix over it.
Crush Ritz crackers, blend with butter and sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli deluxe(serves 6)
directions: Mix all ingredients; put in 6 x 10-inch flat casserole. Melt butter (2 tablespoons).
Add
cup
croutons;
spread over broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: skillet dinner
directions: Cook beef and onion in large skillet until lightly browned. Add salt, water and tomatoes; cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Mix in noodles and vegetables.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes, stirring often.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: caramel brownies
directions: In double boiler, mix 1/3 cup milk and caramels until well melted.
In bowl, mix cake mix, butter, 1/3 cup milk and nuts. Press 1/2 dough in greased 11 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top and spread caramel mixture.
Crumble rest of batter on top.
Bake an additional 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool completely (refrigerate) before cutting into bars.

title: polish cream cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese; add sugar and beat until light and feathery.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one. Beat in vanilla and sour cream.

title: english cookies
directions: Mix together brown sugar, shortening, eggs, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add remaining ingredients; mix all well.
Bake at 350° until browned.

title: watercress salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a salad bowl.
Add enough water to salad dressing to make 1/3 cup, mixing well.
Pour over salad and toss.

title: joyce's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saucepan over low heat.
Heat to boil.
Remove from heat and let stand at room temperature until cool.
Store, covered, in refrigerator.
Use over ribs, pork chops or chicken.
Makes 7 cups.

title: pot pie
directions: Mix margarine, milk and flour; pour in baking dish.
Do not stir.
In another bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Pour in baking dish on top of milk mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Add water; sprinkle brown sugar evenly in pan.
Arrange nuts and coconut in sugar mixture.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Pour cake batter over mixture in pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes and turn upside down onto cookie sheet.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: chicken wings
directions: Boil chicken wings.
Remove from pan; cool.
Put flour into a flat bowl separately.
Put broth into another bowl.
Put cracker crumbs into a 3rd bowl.
Dip wings into flour first, then into broth, then into cracker crumbs.
Put into deep fryer just enough to give a good crust.

title: seasoned crackers
directions: Put ranch dressing in bottom of a large container.
Add the remainder of ingredients (except crackers) and mix well.
Add crackers, gently toss to coat.
Refrigerate.

title: jim's tropical fruit punch
directions: Gently combine liquid and thawed ingredients.
While facing north and standing upright, add banana slices.
While sitting with knife in hand, add orange slices.
Grip firmly a large spoon and stir briskly all ingredients in a large punch bowl or small wash tub.
Serve while still swirling.
If swirling stops, well, stir it again!

title: cheesy beef enchiladas
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Stir in 1/2 cup salsa and 1 cup cheese. Spread 1 cup salsa in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Place 1/4 cup meat mixture down center of each tortilla; roll up.
Place tortillas, seam-side down on salsa.
Top with remaining 1/2 cup salsa and 1 cup cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
When served, top with shredded lettuce and diced tomatoes.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar, oatmeal and oleo together.
Put half of the mixture in a 9-inch square pan.
Add cut up rhubarb on top. Bring water, cornstarch, sugar, vanilla and food coloring to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Pour on top of rhubarb, then put the rest of oatmeal mixture on top of that and bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: cocoa cola cake
directions: Sift together the sugar and flour.
Mix in saucepan crisco oil, butter, cocoa and coke.
Bring mixture to a boil and pour over dry mixture.
This may look lumpy but beat good.
Then add buttermilk, soda, eggs, vanilla and marshmallows.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: one pot dinner
directions: Brown hamburger, bacon and onion together.
Mix all ingredients in crock-pot and cook on low up to 4 to 9 hours.

title: hodge-podge soup
directions: Slice all vegetables and cook in melted butter and water until soft.
Season to taste.
Blend all ingredients (except chicken broth and half and half) in blender, while slowly adding chicken broth.
Return to saucepan and add half and half.
Taste again for desired seasoning.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into bite sizes and place in large bowl. Add bacon, onion and raisins.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Put all ingredients in heavy saucepan and cook to hard crack stage.
Remove from heat.
Pour over 8 quarts of popped corn. Butter hands and make into balls.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add sugar and beat until mixture is smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Combine flour and soda and add to mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla; add coconut and nuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in three greased pans (9-inch).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Parboil zucchini, onion and carrot for 5 minutes.
Drain; mix soup, sour cream, onion and melted butter.
Add all to package from dressing.
Put in casserole.
Can add chunks of chicken. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Coat 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish with cooking spray.
Place rice in bottom of dish and top with chicken.
Combine water, mushroom soup and onion soup mix, stirring to blend.
Pour over chicken.
Cover casserole and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until chicken and rice are done.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Divide in half.
Crumble half into a large glass punch bowl.
Top with 1 can cherry pie filling and 1 can crushed pineapple.
Sprinkle with pecan pieces.
Mix 1 box pudding as directed; spread over nuts.
Slice and layer bananas over pudding.
Top with one 8 ounce container Cool Whip.

title: fiesta corn casserole
directions: I add some milk if necessary as the corn has little juice. Combine corn, olives, pimento, onion, pepper with eggs and cracker crumbs.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into casserole.
Season with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until set like custard.

title: coconut chess pie
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Put in unbaked pie shells (9-inch).
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Makes two 9-inch pies.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Cook eggs, sugar and margarine for 2 minutes.
Cool.
Add crushed graham crackers, coconut and marshmallows.
Mix together and then press in cake pan.
Cover with butterscotch chips and peanut butter that have been melted together over low heat. Refrigerate for a few hours and cut into squares.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Cream together butter or margarine, sugar and brown sugar. Blend in egg, peanut butter, baking soda, salt and vanilla.
Add flour and oats.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes in 9 x 13 pan.

title: homemade biscuits
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt and cream of tartar.
In another mixing bowl, stir milk and oil together.
Add flour, a little at a time, until mixture is light (you may not need all of the flour mixture). Flour cutting board. Roll out into 1-inch thick circle. Cut with biscuit cutter.
Put in baking pan close together touching each other.
Spread with melted butter. Bake in a 400° oven until light brown on top, about 20 minutes.

title: crispy coconut pie
directions: Soak together milk and coconut.
Beat eggs together and add sugar, softened oleo or butter, vanilla, milk and coconut.
Stir all together and pour into 9-inch unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 475° for 15 minutes, then at 350° until done.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix ingredients.
Use 1/3 cup mix to 2/3 cup boiling water.

title: mom's caramel rolls
directions: Heat milk, sugar, salt and Crisco just until Crisco is melted. Pour into mixing bowl.
When lukewarm, add 1 cup of flour.
Add softened yeast.
Beat until smooth.
Add 2 eggs.
Add enough of the remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Turn onto floured surface, let stand 5 minutes and then knead until smooth.

title: baked fish
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium skillet, saute onion and garlic in olive oil until soft.
Mix in cornstarch.
Add tomatoes and their juice; mix until well blended.
Cook over medium-high heat until sauce thickens.
Stir in olives and chili pepper. Spoon half the sauce into a baking pan large enough to hold the fillets in one layer.
Place fish over sauce; sprinkle with lemon juice (salt optional).
Cover with remaining sauce; bake for 10 minutes, or until fillets flake easily.
Serves 6.

title: cranberry pot roast
directions: Combine the flour, salt and pepper and rub onto the roast. (Make more mixture if necessary to cover the roast.)
In Dutch oven, slowly brown the meat on all sides in 2 tablespoons hot shortening or salad oil.
Add the cloves, cinnamon and 1/4 cup water.
Cover tightly and simmer about 2 1/2 hours or until tender, adding small amount of water if necessary.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan (two 9-inch round or 30 cupcake liners).

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine. Mix all ingredients. Add chicken last. Put in greased crock-pot. Cook on high 45 minutes; cook on low 4 hours. Stir twice during cooking.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Place all in food processor and chop, scraping sides of bowl at least twice.
When well mixed and chopped, pour in 2-quart casserole (Pyrex) and bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with Wheat Thins or Fritos.
Serves 20.

title: kahlua cocoa balls
directions: Combine Kahlua with syrup, coconut and chocolate chips.
Blend sugar, cocoa, crumbs and pecans.
Combine mixtures.
Shape into small balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Freeze or store in airtight container.

title: strawberry cream punch
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a punch bowl, stirring well. Add ginger ale, stirring gently.
Scoop ice cream into punch bowl. Yields 1 3/4 gallons.

title: cheese-sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly together.
Roll into small balls. Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 400° until golden brown. Freeze mixture, or bake as needed.

title: cherry topped cheese pie
directions: Crust:
Melt 1/2 pound butter and mix with Zwieback toast crumbs.

title: peanut butter swirl bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine 1/2 cup crunch style peanut butter, softened butter, brown sugar and sugar.
Beat until creamy.
Gradually beat in eggs and vanilla.

title: crab mold delicious
directions: Combine first three ingredients in bowl.
Add mayonnaise and cream cheese.
Warm mushroom soup on stove, undiluted.
Dissolve gelatine in the 3 tablespoons of water.
Add to soup mixing well. Pour soup and gelatine mixture over celery and crab mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into Tupperware mold and refrigerate.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cut up cranberries, add sugar and let stand several hours. Drain juice from pineapple and save.
Add pineapple, apple and nuts to cranberry mixture.
Heat pineapple juice and juice from orange and use to dissolve jello.
Pour over cranberry mixture and chill until congealed.
Serve on lettuce with favorite dressing.

title: banana pudding
directions: Beat pudding mix and milk on slow speed until it begins to thicken (2 to 3 minutes).
Mix cream cheese with sweetened condensed milk and beat until smooth.
Add this to vanilla pudding mixture, then fold in 1/2 of the Cool Whip.

title: almond roca bars
directions: Mix butter,
brown
sugar, flour and vanilla.
Pat into pan. Bake at
for 20 to 30 minutes.
Take from oven and pour chocolate
chips
over.
Let
stand 5 minutes and spread. Sprinkle with almonds.
Good for holidays and easy to make.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Brown bacon until crisp, then dry.
Brown ground beef; drain. Put bacon, beef and onion in casserole dish.
Add beans, ketchup, mustard and brown sugar.
Mix well.
Bake 1 hour or longer.
Can be made in crock-pot, about 4 hours on low heat.

title: icebox delight
directions: Mix together and press into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Cool completely. Add next layer.

title: cocktail wieners and sauce
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in slow cooker. Simmer about 15 minutes. Add pineapple with juice and wieners. Simmer until wieners are done.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in buttered baking dish at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until light golden brown.
Serves 15.

title: clam dip
directions: Saute clams with water and lemon juice for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Saute butter, green pepper, onion, garlic, cayenne, oregano and parsley for 20 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add bread crumbs.
Top with cheese and bake until cheese melts. Serve with crackers.

title: sugar and spice cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly the shortening, sugar, egg and molasses.
Sift together and stir in the rest of the ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and form into small balls.
Place about 2-inches apart on greased baking sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.
Will be rough and cracked on top.

title: country crust bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Stir in sugar, salt, eggs, oil and 3 cups of the flour. Beat until smooth. Mix in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.

title: sausage and noodle casserole
directions: Brown sausage in skillet; drain.
Remove from skillet.
Return 2 tablespoons drippings to skillet.
Add bread crumbs and brown.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt margarine and mix with brown sugar. Add eggs and blend. Stir in flour. Add vanilla and chocolate chips. Pour into greased 9 x 13 AND 8 x 8 pans. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 325°. Cool and cut into squares.

title: linguine and clams
directions: Put the pot up for 1 pound of pasta.
Cover the bottom of pan with oil.
Half garlic cloves and saute being careful not to brown.
Add a handful of fresh parsley.
Now add bottle clam juice and about 1 dozen clams which have been opened, cleaned and cut in half.
(Be sure to strain the clam juice for sand.)
Bring to boil and shut off.
Pour over linguine which has been cooked al dente (not soft); add a pat of butter and top with Locatelli cheese.

title: apple marmalade
directions: Simmer 20 to 25 minutes. Can in pint jars.

title: potato pudding
directions: Cook the potatoes and mash.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Put mixture into a well-greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 400° for about 40 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve and enjoy.

title: pecan pie
directions: In bowl, combine all ingredients except pecans and beat well by hand until thoroughly combined.
Place pecans in unbaked pie shell and pour liquid ingredients over top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until set.
May serve with vanilla ice cream or whipped cream, if desired.

title: bulgar salad
directions: Soak Bulgar wheat in 2 cups water for 1/2 hour.
Drain and squeeze all water out.
Combine with remaining ingredients. Chill.
Serves 6.

title: snack crackers
directions: In a grocery bag, place all ingredients, adding oil last. Roll bag top closed and shake.
Air dry on cookie sheet for 1 hour.

title: hamburger goulash
directions: Brown the hamburger in frying pan; drain off fat.
(Use a large electric frypan so you can add all the ingredients and continue cooking.)
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook on low and keep turning so it doesn't burn.
Taste and add more salt if needed. Cover and allow to cook very slowly, about 1/2 hour.
Top with grated cheese and cover, about 15 minutes.
Serve with Parmesan cheese and garlic bread.

title: fresh peach cake
directions: Blend peaches and eggs, then add the other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: pineapple-waldorf pasta salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/4 cup of the juice.
Combine pineapple, pasta, apple, celery and nuts in a large bowl.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream, reserved pineapple juice and salt.
Add to salad.
Toss until well mixed; chill well before serving.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in a medium size boiler.
Cook over medium heat until mixture begins to thicken.
Add egg yolks and margarine.
Stir well.
Remove from heat and add the vanilla flavoring.
Stir out any lumps that might have appeared.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff and add 3 tablespoons sugar while beating.
Pour on top of chocolate mixture.
Place in oven until meringue is brown.

title: seven-layer dip
directions: Layer on platter in order:
Refried beans, 1/2 jar salsa, guacamole, sour cream, Muenster cheese, remaining 1/2 jar salsa, jalapeno peppers and Cheddar cheese.
Garnish with black olives. Use chips to dip.

title: king's ranch casserole
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick spray.
Preheat oven to 375°.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Combine Ranch mix and oil.
Add the rest of the seasonings. Pour over crackers and stir to coat.
Place in warm oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Boil the noodles as directed on package.
Brown ground beef and onion; drain fat.
Add tomato sauce, Italian seasoning and salt. Simmer while noodles cook.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer noodles, sauce, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese. Sprinkle Parmesan over top layer.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes in a 350° oven. Let sit 15 minutes before cutting.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Sift flour.
Measure and add salt, soda and spices.
Sift again.
Add sifted dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Add mincemeat and chopped nuts and blend into dough. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet spaced 2 to 3 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and spread in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread the sour cream over avocado mixture.
Mix the cream cheese and picante sauce and spread over sour cream.
Combine the olives and tomatoes and spread over cream cheese mixture. Sprinkle cheese over top.
Serve with large corn chips.

title: pot pie
directions: Cook meat and onion.
Set aside.
Put pie crust in the 8 x 8-inch casserole dish.
Mix all other ingredients and put into dish.
Cover with pie crust.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: minestrone soup
directions: In a large stock pot, bring to boil chicken stock, water, beef bouillon, chicken bouillon and cooked ham.
Saute in 3 tablespoons oil and add to meat and stock:
garlic, onion, parsley, basil, bay leaf and pepper.
Add celery, cabbage, carrots, green beans, rutabaga, potatoes and canned tomatoes and juice.
Simmer 1 hour covered.
Add frozen peas, red kidney beans and spaghetti.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.

title: chow mein casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Add nest 3 ingredients, mixing well.
Place 1/4 of the noodles in greased 1 qt. baking dish.
Layer half the ground beef, half the soup and half the remaining noodles in casserole.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: veg-all
directions: Mix it all together into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Add package of Ritz crackers, crumbled.
Bake 10 more minutes.

title: cocktail eggroll (lumpia)(philippine recipe)
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients in a bowl.
Beat egg.
Add to the first mixture and mix thoroughly.
At one end of lumpia wrapper, spoon 2 tablespoons of the mixture and roll tightly. Seal one end of wrapper by brushing with water.
Cut roll in 2 equal pieces and deep fry until golden brown.
Serve with prepared sweet and sour sauce.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain and combine peaches, pears and pineapple.
Sprinkle dry pudding mix over fruit, then add thawed strawberries.
Do not stir.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Add bananas; stir gently just before serving.
Serves 10.

title: sunday potato salad
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Cook in salted water until fork-tender.
Do not over-cook.
Meanwhile, chop boiled eggs and mix together with remaining ingredients.
Remove potatoes from heat and drain thoroughly.
Gently combine the egg mixture with potatoes, being careful not to break up potatoes.
Spoon into dish and sprinkle lightly with paprika.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Heat can of stewed tomatoes and add bouillon cube until dissolved.
Stuff chilies with hunks of Monterey Jack cheese. Separate eggs.
Beat egg whites until fluffy.
Slightly beat egg yolks and add to egg whites.
Add flour.
Heat oil in frying pan (enough to halfway cover chilies).
Take stuffed chilies and roll in flour, then in batter.
Fry chilies until golden brown.

title: date balls
directions: Cook butter, sugar and dates until thick.
Remove from heat; add nuts, vanilla and Rice Krispies.
Dip with teaspoon and roll into balls.
Roll in powdered sugar or coconut.
Let cool on waxed paper and store in cookie can.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Spray 2 bread loaf pans with pam.
Beat eggs until foamy, add rest of ingredients.
Put batter into loaf pans and bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: pork chops and dressing
directions: Brown pork chops in oil.
Place in baking dish.
In small pan simmer water, butter, onion and celery until tender.
Pour in bowl with bread crumbs.
Fluff up.
Spoon over pork chops evenly, then mix mushroom soup and 1/2 can water.
Pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour with foil covering dish.
Remove foil and bake for 1/2 hour longer.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Place beans in large buttered casserole.
Mix sour cream, cream of mushroom soup and seasonings.
Pour this mixture over green beans.
Sprinkle grated cheese over casserole.
Crush crackers (not too fine) and mix with oleo.
Spread crumbs on top of cheese.
Bake in 350 degree oven for 45 minutes or until bubbly hot.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Combine dressing, soup and preserves; pour over chicken in a large shallow baking dish.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Baste and turn occasionally.

title: beer cheese soup
directions: Cook carrots, celery and onion in butter in 4-quart Dutch oven until transparent (about 10 minutes).
Stir in baking mix, paprika and black and red pepper.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in chicken broth.
Heat to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir for 1 minute.
Reduce heat; stir in half and half, cheese and beer.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: grandmothers ham and potato casserole
directions: Slice the potatoes into "wagon wheels". Layer potatoes, ham, onion, and cheese and sprinkle lightly with flour. Repeat until finished. Pour enough milk for moisture only. Sprinkle with desired amount of salt and pepper. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes, taking care not to burn the cheese on top.

title: rice-a-roni chicken
directions: Prepare by directions on box.
Add chicken and water or milk. Simmer 5 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: cocoa oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Let come to boil and boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix good and drop by tablespoons onto waxed paper.

title: rum or whiskey sauce
directions: Mix flour and sugar into margarine; stir in milk until smooth. Bring to simmer; cook for about 5 minutes, until thickened.
Beat egg in a small cup.
Add some of the hot mixture to the egg, beating well.
Stir egg into sauce mixture, beating until smooth. Cook 3 to 5 minutes, until thickened.
Do not boil.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and rum or bourbon.
Serve warm over bread pudding.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased oblong pan.
Start baking at 375°; reduce to 350°.

title: jello popcorn balls
directions: Cook sugar, Jell-O, Karo, margarine and water to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and pour over popped corn.
Mix.
When cool enough to handle, form into balls with greased hands.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Add egg whites after straining the mixture.
Bake in two 9-inch pie shells at 400° approximately 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pistachio fruit salad
directions: Mix crushed pineapples with Jello pudding mix.
Add cool whip, and sour cream, marshmallows, and nuts.

title: kruppsua
directions: While preheating oven at 375°, melt butter in large 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
In a large bowl, mix eggs, salt and sugar together.
Add milk and mix well, then mix in flour slowly.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Transfer to large baking dish (2 x 9 x 13-inch).
Top with Topping.

title: apple cabbage slaw
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; pour over cabbage, apples and pineapple.
Mix well.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch Bundt pan. Drain pineapple (reserving juice).
Add water to juice to equal 1 cup.
Combine cake and pudding.
Mix oil, juice, water, eggs and cinnamon in a large bowl.
Beat at low speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in fruit and nuts.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until done.
Cool 25 minutes in pan.
Glaze if desired.

title: norwegian fish mousse
directions: Dry fish and put through a blender.
Work puree until smooth. Stir in cornstarch, salt, pepper and nutmeg, then gradually add milk and cream.
The mixture should be like a heavy cream.
More seasoning may be added if desired.
Pour mixture into an 8-inch buttered and breaded pudding mold; cover with foil.
Place the mold in a pan with boiling water and cook at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes or until mousse is set.
Add more water to pan as needed. Unmold on a hot platter and garnish with parsley, sauteed mushrooms or shrimp.
Serve with browned butter or a shrimp sauce. Makes 6 servings.

title: squash relish(10 pints)
directions: Cook over low heat for 45 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Put in jars.
Process in hot water bath 20 minutes.

title: world's best sugar cookie
directions: Cream margarine, oil and granulated sugar.
Add confectioners sugar and eggs.
Add all other ingredients.
Shape into small balls and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 150 cookies. May add chocolate chips, coconut or fruit.

title: traditional chex party mix
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 15 x 10 x 2-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Remove from oven and stir in seasoned salt and Worcestershire.
Add cereal and nuts gradually, mixing ingredients until all pieces are evenly coated.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
Spread on absorbent paper towels to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat together oil, eggs and vanilla.
Add sugar.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add flour and apples alternately to mixture.
Stir in pecans and raisins.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: zesty salad cocktail
directions: Put all ingredients in blender with 1 cup ice cubes and whirl until thoroughly blended.
Makes 4 cups, about 30 calories per cup.

title: potato casserole
directions: Break up defrosted hash brown patties.
(You can also use "Simply Potatoes" shredded hash browns found in dairy case.) Combine with all ingredients, except corn flakes.
Mix thoroughly. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with crushed corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mom's green pea casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in margarine.
Combine all ingredients and heat thoroughly on top of stove, then pour into casserole dish.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cover casserole with Pepperidge Farm dry stuffing mix.
Put a little butter in dots on top of dry crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven until well browned.

title: cinnamon chocolate bars
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and cinnamon together in a mixer.
Mix together until blended.
Add margarine, egg and egg yolk.
Mix together until right consistency.
Spread in a greased jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over all.
Add 1/3 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: squash stuff(the kid's named it)
directions: Fry bacon crisp, drain and chop.
Slice squash and chop onions.
Mix eggs and corn.
Mix all ingredients.
Place in covered dish.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: lean and light pancakes
directions: Mix egg, milk and melted margarine. Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Add liquid mixture to dry ingredients with a beater until all ingredients are moistened (batter may be lumpy).
Pour onto a lightly oiled griddle, using 1/4 cup for each pancake.
Cook until pancakes are puffed and bubbly. Turn and cook until nicely browned on both sides.
One pancake contains 90 calories.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain well.
Spread crescent rolls in bottom of casserole dish.
Add sausage and cheese.
Whip eggs, milk, salt and pepper and pour over top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: cranberry upside-down cake
directions: Put butter, sugar, water, and cinnamon in sauce pan for about 3 minutes until sugar/butter melts. Add cranberries and set aside while mixing cake batter.

title: strawberry delight
directions: In one bowl, break angel food cake into chunks.
In another bowl, slice strawberries and stir in glaze.
In a third bowl, mix Cool Whip, sugar and sour cream.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Put your chicken on stove and cook until done.
Salt and pepper.
While chicken is cooking, mix your flour and water and roll into a ball.
Roll out a little bit of the ball at a time on a floured surface.
