Roll real thin and cut 2 inches wide and 4 inches long.
When chicken is done, pick it from the bone and put it into the broth you cooked your chicken in.
Add all the ingredients except flour mixture.
Bring back to a boil and add dumplings one at a time.
Take a fork and push down on the dumplings to make room to add more.
Let cook until done, about 15 minutes.

title: never fail dumplings
directions: Mix together and add just enough water or milk to drop from spoon.
Drop by spoonfuls into boiling soup.
Cover and steam 15 minutes without removing cover.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix well and cook enough to pour in a pie shell (like pudding).
Bake at 350° for pie shell until brown.
Pour in cool pie shell.

title: cobbler
directions: Melt butter.
Mix sugar, flour and milk.
Beat until smooth and pour into melted butter.
Add strawberries and juice or cherries or peaches.
Bake at 400° until done (1/2 hour?).
You may top with whipped topping or eat as is.

title: grandma's stewed chicken
directions: Cook cut up chicken until tender.
Brown 6 to 8 tablespoons flour in dry skillet.
With spoon, keep flour moved so it does not burn.
Add water to flour to make soft paste.
Add to cooked chicken; cook until broth thickens.

title: hooties pumpkin pie
directions: In large saucepan, combine brown sugar, gelatin, salt, spices, pumpkin, milk and slightly beaten egg yolks. Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring often. Set aside to cool. Beat egg whites with sugar until stiff peaks form. Fold into pumpkin mixture. Pour into pie shell and refrigerate. Serve with whipped topping.

title: easy and good cobbler
directions: Pour into 9 x 12 dish in layers in order given. When you add the butter, put it on top in small pieces or melt and drizzle on cake mix. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: healthy blue cheese dip(low fat dip recipe)
directions: Combine and blend above ingredients.
Chill until ready to serve.
Serve with veggies or on salads as a dressing.

title: crumb cake(approximately 100 year old recipe)
directions: Mix brown sugar, butter and flour like pie dough.
Take out 1 cup crumbs for top.
Put soda in milk; add egg, milk and salt to remaining ingredients.
Pour batter into a greased cake pan and sprinkle the crumbs on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: lemon supreme pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine first 6 ingredients and beat well.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan until cake tests done.
Cool for 15 minutes in pan before removing.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until it forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water, then add peanut butter.
Stir well.
Pour into buttered pan and allow to cool completely before cutting.

title: glup
directions: Cover bottom of cake pan or baking dish with meat.
Cover meat with sliced potatoes.
Put rice over potatoes; pour gravy on top. Bake at 375° for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours until potatoes are tender. Great recipe for leftovers.

title: pizza fingers
directions: Cut cheese into 3 x 1/4 x 1/4-inch strips; set aside.
Lay pepperoni (4 pieces), overlapped, enough to put into 15 or 16 egg roll wraps.
Lay cut cheese onto pepperoni.
Lay egg roll wrap diamond-wise and put a teaspoon of the sauce on the corner nearest you.
Place pepperoni and cheese on top of sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and add any optional ingredients (use sparingly). Baste wrap across from fillings.
Roll according to wrap instructions.
Deep fry until golden brown and cheese starts coming out of pizza finger.
Heat extra sauce for dipping.
Serves 4 per person.

title: cream cheese stuffing
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften.
Add mayonnaise and mix well. Add finely cut cucumber and onions; mix well.
Salt to taste. Refrigerate overnight.

title: mayonnaise mahimahi
directions: Salt and pepper the mahimahi.
Mix mayonnaise, round onion and parsley flakes.
Slather on top of the fish.
Bake in a 350° oven until fish begins to flake.
Garnish with cilantro.
Can also be used with salmon.

title: broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Cook onion
in	butter	in 3-quart saucepan until soft. Blend in	flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk and cook, stirring constantly until
mixture
comes
to a boil and thickens.
Add cheese and	stir
until melted.
Remove from heat.	In another saucepan,
dissolve
bouillon
cubes
in
boiling
water.
Add frozen broccoli,
cover
and
cook until tender, do not drain. Add to cheese mixture.	Heat to serving temperature.

title: eggnog bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, nutmeg, sugar, baking powder and salt in a large bowl.
Stir in fruit and nuts.
Combine eggs, eggnog, vanilla and melted butter.
Pour eggnog mixture into flour mixture.
Stir just until thoroughly combined.
Pour batter into 1 large or 2 medium loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour.
Cool for 10 minutes and remove from pans.
Great or spray pans with nonstick spray.

title: old fashioned rice pudding
directions: Use medium-sized coated saucepan or rinse pan with cold water (don't dry).
Pour milk in pan and bring to boil over medium-high heat.
Stir in rice and return to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until rice is tender, about 55 minutes.
Don't cover; stir occasionally.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and lemon juice.
Add Cool Whip. Place in a graham cracker crust.
Top with canned cherries.
This makes 2 pies.

title: caesar bean and potato salad
directions: Whisk first 5 ingredients in a large bowl until blended.
Add remainder of ingredients and toss to mix and coat.

title: gingerbread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour square 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Measure all ingredients into large mixing bowl.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour into pan.
Bake 50 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve warm and, if desired, with whipping cream.
Also good with applesauce.

title: oreo sundaes
directions: Crush the Oreo cookies (all but 5).
Mix with butter.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place in freezer until set (20 minutes).
Place softened ice cream over crust.
Spread the fudge topping over the ice cream and freeze for 20 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip, then remaining 5 crushed Oreo cookies.

title: sugarless peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients; shape into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Press with fork before baking.

title: cornstarch pudding
directions: Heat milk and salt (just hot, not boiling).
Mix sugar, cornstarch and egg with just enough milk to make a thin batter. Pour slowly into hot milk, stirring as you pour, and bring to a good boil.
Add vanilla and stir.
If it gets too thick, add a little cold milk and stir.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Place corn in large paper bag. Combine remaining ingredients in qt. glass bowl and bring to a boil in microwave on high power. Boil 2 minutes. Add 1/2 tsp. soda and stir. Pour over corn close bag and shake. Cook on high power for 90 seconds and shake. Repeat above step and shake. Cook 30 seconds and shake. Repeat for 30 seconds and shake. Cool on cookie sheet.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Put a lot of water on giblets or use a can of chicken broth. Mix all the ingredients well and heat in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix sugar and flour together; add drained pineapple and cheese mixture.
Mix well.
Grease a baking dish and add mixture; top with crackers.
Melt margarine and pour over top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: grilled bratwurst with german potato salad
directions: Bring the beer to a simmer in a saucepan over medium heat.
Add the sausages and cook until plump, 4 to 6 minutes.
Preheat the grill.
Cook the potatoes in salted water in a saucepan over medium heat until tender, about 15 minutes.
Remove and drain well.
Keep warm.
Cook the bacon until crispy in a skillet over medium heat. Add the onions; season with black pepper and cook, stirring, for 1 minute.
Remove from the heat.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: After putting persimmons through colander, stir in other ingredients.
Bake in greased pan at 350°.
With knife blade, test.
When mixture stops sticking to blade, it's done.
Also it will flatten considerably when done.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: taco pie
directions: Press biscuits into bottom of pan to make crust. Mix rest of ingredients, except cheese, in skillet and cook on low for 10 minutes. Layer 1/2 meat and 1/2 cheese; repeat until all is used. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: fresh vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together in a bowl.
Blend in blender to make smooth.

title: country hash(easy main dish)
directions: Use large skillet.
Cover meat and potatoes with milk.
Cook on low heat.
Cover, low boil (as milk will boil over).
Cook until milk reduces and is absorbed, about 45 minutes (keep watch). Press together; light brown crust will form.
Excellent use of leftover meats.

title: "sea leg" dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In round dish or medium souffle dish, soften cream cheese in microwave for one minute.
Add lemon juice and mayonnaise and stir until smooth.
Chop sea legs into 1-inch pieces and blend into cream cheese mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes or until top turns light brown.
Serve hot with crackers.
Serves 12.

title: barbecued chicken by danish
directions: Mix ketchup, chili powder, Worcestershire sauce, margarine, vinegar, salt, sugar, lemon juice, paprika and water in a bowl. Roll chicken pieces in mixture and place in a baking pan or dish. Cover with foil.
Bake 15 minutes at 500°; then reduce heat to 325° and cook 1 hour.

title: crab salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together; pour into a baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs and almonds.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cherry-nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 3 large loaves or 6 small loaves.

title: fruit filled cake bars
directions: Grease pan.
Combine ingredients.
Sprinkle with coconut. Bake at 350° until done.

title: zesty breaded chicken breast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dip the chicken in melted margarine, then Fiesta soup mix combined with bread crumbs.
Arrange chicken in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Drizzle with remaining margarine. Bake for 20 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Beat eggs until frothy with wire whisk.
Gradually beat in milk.
Add flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Beat until smooth.
In large skillet, put 1-inch of oil.
Put batter into pitcher or bowl with pouring spout starting in center of skillet. Pour batter (small stream) in spiral until 1-inch from edge of pan. Fry until golden.
Turn with 2 pancake spatulas to fry other side. Remove onto paper towels.
Serve hot sprinkled with powdered sugar.

title: sausage bean chowder(yields 6 servings)
directions: Brown, drain and rinse sausage.
In large kettle, combine kidney beans, tomatoes, water, onion, bay leaf, garlic powder, thyme and pepper.
Add sausage.
Simmer, covered, 1 hour.
Add potatoes and green pepper.
Cook, covered, 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Remove bay leaf and serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine
butter,
sugar
and
corn syrup; cook over low heat, stirring
constantly
until
sugar is dissolved.
Cool. Add beaten eggs, vanilla and salt; blend well.
Stir in pecans and pour into pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Stir thawed Cool Whip and dry pudding together until "green" is fully absorbed.
Drain all fruit.
Stir in fruit.
Refrigerate. Three to 6 grams of fat per serving.

title: zippy bean skillet
directions: Brown meat, onion and peppers in shortening.
Reduce heat; add beans, sugar and cloves.
Cover and heat 10 minutes.
Serve.

title: fumi salad
directions: Chop cabbage and place in a very large bowl. Toast sesame seeds and almonds (being careful since they can burn easily). Remove the seasoning from the noodles and set aside for the dressing. Crunch up the noodles into small pieces. Mix all ingredients together. Prepare dressing.

title: layered soup
directions: Layer in crock pot beginning with ground beef.
Do not stir. Cook on low for 8 hours.
Sometimes we just mix, heat and eat!

title: apple pudding
directions: Mix apples, salt, sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon until moist.
Add egg and beat pudding.
Mix egg and apple mixture together.
Add soda and flour.
Mix well.
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch pan in a 375° oven until toothpick comes out clean.
Serve with Vanilla Sauce.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Spread 1/2 cup of the fudge sauce in bottom of the crust. Pour cold half and half into large bowl. Add pudding mix and flavored instant coffee. Beat with wire whisk for about 1 minute or until well mixed. Let stand 5 minutes or until thickened. Gently stir in whipped topping. Spread into crust. Freeze for 6 hours or overnight until firm. Let stand at room temperature about 10 minutes or until pie can be cut easily. Serve with remaining 1/2 cup of fudge sauce. Makes 8 servings. Store leftover pie in freezer.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: In large skillet, saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender. Add tomatoes, olives, oregano, and ground beef. Simmer, uncovered for 10 minutes. Place half of the spaghetti in a large, rectangular baking dish (greased). Top with half of the vegetable mixture. Sprinkle with 1 cup of cheddar cheese. Repeat layers. Mix the soup and water until smooth; pour over casserole. Sprinkle with parmesan cheese. Bake, uncovered at 350° for about 45 minutes, or until heated through.

title: shrimp louis
directions: Salad: 8 c. Shredded lettuce, iceberg, 1 lb. Cleaned and Cooked fresh medium shrimp, 4 Celery stalks, cut into sticks, 4 Tomatoes, quartered, 2 Hard boiled egg whites, quartered, parsley sprigs.

title: dessert hamburgers
directions: Color some coconut green for lettuce and some coconut yellow for cheese.
Cut the strawberries into slices.
Make the hamburgers the way you like them or let each person create their own.
The vanilla wafers are the buns.
The peppermint patty is the meat. The colored coconut is the lettuce and cheese.
The strawberries are the tomatoes.

title: breakfast pie
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Combine with other ingredients and pour into shell.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 375°.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: chocolate dream cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar in mixing bowl.
Blend well.
In a saucepan, bring to a rapid boil the oleo, shortening, water and cocoa.
Pour over flour and sugar mixture; mix well.
Combine remaining ingredients and add all at once to the batter, mixing well.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: uncle charlie's marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients in shallow dish.
Place London Broil in marinade and let sit for 2 days, turning twice a day to coat both sides.
When cooking, baste with the sauce.

title: baked corn
directions: Drain corn.
Measure milk by the size of the can.
Use greased baking dish. Beat milk and eggs together.
Add all other ingredients together.
Then sprinkle bread crumbs and butter on top.
Heat oven to 350°.
Bake 1 hour or until it's thick.

title: southern cornbread
directions: Mix meal and flour together.
Add drippings and mix gradually. Add buttermilk until well blended and thick.
Grease skillet (iron), preferred heavy.
Pour in mixture and bake at 425° about 20 to 25 minutes, until golden brown.

title: company carrots
directions: In a saucepan, cook the carrots in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain the carrots and reserve 1/4 cup of the liquid. Arrange the carrots in a shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
In a bowl combine the mayonnaise, carrot liquid, onion, horseradish, salt and pepper.
Pour the mixture over the carrots.
Sprinkle the casserole with the cracker crumbs, parsley flakes and paprika and dot with butter.
Bake the dish, uncovered, at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheese pepper bread
directions: Grease two (1 pound) coffee cans.
In a large mixer bowl, dissolve yeast in hot water.
Add 1 1/3 cups of the flour, the sugar, salt, soda, sour cream and egg.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in remaining flour, the cheese and pepper thoroughly.
Divide batter between cans.
Let rise in warm place 50 minutes.
(Batter will rise slightly, but will not rise above cans.)
Heat oven to 350°.
Bake 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately remove from cans.
Cool slightly before slicing.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: biscotti
directions: Add sugar to beaten eggs; beat well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well but do not overbeat.
Spoon batter on greased cookie sheet, forming 3 rows lengthwise.
Bake 18 minutes at 375°. Remove loaves from oven and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Lay slices flat on cookie sheet and return to oven to brown lightly:
5 minutes at 350°, turn, and then 5 minutes more at 350°.

title: english trifle
directions: In a trifle bowl or large glass bowl, layer diced pound cake, 2 tablespoons of orange juice, pudding and fruit.
Continue layering until you reach the top of the bowl.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: southern style banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions. Arrange half the vanilla wafers in bottom of an 8 x 8 x 2-inch square baking dish. Top with half the bananas, then half the pudding.

Repeat with layer of remaining wafers, bananas and pudding. Beat egg whites, vanilla and cream of tartar in medium size bowl at high speed until soft peaks form. Add sugar gradually, beating until stiff peaks form.
Spread meringue evenly over pudding, spreading to edge of dish to seal. Bake in preheated moderate oven at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: nilla banana heaven
directions: Add milk to pudding.
Mix until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip. Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with Nilla wafers.
Layer pudding and sliced bananas to make two layers.
Top with a layer of Nilla wafers.

title: homemade chili
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Add other ingredients.
Let simmer for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fruit crisp
directions: In a small mixing bowl, combine sugar and 1/4 tsp. cinnamon. Place the apples or other fruit in a
9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle sugar-cinnamon mixture over fruit.
Toss gently to coat.
Cover; bake in a 375 degrees oven for 25 minutes.
Meanwhile, stir together the oats, flour, brown sugar, margarine, and 1/4 tsp. cinnamon.
Sprinkle over partially cooked fruit mixture.
Return to the oven and bake, uncovered, for 15 to 20 minutes more or until fruit is tender.
Serve warm with ice milk.
Makes 4 servings.

title: butterscotch cake
directions: Mix well and bake in a 350° oven until done.
Use two round pans.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix oleo, creamy peanut butter, white sugar and brown sugar until creamy.
Mix egg and vanilla and add to first mixture until creamy.
Add flour, baking soda and salt and mix all together. Form into 1-inch balls and place in ungreased tassy pans.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and press peanut butter cup into center.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.

title: baked salmon squares
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put into a greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour, or until set. Cut into squares and serve with creamed spinach.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Thoroughly mix water and Jell-O.
Add orange juice, pineapple and juice and orange slices.
Pour into mold or 8 x 8-inch pan and let set.
Mix pudding, sour cream and milk until smooth.
Pour over Jell-O mixture and chill until set.

title: grandma's buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and soda together.
Cut in lard and stir in buttermilk to make a soft dough.
Work lightly on a floured board.
Roll out to about 1/2-inch thickness and cut out with a biscuit cutter.
Place biscuits on a greased baking sheet and bake at 450° for 6 to 8 minutes or until brown.

title: guacamole
directions: Peel and pit avocados, reserving one pit.
Mash avocados and add onions and tomatoes.
Add remaining ingredients and stir. Place reserved avocado pit in center of mixture and place in refrigerator for 1 hour to blend spices.
Use plastic wrap to cover instead of foil.
Foil will brown the mixture.
Discard the pit and serve immediately.

title: apple salad
directions: Bring vinegar to a boil.
Add sugar and flour.
Mix and add butter and milk.
Add beaten eggs a little at a time, stir.
Cook over low heat until thickened.
Let cool.
Keep in refrigerator. Pour over apples when serving.

title: antipasto salad
directions: Julienne slice the cheeses.
Peel and seed the tomatoes; julienne slice.
Drain the olives.
Mix all salad ingredients in a large bowl with a tight fitting lid.

title: fresh pear bread
directions: Soak pears in sugar 1 hour.
Stir together flour, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and soda.
Beat together eggs, oil and vanilla; add nuts.
Pour mixture into pears and add flour mixture; mix well.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.
Freezes well.

title: date nut balls
directions: Cook dates, sugar and margarine, stirring constantly, until margarine is melted and bubbles.
Add nuts.
Pour hot mixture over cereal in a large bowl.
Mix well. Form into small balls and dust with powdered sugar.
Place a few balls in bag and shake until completely coated.

title: applesauce raisin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° or so for a glass pan).

title: macaroni and tomatoes
directions: Cook onion, celery and green pepper in bacon grease.
Add bacon and cooked vegetables to tomato mixture.
Cook about 20 minutes. Drain macaroni and add to tomato mixture.
You will have a lot of tomato juice in your pan.
Don't be alarmed, just let the mixture sit on the stove for about an hour and during this time the macaroni will absorb all the juice.
(If you try to cook it down, it will stick badly.)
Put in a casserole dish and run in a 375° oven for about 45 minutes.
Serves 12.
If you have leftover chopped ham, this is a nice addition to this dish.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Put broccoli in bottom. Layer chicken pieces on top.
Mix chicken soup and mayonnaise. Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Make dressing according to directions on bag.
Put dressing on cheese layer. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: carrot ambrosia salad
directions: Combine together.
Toss well just prior to serving.
Chill for several hours prior.

title: cheese sticks
directions: Mix ingredients and knead together well.
Roll out, then cut in strips, 1/2 x 3-inches.
Indent with tines of fork.
Bake on cookie sheet, 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
(Best not brown.)

title: dave's chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Add taco seasoning, tomatoes, beans and vegetable juice.
Bring to a boil and then simmer 45 minutes.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Salt
and
pepper
hamburger
to
taste;
mix
in bread crumbs.
Add enough water to make it stick together.
Pat down flat in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Chill overnight.
Cut into pieces;
roll
in
flour.
Brown
in margarine.
Place in pan. Dilute the mushroom soup with one can of water; pour on top of meat.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: carrot and zucchini bars
directions: In a large mixing bowl, stir together flour, brown sugar, baking powder, ginger and baking soda.

title: oyster dressing
directions: Mix with juices.
When ready to serve, add:
2 (2 liter) bottles of 7-Up.
Spoon on top:
3 qt. rainbow sherbet (can use any flavor desired).
Serves about 50 people.
Juices can be varied according to taste.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Stir jello into boiling water until dissolved.
Add strawberries.
Mix in well drained pineapple and mashed bananas. Chill until mixture begins to thicken.
Pour 1/2 of jello mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread sour cream over top.
Pour other half of jello mixture on top of sour cream.
Place back into refrigerator until firm.
Serve with a dollop of mayonnaise.

title: deli-in-a-skillet
directions: Mix corned beef, sauerkraut and water in large skillet.
Bring to a full boil. Stir in rice.
Pour dressing over rice and top with cheese.
Cover;
remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
You may also use knockwurst in place of the corned beef.

title: potato soup
directions: Mix everything and simmer for 10 minutes, but do not boil. Garnish with parsley.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix ingredients and freeze.
Can use plastic milk containers. Before serving, begin to thaw, and as it becomes mush add 2 large bottles of orange crush or ginger ale.
Serves 50.

title: turkey or chicken tetrazzini
directions: In saucepan, put soup, sour cream, garlic, oregano, salt and pepper to taste.
Stir well until smooth.
Add chicken.
Cook noodles and drain.
Toss with butter.
Pour chicken mixture over or mix right together, if desired.
Sprinkle grated or shredded cheese on top.
Serve hot.
May be reheated in microwave.

title: something different meatballs (easy)
directions: If making your own meatballs, cook in oven at 350° until cooked through.

title: cooked mush
directions: Bring water to boiling point.

title: spring mix salad
directions: Mix the walnuts, butter and sugar and roast in oven for 3 to 4 minutes at 300°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend all together.
Roll
into
two
equal size balls. Chill, then roll
balls into equal amounts of chili powder and paprika.

title: rum and eggnog cake
directions: Let butter, eggs and eggnog stand at room temperature 30 minutes.
Grease and flour 10-inch fluted tube pan.
Stir together 2 1/4 cups flour, baking powder and nutmeg.
Toss together fruits, raisins, nuts and 2 tablespoons flour.
Set aside.
In a mixing bowl, beat butter with mixer on medium speed for 30 seconds. Slowly add sugar; beat 10 minutes until fluffy and light.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating 1 minute after each.
Add flour mixture and eggnog alternately to egg mixture, beating on low speed after each, just until combined.
Do not overbeat.
Stir in 1/4 cup rum or 1/4 cup orange juice and rum extract.
Fold in fruit.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in the middle comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely. Poke holes in cake.
Soak a 100% cotton cheeses cloth with 1 cup rum or 1/2 cup orange juice.
Wrap in cheesecloth.
Wrap lightly in foil and seal in a plastic storage bag.
Store cake in refrigerator or freezer for 1 to 2 days to mellow flavors.
After 1 day, drizzle with 1/4 cup rum or orange juice.
Rewrap for another day or serve.
Before serving, drizzle with eggnog glaze.

title: cranberry cherry salad
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Pour gelatin into boiling water and remove from heat; stir to dissolve.
Set aside 1/2 cup of the gelatin.
Put cranberry sauce into gelatin; stir to dissolve. Drain cherries and save juice.
Add water to the juice to make 1 1/2 cups.
Add cherry juice to the gelatin and refrigerate until almost set.
Add sour cream to the 1/2 cup of gelatin and refrigerate.
Halve cherries.
Peel and dice apple.
Toss apple, nuts and cherries together.
When the gelatin is almost set, spoon the fruit into it and lightly mix.
Layer the gelatin mixture and sour cream mixture in a serving dish or individual dishes.

title: hot cheese
directions: Grate cheese.
Mix with cream cheese.
Add Worcestershire, garlic salt and cayenne.
Mix well with hands.
Roll in 4 sticks on wax paper.
Roll in cayenne pepper to taste.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray pizza sheet with Pam spray. Slice cookie roll and spread together in pan.
Bake until golden brown, 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Over low heat, melt the margarine; then add the flour, mixing well.
Add milk, continuing to stir to make a smooth white sauce.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in saucepan and cook until it comes to a boil (about 1 minute).
Take off stove and add vanilla and peanut butter.
When they have melted, add oats and mix well. Drop by tablespoon on wax paper.
Makes about 40 cookies.

title: skunk antidote
directions: Bathe dog with above mixture.
Rinse with water.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix well and put in a loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven 1 hour until done.

title: sweetheart punch
directions: Chill ingredients and combine.

title: cowboy chili
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Brown bacon and crumble into hamburger.
Add rest and cook.

title: tomato juice cocktail
directions: Mix and chill thoroughly before serving.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 12 x 12-inch pan.
Mix flour, sugar, milk and egg.
After butter melts, add dough, then about 16 ounces of fruit and mix with dough.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sauerbraten - beef in marinade
directions: Heat to a boil equal parts sugar, water and vinegar. Place chuck roast into a deep bowl. Add onions. Pour hot liquid over chuck roast. Cover and refrigerate overnight, turning twice. The longer it marinates, the more sour it gets.

title: stuffed pineapple
directions: Cream butter, add sugar, beat in one egg at a time.
Stir pineapple into eggs and sugar.
Fold in bread cubes making sure to cover all.
Pour into 1 qt. casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. If bread gets too brown before finished baking, cover until done.

title: tomato hot sauce
directions: Cook and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Pour in hot jars and seal.

title: buns
directions: Mix in the evening.
Boil the water, salt and sugar for 5 minutes.
Add lard and cool. Add 4 cups flour and mix. Add yeast and the rest of the flour. Turn out on floured board and knead. Let rise until double. With hands, shape into 2-inch buns.
Place a little apart on greased cookie sheets and let rise overnight. Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 400°.
Makes about 80 buns.

title: melomakaruna(greek cookies)
directions: Grate a little orange peeling into juice.
Mix all ingredients and add plain flour until mixture is right consistency to roll. Roll and cut cookies.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
After cookies get cold, dip into following mixture:

title: quick fruit curry
directions: Brown the chicken in oil and butter over moderate heat. Remove pieces and set aside.
Lightly saute the onion in the same large skillet or pot.
Stir in the curry powder; return chicken to the pot and cook for 3 to 5 minutes, turning pieces several times. Add the fruits, salt, vinegar and peanuts, with enough water to cover.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer until chicken is tender, about 45 minutes.
If the sauce is too thin to ladle well over
rice, cook uncovered another 15 to 20 minutes until liquid is reduced.

title: vegetable cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350. Place veggies in a 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle with cubed Velveeta and pats of cold butter. Top with Ritz crackers and bake for 30 minutes or until veggies are tender.

title: baptist pie
directions: Mix with mixer.
Pour into crusts, cover with coconut and pecans.
Chill before serving.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine
pudding
with	2
cups
of water or milk.
Let stand 5
minutes.
Add
Cool Whip, sour cream and Eagle Brand milk
to pudding mix.
Layer wafers, bananas and pudding mix. Drizzle chocolate
syrup
between layers, if desired.
Repeat process until all mixture is gone.

title: pork chops and fried rice
directions: Trim excess fat from pork chops.
Fry out trimmings in large skillet over medium heat to make 1 tablespoon of melted fat; add chops and brown on each side for about 5 minutes.
Remove chops, put onion in skillet, cook, stirring frequently, about 5 minutes or until browned.
Add water, rice, marjoram, salt and pepper; mix well.
Place chops on top.
Cover, bring to boil, then cook over low heat 18 to 20 minutes or until tender.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Combine with soup, corned beef, milk, cheese and onion.
Put into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole and top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: landing zone party loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients (except bread) together in a bowl.
Cut French bread lengthwise and spread mixture onto both halves.
Wrap in foil and bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes or longer if desired.
Open foil at top during last 5 minutes to expose meat mixture for browning.
Serves 4.

title: savory meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Pack into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch greased loaf pan.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
Juice should be 1 cup. If not, add enough water to make 1 cup.
Mix softened cream cheese and 1/2 cup juice on low speed of mixer.
Pour into crust and put in refrigerator to set about 45 minutes.
With remaining juice, bring to a boil with jello.
Put in refrigerator about 15 to 25 minutes to stiffen.
Do not let congeal. Arrange pineapple on top of pie and put jello mixture over.

title: three leaf salad
directions: Wash and chop all vegetables; put in salad bowl.
Add mandarin oranges, Feta cheese and cooked bacon that is crumbled up.
Make dressing, then toss with other ingredients.

title: crispy onion rings
directions: Peel
and
slice
onions about 1/3-inch thick; separate into rings.
Pour buttermilk into shallow pan; let onion rings soak for
minutes.
In
another
bowl,
combine remaining ingredients,
except
oil; mix until smooth.
In a large skillet, heat
cooking oil, about 1/4-inch deep, over medium high heat. Remove
onion rings form buttermilk, and dip in batter; fry in hot
oil until brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: carrot meringue pie
directions: Cook carrots with lemon juice and salt in small amount of water until well done.
Drain and mash.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie shell and bake in 350° oven one hour or until firm.

title: deb's baked beans
directions: Drain all juice of beans.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in baking dish with cover.
Put in microwave on High for 20 minutes.
Take out; stir.
Put back in microwave 20 minutes more. Take out; uncover and stir.
Let stand 20 minutes before eating.

title: enchiladas hot dish
directions: Layer the taco shells into pan and keep layering using grated cheese on top on each layer.
Bake at 325 degrees for 30-45 minutes or till it bubbles.

title: bird feeder
directions: Will also need a spoon and string.

title: jelly roll
directions: Combine baking powder, salt and eggs. Add sugar.
Beat until mixture becomes thick and light colored.
Fold in flour and vanilla.
Turn into 15 x 10-inch pan lined with greased brown paper.
Bake at 400° for 13 minutes.
Turn cake onto towel dusted with powdered sugar.
Remove paper.
Cut off crisp edges of cake. Roll cake and towel together.
Cool 10 minutes.
Unroll.
Remove towel.
Spread cake with jelly and roll again.
Yields 8 servings.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Add flour.
Roll thoroughly and cut in small circles.
Sprinkle with grated sharp cheese and fold. Bake at 400° until brown.

title: cheese straws
directions: Grate cheese and mix with soft margarine.
Add flour sifted with salt and pepper. Press into ball and roll out on floured pastry cloth to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into strips with fluted roller.
Cut strips into 2 to 3-inch lengths.
Sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Slide pieces gently onto cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° to 375° oven for about 10 minutes.
Watch carefully as they burn easily.
Cool on wax paper.

title: cheese balls
directions: Blend cheese with butter.
Add salt, pepper and garlic salt in flour.
Wrap mixture around the olives or nuts or mix both.
Make into balls.
Place on tray or cookie sheet and freeze.

title: italian cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together, then mix eggs, milk and vanilla together.
Combine the two mixes.
Cover and set in refrigerator overnight.
Roll in ball or finger shape and bake 15 minutes in 325° oven or until light brown on bottom.
When cool, ice with cookie icing.

title: mexican creole cake
directions: Cream together the sugar, oil, vanilla and eggs.
Sift together the flour, cocoa and salt.
Add flour mixture to sugar alternately with buttermilk.
Mix baking soda and boiling water; add to mixture last, making a thin batter.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour in a long, shallow pan at 300°.
Do not overbake.

title: pam's chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken until it slips off the bone easily.
Place boned chicken, broth and soup in a large pan.
Bring to a boil.
Add potatoes and/or noodles.
Peel biscuits off in layers and roll in flour. Roll thin and cut into strips and place in boiling broth. Cook fast for about 10 minutes and then turn heat to low and cook for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate caramels
directions: Cook and stir over low heat the above to soft ball stage 240. Add 1/2 cup cream and cook to soft ball stage 240.
Add 1/2 cup cream and paraffin wax (size of a walnut) cook to firm ball stage 248.
Pour into buttered pan- let set till cool, then cut and wrap.

title: modeling dough
directions: In bowl
mix
flour
and
salt.
If
you are using food coloring, add 2 or
3 drops at a time to water and stir.
(For deeper shades, add
to 15 drops.) Slowly add water and oil to dough
and
mix
well.
Knead
dough
by hand until smooth. Dough can
be
refrigerated
in
a sealed plastic container or plastic bag for up to 1 week.

title: ranchero corn
directions: Fry bacon until cooked, but not brown. Drain excess fat. Stir in drained mushrooms and onions. Saute until onion is tender. Blend in corn (drained) and heat through. Sprinkle with cheese. Heat until cheese is melted.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, peanut butter, sugar and vanilla with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended. Gently stir in 1 and 1/2 c. Cool Whip. Freeze 4 hours or overnight until firm. Let stand 1/2 hour or until pie can be cut easily. Garnish with remaining Cool Whip.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, Karo and water; cook until spins a thread (hard ball).
Add peanuts; cook until forms a hard ball in water (hard crack on thermometer) and peanuts start to pop.
Remove from fire and add soda; stir and pour in greased cookie sheet.
Spread thin. When cool beat into pieces.

title: long island iced tea
directions: Mix in a gallon pitcher 3/4 cup each of vodka, gin, tequila, rum and Triple Sec.
Add 2 cans Coke (12 ounces each; can use diet Coke).
Add 24 ounces of sweet and sour mix to liquors.
Add ice and lemons, limes and cherries as desired.

title: roast beef a la stroganoff
directions: Cook celery, onion and mushrooms in butter until tender.
Stir in flour and soy sauce.
Add bouillon; cook, stirring until thickened.
Stir in sour cream.
Add beef and heat through.
Serve with hot cooked rice or noodles.
Serves 4.

title: crock-pot lasagna
directions: Brown ground meat and onion with salt and pepper; drain off grease. In large bowl, add ground meat mixture and all of the remaining ingredients with the exception of the cheese and tortillas. Stir mixture well. Layer in a crock-pot: 1 cup mixture, grated cheese and 1 tortilla until all are used, ending with the cheese. Cook in crock-pot 3 to 4 hours on low or 1 to 1 1/2 hours on high.

title: breakfast in a glass
directions: Whirl all ingredients in blender.

title: witches brew
directions: Saute onion in butter. Add Worcestershire sauce and ketchup. Stir in chipped beef, pepper, mushrooms and cheese.
Heat slowly until cheese is melted.
Watch closely and stir often. Serve with chips or cold vegetables.

title: kentucky benedictine sandwich filling or dip
directions: Place cucumber in food processor to mince.
Place minced cucumber in cheese cloth and squeeze out excess liquid.
Place onion in food processor to mince.
Place minced onion in cheese cloth and squeeze out excess liquid.

title: pork chops and potatoes
directions: Spray a 12 x 8-inch dish with cooking spray.
Layer potatoes, flour, salt and pepper in 2 to 3 layers.
Flour pork chops and lay on top of potatoes.
Pour milk over all.
Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and place under broiler until browned.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix 2 cups Minute rice with 3/4 cup water and 1 can of soup. Put in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Lay chicken on top.
Don't overlap or the chicken won't brown.
Sprinkle 1 package onion soup mix over chicken.
Cover loosely with aluminum foil.
Bake for 2 hours in a 350° oven.
If using boneless, skinless chicken, cook for 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Drain blueberries.
Mix in bowl with sugar and cinnamon.
Take pie pans, pour ingredients into them.
Cover with cream cheese. Crush graham crackers and cover cream cheese.
Top with chopped nuts.
Chill 2 hours.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Stir cocoa into oil.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir remaining ingredients except nuts.
Spread in greased pan. Sprinkle nuts on top for baking.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until brownies pull away from pan.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all together and serve.

title: dip for vegetables
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate until well chilled.

title: artichoke heart dip
directions: Chop artichoke hearts and add the mayonnaise and Parmesan cheese.
Mix well and heat in microwave until warm.

title: cooked tomato dish
directions: Cook slow, stirring frequently until ingredients become thick.

title: polish apple pancakes
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, sugar and salt.
In another bowl, lightly beat egg, milk and oil.
Add to dry mixture.
Stir until smooth.
Fold in apples.
Pour batter by 1/2 cup full onto a lightly greased griddle and spread to form 1/2-inch circle.
Turn when bubbly.

title: strawberry-pineapple jell-o salad
directions: Mix strawberry Jell-O, hot water, frozen strawberries with strawberry juice and crushed pineapple.
Set aside to cool for a short time.

title: crescent chicken
directions: Mix soup, milk and cheese.
Put 1/2 of mixture in a baking dish.
Roll chicken in crescent rolls and place in a dish.
Cover with other half of mixture.
Put extra cheese on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: cheesy french bread
directions: Spread French bread with butter, garlic salt and sour cream. Sprinkle with diced chiles and Jack and Cheddar cheeses.
Top with sliced olives.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients smoothly.

title: buttermilk chocolate bread
directions: Grease bottom only of a loaf pan.
In bowl, combine sugar and margarine; blend well.
Add eggs; blend well. Stir in buttermilk. Add flour, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in pecans. Pour into prepared loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool completely.
Wrap tightly and store in the refrigerator.

title: spinach and bean burrito
directions: Steam spinach until cooked.
Warm tortillas over flame or in frying pan.
Put cheese and beans on tortilla.
Microwave until beans are hot and cheese is partly melted.
Add spinach, Ortega chili, salsa and rice (if you want).
Roll up burrito and add a topping.
Makes a deliciously filling burrito.
Serves 1.

title: north face
directions: In an 8 ounce coffee glass, add Bailey's, peppermint Schnapps and fill with coffee.
Add whipped cream.

title: honey fudge brownies
directions: In saucepan, melt together over low heat the butter, chocolate, salt and vanilla; mix well.
Remove from heat.
Blend in honey, flour and baking powder.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add nuts.
Pour into a greased square 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, or until done in center.
Cool on rack for 15 minutes. Mark into 2-inch squares.
Makes 16 squares.

title: golden lamb's shaker sugar pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar and place in bottom of pie shell.
Add cream, vanilla and soft butter in small pieces.
Sprinkle nutmeg over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until firm.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and butter with sugar adding one egg at a time.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and pour into greased and floured tube pan and bake at 325° or 350°. When cake tester comes out clean, the cake is done.
Cool for 10 minutes, then invert onto serving dish.

title: easy fruit salad dressing
directions: Mix honey and lemon juice.
Stir in sour cream a little at a time, mixing well.
Pour over well drained mixed fruit of your choice and blend.

title: avocado crab salad
directions: Halve the avocado and arrange on lettuce leaves. Cover with crab or shrimp.
Mix remaining ingredients to taste.
Serve over crab.

title: turtle cake
directions: Make cake mix according to package directions.
Pour 1/2 mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until done.
Melt caramels, milk and butter on stove.
Pour this over the baked cake.
Sprinkle nuts and chocolate chips on top of this.
Pour rest of batter on top of this and bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Top with desired topping.

title: spiral sandwich roll-ups(students' favorite demonstration request)
directions: Dampen cracker bread on both sides by holding the bread briefly under gently running cold water.
Place the moistened bread between 2 damp, clean towels, making sure the sesame seed is facing down.
Let the bread stand at room temperature about 1 hour or until it has softened enough to roll.

title: blonde fudge
directions: Combine everything except nuts in a 3-quart saucepan.
Place over medium heat.
Stir continuously as it sticks easily.
Cook until a firm ball forms in cold water.
Remove from heat and let cool for a few minutes.
Add nuts and beat until thick.
Pour into buttered 12 x 12-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: butterscotch loaf
directions: Cream egg and sugar; add melted butter.
Sift flour, soda, powder and salt and set aside.
Put half your buttermilk into creamed mixture; add half your flour mixture.
Keep doing until all used.
Put in nuts.
Pour into bread pan and bake 1 hour at 350° in greased pan.

title: tennia's apple relish
directions: Boil vinegar, sugar, pickling spice and salt.
Add vegetables and bring to boil.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Pour into hot jars and seal.
Makes 12-14 pints.
Great with black-eyed peas, dried beans.

title: blushing punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar and water.
Pour into a mold or tube cake pan and freeze solid.
Prepare fruit ahead of time.
Just before serving, unmold Kool-Aid and put in punch bowl.
Slowly pour Sprite over mold;
add fruit as a garnish and serve.
May change fruit flavoring and fruit.
Serves 16 people.

title: mr. t's chocolate pie
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together and then add eggs.
Mix well. Add butter, vanilla and milk.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 1 deep dish pie.

title: moms fried squash
directions: Peel squash cut in 1/4 slices. In another bowl beat eggs add milk salt and pepper. Dip squash in milk; then corn meal. Fry at 350° for 6 minutes.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into slices.
Place in 6 cups of water, along with butter and salt.
Bring to boil, then reduce heat and cook until tender.
Drain.
Place potatoes in baking dish.
Add Cheddar cheese and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: "dirty" taters
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Melt the butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add potatoes, sprinkle soup mix on top.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: corned beef dip
directions: Combine
all
ingredients.
Hollow
out center of large loaf of
pumpernickel or rye bread.
Fill with dip.
Cut bread taken from center into pieces and use for dipping.

title: busy day meat
directions: Season meat with salt and press into a casserole bowl.
Place potatoes and onion in layers on top.
Dilute soup with water and pour over top of casserole.
Bake at 375° for 2 hours or until potatoes are tender.

title: vegetable and pasta toss
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Add broccoli and cauliflower to boiling pasta for the last minute of cooking; drain.
Rinse with cold water; drain well.

title: ginger whipped cream
directions: Using electric mixer, beat first 3 ingredients in large bowl to soft peaks.
Add rum and ginger; beat until almost stiff.
(Can be prepared 5 hours ahead.)
Cover and refrigerate.
Makes about 3 1/2 cups.

title: carrot pineapple date cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil; add eggs and cream well.
Add flour and cinnamon;
mix
well.
Add
carrots,
pineapple, dates and pecans. Pour
into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: *You may need to add an additional 1/4 teaspoon cloves and cinnamon.

title: easy homemade chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk together.
Add chocolate milk (may not need 3 full quarts).
Pour into ice cream freezer container.
Freeze as directed for ice cream freezer.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: mock wiener burgers
directions: In mixing bowl, thoroughly combine beef, A.1., egg, salt, onion and cheese.
Divide into 6 portions.
Shape each into a long roll resembling a wiener.
Wrap with a bacon slice.
Broil, turning carefully, until brown on all sides and cooked as desired.
Serve in toasted hot dog buns.
Makes 6.

title: aunt jo's cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, then add honey.
Add remaining ingredients; mix.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream shortening with sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour and add along with sour cream and flavorings.
Beat well.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: taco stuff
directions: Brown meat and add remaining ingredients.
Simmer.
Pour over Fritos and add grated cheese.
Add tomatoes, lettuce and onions.

title: spiced peaches (brandied)
directions: Cook spices, sugar and vinegar for 20 minutes.
Drop peaches carefully in syrup and cook until heated through.
Pack in sterile jars; cover with syrup and seal airtight.

title: delicious custard
directions: Blend cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Add milk and eggs and cook until thickened.
Add butter and vanilla.
I use one whole egg.

title: summer dessert
directions: Break cake in bowl.
Drain peaches (reserving juice).
Add boiling water to peach juice to make Jell-O; add Jell-O and 2 cups of cold water.
Pour over cake.
Layer peaches on top.
Make pudding and pour over peaches.
Slice bananas on top.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: percolator punch
directions: In basket of a 30 cup percolator place whole cloves, salt and cinnamon sticks.
Perk as usual.

title: giblet broth
directions: Combine all in a saucepan.
Bring to boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer 1 hour or until giblets are tender.
Remove giblets and neck; chop meat fine.
Refrigerate.
Strain broth and refrigerate. Makes 4 cups broth.

title: pumpkin orange cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking soda, and salt in medium bowl.
Mix butter and sugars in large bowl.
Beat until creamy and add egg, pumpkin, orange juice and orange peel.

title: breakfast food
directions: Place rolls in a well-greased tube pan; sprinkle pudding mix over rolls.
Bring butter, sugar, cinnamon and nuts to a boil. Pour over rolls.
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Let sit on countertop overnight.
In morning bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Turn onto plate.

title: mexican dip
directions: In a casserole pan, spread softened cream cheese; then layer chili.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over the top.
Spread olives on top, if desired.
Put in oven at 200° until heated and cheese is melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: seven cup salad
directions: Chill well and serve.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin and sugars.
Mix well.
Add salt, flour and spice.
Mix again.
Beat eggs and add with milk to pumpkin mixture.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes at 450°.
Lower heat to 350° and bake 30 to 45 minutes until well brown.

title: pretend heath bar cookies
directions: Line 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan with foil.
Spray with Pam. Line with saltine crackers.
Melt 3/4 cup margarine or butter with the sugar.
Slowly pour over crackers; spoon it over, making sure the sugar is mixed into the butter.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven and sprinkle the chocolate chips over it.
Let them melt and spread evenly with a knife.
No need to melt the chips first.
Cool completely in the refrigerator, then turn upside down on board and peel the foil off the entire sheet of cookies.
Cut or break into pieces. They keep for a long time if kept in covered container in refrigerator.

title: italian vegetable soup
directions: Cook and stir sausage and onion in 3-quart saucepan until sausage is light brown; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients except cheese; break up tomatoes with fork.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until zucchini is tender, about 5 minutes.
Serve with cheese.

title: banana bars
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into greased jelly roll pan (10 x 15).
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with powdered sugar frosting.

title: dried apple cake
directions: Add cocoa to apples.
Sift 3 cups of flour with the soda, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon and allspice.
Take 1 cup of flour; mix with raisins.
Mix all ingredients; pour into tube pan that has been greased.
Cook in oven at 350° for about an hour.
Test with toothpick.

title: white castle dressing
directions: In large mixing bowl, tear burgers and buns in pieces.
Add celery and seasonings.
Toss and add chicken broth.
Stuff turkey or use as a side dish.

title: chocolate butterscotch fudge
directions: In saucepan, combine brown sugar, white sugar, evaporated milk and margarine.
Bring to a full boil over moderate heat, stirring frequently.
Boil for 15 minutes over moderate heat, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallow cream and chips. Stir until chips are melted and mixture is smooth.
Blend in walnuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Yields 2 1/2 pounds.

title: cream corn souffle
directions: Combine corn, eggs, salt and sugar.
Pour into 8-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle Ritz crackers over top and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except grated cheese and put in casserole dish or baking pan and sprinkle grated cheese over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.

title: zucchini crisp
directions: *If zucchini is quartered and then sliced, it looks like apple slices.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours. Roll into 4 (1 pound) rolls and bake on broiler rack (so grease can drain off) in oven for 50 minutes at 300°.
Can use deer meat with a little hamburger or sausage.

title: luscious layer chocolate coconut bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Combine cake mix, margarine, sour cream and eggs.
Beat at low speed until moist, then at high speed for 2 minutes. Spread in greased and floured pan.
Bake for 12 minutes.

title: pork chops "n" gravy
directions: Roll chops in flour and brown in shortening.
When done, put in casserole dish.
Slice 1 small onion over top and add soup, diluted with water, over chops and onion.
Bake, covered, 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: plum cake
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, flour, spices and oil.
Mix together well, then add baby food and nuts.
Pour in prepared Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pimento cheese sandwich filling
directions: Grate cheese into mixing bowl.
Add mayonnaise, pimento with juice, salt and Tabasco.
Mix well.
Makes 2 2/3 cups.

title: good old fashioned cookies
directions: Combine sugar, shortening, eggs and molasses.
Beat until smooth.
Add flour, cinnamon, salt, soda, oats, nuts and raisins. Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes. Do not overbake.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef with bacon.
Add onion; cook until tender, not brown.
Drain off grease.
Add seasoning to meat mixture. Stir in soup.
Cook slowly, uncovered, for 20 minutes; stir frequently.
Stir in sour cream; heat thoroughly.
Serve over hot buttered noodles.
Serves 4.

title: foolproof beef and broccoli
directions: Slice beef across the grain into very thin strips.
Brown the beef and garlic in a skillet over medium heat; add onion and cook 5 minutes, stirring often.

title: chutney cheese ball
directions: Mix first seven ingredients together and roll into ball. Makes 1 large or 2 medium size.
Cover the balls with the jar of chutney.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Serve on rice crackers.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Combine butter, egg, sugar and vanilla. Cream and then add flour mixture of flour, soda and salt. Stir until completely mixed. Roll on lightly floured surface. Sprinkle with sugar. Cut with floured cutter. Bake on lightly greased baking sheet for 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: veal fiestas
directions: Cut veal into serving pieces; season with salt and pepper. Dredge veal with flour.
Saute on both sides in hot shortening in heatproof casserole; cover with onions, chili sauce and 1 1/2 cups hot water.
Cover.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 30 minutes. Remove cover; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 10 minutes longer. Remove veal to hot platter.
Stir macaroni into pan juices; heat through.
Spoon macaroni mixture over veal.

title: world's best cookie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Add oatmeal, coconut and cornflakes.
Mix well.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Stir in vanilla and chopped pecans.
Form into balls about the size of small walnuts.
Bake on greased cookie sheets 10 to 12 minutes at 325°.
Cool and remove from pans.

title: mullins stack cake
directions: Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Set aside. Work shortening until soft.
Add sugar, a little at a time, while creaming mixture.
Mix in molasses thoroughly.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in flour combination and milk, alternating. Spoon thin layer of batter, about 1/4-inch thick, into greased 9-inch cake pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes, until cake pulls away from sides of pan.
There will be 6 to 7 layers.
When all layers are baked and cooled, stack with generous amounts of dried fruit or lightly spiced applesauce. Sprinkle with 10x sugar.

title: door knobs to heaven
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add beaten eggs, then pineapple. Spread mixture between vanilla wafers.
Cover with whipped cream and roll in coconut.
Refrigerate.
Makes 30 to 40 desserts.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Put onion and cucumbers in large jar and pour mixture over. Put in refrigerator and let set for 24 hours.
These are so simple and so good.
No cooking required.

title: chinese beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and place in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients, except potato chips.
Pour over meat. Place chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Follow directions on cake mix box and add extra oil.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat yolks of eggs; gradually add sugar, beating until thickened. Pour mixture in chilled bowl; place bowl on bed of ice. Whip the cream and milk.
Add to egg yolks; set aside for a few minutes.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into yolk mixture. Add vanilla and nutmeg.

title: d's dixie-delight biscuits(makes 15 to 17 biscuits)
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Cut shortening into flour until particles are fine like crumbs.
Add sugar.
Mix lightly.
Add milk or buttermilk and stir with a fork until just mixed.
Add semi-sweet chocolate mini-chips and pecan chips.
Mix.
Turn out on lightly floured board.
Roll dough out to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with a 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on a very lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes.

title: corn chowder
directions: Place half the corn and 1 cup water in blender to make smooth puree.
Fry the bacon crisp and brown.
Remove and set aside.
Add the onions to the frying pan; cook, stirring, until soft.
Put in large saucepan or Dutch oven.
Stir in the corn puree, the remaining corn kernels, the potatoes, salt, pepper and 2 cups water.
Cover and simmer until the potatoes are cooked, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Add the cream and milk.
Heat without allowing it to come to a boil.
Before serving, stir in the bacon.
Garnish with parsley.

title: squash fritters
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Stir eggs into squash mixture. Add margarine.
Drop fritters by tablespoon into a greased skillet.
Cook until delicately brown.
Turn and brown on other side.
Serve immediately.

title: apple cheese bread
directions: Combine butter, eggs and dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Blend well.
Stir in shredded apples, Cheddar cheese and chopped walnuts.
Turn into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes, until center of loaf tests done with toothpick.
Cool thoroughly before removing from pan.

title: adam's banana bread
directions: Combine sugar, shortening, bananas, egg and buttermilk in bowl and mix well.
Blend in remaining ingredients until well mixed. Turn into greased loaf or bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Put in casserole dish. Mix Bisquick and milk together.
Spread on top of pie.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Cook the corn meal and cold water until thick.
Add other ingredients and stir.
Pour in baking dish.
Cook at 400° until brown.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli quiche(low-fat)
directions: In a large bowl, mix the milk and eggs.
Stir in the broccoli, peppers, Monterey Jack, scallions and dill.
Coat a 9-inch pie plate with nonstick spray.
Add the broccoli mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until knife inserted in the center comes out clean and the quiche is lightly puffed and golden on top.

title: smoked salmon cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and arrange a rack on the middle shelf of oven.
Spray a 9-inch spring-form pan with nonstick vegetable cooking spray.
Place the bread crumbs and 1/4 cup of Parmesan cheese in the spring-form pan and toss to mix.
Add melted butter and mix to blend.
Chop the smoked salmon fine in a food processor fitted with the metal blade, or by hand.
Set aside.
Press the crumb mixture into the bottom of pan.
Set aside.

title: caramel corn
directions: In heavy, large pot, stir and cook sugar, Karo and water to 290° on candy thermometer.
Add butter, soda and salt; stir, then pour over popped corn and toss until well coated.
Spread on waxed paper to cool.
Break apart into pieces and store in airtight container.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: southern biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, cream of tartar, salt and sugar. Cut in shortening until like cornmeal; pour milk in slowly.
Add egg and stir until stiff.
Drop by tablespoon on greased pan. Bake at 450° for about 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix
all
together at medium speed.
Then at high speed until well blended.
Very delicious.
Don't forget the chips. Refrigerate.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients, thin with water to desired thickness. Simmer over heat for 1 hour.

title: tartes au fromage(cheese pie)
directions: Put the flour in a bowl.
Put the yeast in the milk with the sugar in another bowl.
When the yeast is dissolved, add the milk to the flour while mixing with the mixer.
Add the egg yolks and mix.
Add the sugar and butter and mix until the mixture becomes "solid."
Place the bowl in a warm place; cover with a towel and allow to rise for 1 to 2 hours.
After the dough has risen, cut into fourths.
Roll out to the size of a pie pan.
Place in a greased pie pan and mold to the pan.
Prick the crusts with the tines of a fork.

title: mexican chicken and rice
directions: Cut the chicken into 1/2-inch strips.
Chop onion and garlic separately.
Heat the oil in a large frying pan on medium heat for 2 to 3 minutes.
Saute onion in oil for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add cut-up chicken, garlic and 1 cup of uncooked rice to the pan.
Stir and cook until the chicken turns white (5 to 7 minutes).
Add chicken broth, spaghetti sauce, green chilies, oregano and sweet basil. Mix well.
Cover pan and cook on low heat for 15 minutes.
Add green beans and corn.
Cook 10 minutes longer.

title: cocktail sausages
directions: Cut off ends of polish sausage.
Set crock-pot on high and melt jelly and mustard.
Turn to medium.
Add sausages and cook until darkened.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Mix sour cream, soup and milk in saucepan.
Slowly heat; do not boil.
Brown meat; add onion when meat is partially brown. Drain meat.
Fill tortillas with equal amounts of meat and cheese and 1 tablespoon sour cream-soup mixture.
Add hot sauce to taste. Roll and place in shallow baking dish.
Top enchiladas with remaining sour cream-soup mixture, cheese and meat.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: barbecue polish sausage
directions: Cut sausage into slices and add to ingredients in crock-pot.

title: no-fat banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9 x 5 x 4-inch loaf pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and cinnamon and set aside.
In a larger bowl, whisk together applesauce, sugar, egg whites, banana and vanilla.
Add flour mixture, blend.
Bake batter for 50 to 60 minutes (approximately). Can also be put in muffin tins.

title: strawberry ice
directions: Beat eggs with 1/2 cup sugar.
Add remaining sugar with cream. Bring to boiling point; stir cream gradually into egg mixture. Then add Eagle Brand milk and strawberries and juice.
Put in ice cream freezer and freeze.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Mix together broccoli, soup, eggs, cheese and mayonnaise.
Place in a lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Mix melted butter and cracker crumbs. Sprinkle crumbs over top of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes or until casserole is set and lightly browned.

title: aunt kathy's pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Chill overnight and serve.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Melt margarine in warm potatoes. Add sugar. Add eggs one at a time. Add vanilla and cinnamon. Pour into uncooked shell. Bake at 350° until set (lower rack of oven) for about 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix ingredients well. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: cody's favorite chocolate gravy
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa until blended.
Stir in milk. Transfer to sauce pan and heat over high heat until rolling boil occurs, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Reduce heat to low.
Cook until thick (about 5 minutes).
Serve over biscuits.

title: punch
directions: Boil first 2 ingredients and cool.
This can be put in plastic bags.
Place in freezer for days or until you are ready to use.

title: easy eagle brand dessert
directions: Mix peanut butter, sugar and milk together.
Roll into balls. Then roll balls in crushed graham crackers.
Chill.

title: beef bake
directions: Brown ground beef with salt and pepper; drain.
Mix ground beef with celery, canned soups and 1 cup Chinese noodles.
Pour in square baking dish.
Cover with remaining noodles.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: scotch shortbread cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar thoroughly.
Measure flour by sifting. Work in flour with hands.
Chill.
Roll dough 1/3 to 1/2-inch thick (or thinner if desired).
Cut into fancy shapes.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350° (moderate). The tops do not brown during baking, nor does shape of cookies change.
Makes 2 dozen 1 1/2 x 1-inch cookies.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: To the chicken wings, discard tips and separate drumettes from front part of wings.
Combine soy sauce, oil, garlic clove and lemon juice.
Marinate wings in refrigerator overnight in zipped freezer bag, turn a couple of times next day.
Put wings and marinade into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake, covered, at 300° for 3 to 4 hours.
Drain on paper towels, serve hot or cold.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Cook potatoes with jackets until tender.
Peel and shred. Combine with sour cream, onions, 3/4 cup cheese, salt and pepper. Turn mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease and flour three 9-inch layer pans.
In large bowl, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Sift flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and cloves together 3 times.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk to cream mixture, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Add lemon extract and lemon zest; fold in blackberry jam.
Mix well.
Pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake 25 minutes or until cake tests done.
Ice with frosting of your choice.

title: smoothies
directions: For Banana-Peach: Combine in blender and blend first 3 ingredients until smooth.

title: onion zucchini bread
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, onion, 6 tablespoons Parmesan cheese, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
In a small bowl, mix buttermilk, oil, eggs and zucchini.
Stir into flour mixture just until blended.
Spoon into greased 9-inch round baking pan. Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Beat egg.
Add ingredients except peanut butter.
Mix well. Add peanut butter.	Roll into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press out with water moistened or sugar dipped fork. Criss-cross patterns.
Bake in preheated oven for 7-10 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable marinade
directions: Mix ingredients.
Beat well to blend.
May be used over hot cooked vegetables or to dress up cold vegetables.

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Put chicken in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix soup and milk and pour over chicken.
Stir.
Make stuffing mix according to directions and put this on top of chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: spinach salad
directions: In medium bowl, combine spinach, mushrooms, Blue cheese, green onions and hazelnuts. Mix well.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar; beat well.
Add eggs and blend.
Add flour and cinnamon and blend well.
Blend with oil mixture.
Add carrots, a small amount at a time.
Bake in oblong pan at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: summer minestrone(minestrone estivo)
directions: Heat oil in a large saucepan, add the onion and cook gently for about 5 minutes, stirring constantly, until softened.
Stir in the chopped tomatoes, zucchini, summer squash, potatoes and garlic.
Mix well and cook gently for about 10 minutes uncovered. Shake pan frequently to prevent the vegetables from sticking to the base.
Pour in the stock.
Bring to a boil and add spaghetti. Lower heat to a simmer.
Half cover pan and simmer gently for 15 minutes or until vegetables are just tender.
Add more stock if necessary. Remove pan from heat.
Stir in basil and half the cheese.
Taste for seasoning.
Serve hot, sprinkled with remaining cheese.
Serves 4 - 6.

title: crescent roll treats
directions: Place 1 can of crescent rolls flat in bottom of pan.
Bake for 5 minutes.
Cream together cream cheese, 3/4 cup of sugar and 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Spread over bottom layer.
Layer second can of crescent rolls over cream cheese mixture.
Top with melted butter, 1/2 cup sugar and 2 to 3 teaspoons cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer Doritos in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Add layer of chicken, then layer of cheese.
Mix together the soups, tomatoes and chili powder and pour evenly over chicken ingredients in pan.
(You may want to heat soup mixture in microwave to get a more pourable consistency.)
Sprinkle crumbled Doritos and shredded cheese over the top of casserole and bake in a 350° oven approximately 30 minutes.

title: cherry banana pie
directions: Bake pie shell.
In saucepan, mix cherries, with liquid, sugar and cornstarch.
Cook and stir constantly until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in butter.
Cool and stir in cinnamon and almond extract.
Slice bananas in layers into baked pie shell.
Pour filling over banana slices.
Chill until set.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats.
Cover and let stand 20 minutes. Cream butter and sugar; beat until fluffy.
Blend in vanilla and eggs. Add oats and spices.
Mix well.
Pour
into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350°.
Do not remove from pan.

title: apricot-cream cheese cake
directions: Beat together cake mix, eggs, apricot nectar and oleo at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Mix together cream cheese, lemon juice and sugar.
Beat at medium speed until smooth. Spread evenly over top of cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let cool in pan for 1 1/2 hours.
Turn over on cake plate.

title: brandy slush
directions: In large saucepan, heat 7 cups of water.
Stir in sugar; make sure it is all dissolved.
Set aside to cool.
Heat remaining 2 cups of water to boiling.
In bowl, steep tea in boiling water. Cool.
Remove tea bags and stir tea into sugared water.
Add lemonade, orange juice and brandy; mix well.
Store in freezer for 24 hours.
Makes approximately 3 1/2 quarts.

title: winter wonder salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Keeps well.
Make ahead.

title: my favorite macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil noodles until done and drain.
Add cheese, milk and margarine.
Pour into casserole dish.
Cover with foil and bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: chili con queso
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Stir and bake another 30 minutes.
Serve warm with corn chips.

title: barbecue potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes; arrange in baking dish.
Heat milk and add other dry ingredients that have been mixed to a paste.
Cook over low heat until thickened.
Add some of the cheese.
Leave enough to put on top.
Put in oven and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until light brown and bubbly.

title: crab pasta salad
directions: Refrigerate for 3 hours before serving.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: In a large Pyrex dish, pour in can of enchilada sauce, then layer of shells.
Mix beans with small amount of milk and spread over shells, then another layer of shells.

title: stuffed date cookies(good eats!)
directions: Stuff each date with a walnut half; press to hold in shape. Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in the egg, sour cream and vanilla. Stir in the sifted flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Add the stuffed dates.

title: country egg custard pie
directions: Heat milk (until steam rises).
Mix milk with remainder of ingredients; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle more nutmeg lightly on top.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 more minutes.

title: easy baked chicken and veggies
directions: Place chicken breasts in the bottom of a large baking dish which has a cover.
Add margarine and lemon pepper.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes, at 350°.
Add California mix or mixed vegetables, onion, salt and pepper.
Return to oven for 30 minutes more.
Serve with fruit salad and French bread.
So easy, so good.

title: chicken paprikash
directions: Brown chicken in a skillet in its own fat or a little oil or margarine.
Put chicken to one side of pan then brown onion slices.
After the onion is tender add 1 teaspoon paprika for every 3 to 4 pieces of chicken.
Spread out chicken and spread seasoned onions on top.
You may wish to remove excess fat here or before you add the paprika.
Add chicken broth or bouillon. Simmer with the lid on, turning chicken occasionally.
Cook 1/2 to 1 hour.
Check the meat with a fork, if easily separated, it is done.
Add some of the hot broth to the yogurt and sour cream mixture until it is warmed, then add to pan.
Heat on low to avoid curdling.
Serve over potato dumplings, egg noodles or rice.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate. Combine all ingredients. Bake at 350° 20 minutes in well greased pie tin.

title: pumpkin eaters
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in greased muffin tins 3/4 full or make 2 loaves.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes for muffins or 30 to 45 minutes for loaves.
A Halloween delight!

title: egg dumplings
directions: Mix the flour and egg with cream until thick and doughy.
Drop into boiling broth and cook until tender and fluffy.

title: pear honey
directions: Grind pears and orange.
Mix with the other ingredients.
Cook slowly until desired thickness.
Good.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in 1 bowl.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in a Bundt pan, greased and floured.
Glaze while hot.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers.
Cover over top with salt.
Let stand 1 hour.
Wash salt off cucumbers.
Put cucumbers, onions and peppers in syrup made of the sugar, vinegar, mustard and turmeric.
Heat to boiling.
Put in jars and seal.
Makes 6 pints.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Pour pineapple juice over bananas then drain.
Mix all ingredients and freeze.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs. Add flour, salt and soda (keep a little mixture to put on top of cake when cooking).
Mix all ingredients with nuts and apples. Bake in tube pan at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute sliced yellow onions in butter.
Place 2 tablespoons onion (cooked) in 12 ounce soup bowl.
Add dash of dry sherry and Parmesan cheese.
Add the boiling soup stock and dash of salt to bowl.
Serve with a boat of toasted French bread covered with Swiss cheese in the bowl.

title: honey almond dip
directions: Mix well.
Serve with any vegetable or fruit.

title: st. nicolaas koekjes(santa claus cookies)
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Sift flour with spices, salt and soda and add alternately with sour cream to creamed mixture.
Add nuts.
Knead together well.
Shape into a loaf.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill in the refrigerator overnight.
Slice and bake in a hot oven (400°) until browned.
Makes 72 cookies (2 x 4-inch).

title: eddie's fabulous salsa
directions: Chop cilantro, Serrano chilies and green onions; put into bowl. Mix cans of diced green chilies and diced green jalapenos into same bowl of ingredients.
Pour half of mixture and 1 can of tomatoes with 1 teaspoon salt and lime juice into blender and mix for 3 seconds.
Pour into new bowl.
Repeat process for rest of mixture. Pour into same bowl.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.
The longer it sits the hotter it gets.
"Ole."

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and store tightly covered.
Use 3 to 4 heaping teaspoonfuls with an 8 ounce mug of boiling water.

title: "surprise" pop-tarts
directions: Take 2 Pop-Tarts; spread butter over both.
Put them in the microwave.
Cook until butter melts.

title: hawaiian diabetic cake
directions: Grease a loaf pan.
Mix cake as directed and cool.
Mix pudding as directed and add cream cheese.
Mix well until smooth. Pour over cake.
Drizzle pineapple on cake.
Top with Cool Whip and almonds.
Serves 12.

title: antipasto salad
