directions: Cook and drain Mueller's Twist trio.
Combine all ingredients with Wish-Bone Robusto Italian dressing.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except corn flakes and butter.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix corn flakes and butter; spread over casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Makes 8 or 9 servings.

title: shrimp chinese style
directions: Cook celery, onion and soy sauce in butter until crisp.
Add chili pepper and bean sprouts.
Let simmer slowly 10 minutes.
Add raw shrimp.
Place lid on pan and simmer for additional 25 minutes.
Serve hot over rice.

title: oven chicken parmesan
directions: Combine cheese, flour and seasonings.
Dip chicken in combined egg and milk.
Coat with cheese mixture.
Place in baking dish. Pour margarine over and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: tuna canapes
directions: Blend cream cheese and mustard; mix in tuna, green onion and curry.
Serve with cocktail bagels or crackers.

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and egg; add dry ingredients and milk. Divide into 2 ungreased 9-inch pans.
On top, spread 3/4 pound dark brown sugar.
Sprinkle generously with cinnamon.
Dot closely with 1/4 pound butter, bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients (except cheese).
Pour into oiled casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Peel and cut squash. Remove seeds and cut in 1-inch cubes. Cook in boiling salted water until tender; drain.
Place in buttered baking dish. Top with butter and brown sugar. Bake in a 400° oven
about 20 minutes or until brown.

title: yum-yum cake
directions: Follow directions for cake mix in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake and cool.
Mix pudding according to directions.
Add cream cheese; beat until smooth.
Spread onto cooled cake.
Spoon drained pineapple on top.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle coconut on top of Cool Whip.
May garnish with cherries and nuts, if desired.

title: panic pie
directions: Pour pie filling in greased 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle cake mix on top.
Pour margarine over the cake mix.
Top with nuts. Bake at 325° until golden brown.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: sensational double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in Cool Whip.
Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup milk into bowl.
Add pudding mix. Beat with wire whisk 1 to 2 minutes.
(Mixture will be thick.) Stir in pumpkin and spices with wire whisk; mix well.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until set.
Garnish as desired.
Store leftover pie in refrigerator.
Makes 8 servings.

title: papa j's brunswick stew
directions: Cook meat, then grind meat, corn, tomatoes and onions.
Then add other ingredients. Cook slowly until done.

title: flank steak teriyaki
directions: Combine all marinade ingredients. Marinate 1 large flank steak in refrigerator for about 4 to 6 hours. Refrigerate until about 1/2 hour before grilling. Broil meat about 4 minutes per side for rare or longer for desired degree of doneness. Slice thinly on the diagonal.

title: chicken taco bake
directions: Blend enchilada sauce and soup.
Stir in chicken and onion. Grease a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with half of the corn chips.
Pour chicken mixture over.
Sprinkle with cheese, then remaining chips.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer in dish as listed.
I add a chopped tomato just before serving.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger until crumbly. Drain. Add tomato paste, crushed tomatoes, salt, pepper and basil. Simmer for 30 minutes. In a small bowl, mix eggs, Parmesan cheese, parsley and cottage cheese.
Cook noodles according to directions on package.
Rinse and cool slightly.

title: pumpkin apple streusel muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, pie spice and soda.
In separate bowl, combine eggs and oil.
Add liquid ingredients to dry, stirring just until moist.
Stir in apples and spoon into greased muffin cups.
Top with Streusel Topping.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°. Makes 18 muffins.

title: shrimp pate
directions: Mash shrimp well and add onion.
Pour butter over and add mayonnaise, Tabasco and lemon juice.
Mix well and pack into mold. Refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: cream french icing
directions: Boil water and sugar together until dissolved.
Mix confectioners sugar and egg.
Blend with "syrup".
Add Crisco and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into small pieces.
Mix in cheese, bacon and onion.
Mix together mayonnaise, red wine vinegar and sugar.
Pour over broccoli mixture, stir well and chill.

title: pineapple shrimp
directions: Put pineapple with syrup, pickles, pickle syrup and salt in a saucepan.
Dissolve cornstarch in a little water and add to saucepan.
Bring mixture to a boil, stirring until clear and thickened.
Add the cooked shrimp and heat through.
Serve on rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: easy vegetable kabobs
directions: Thread vegetables evenly onto 12 in. skewers.
Stir together melted butter, basil and garlic powder.
Reserve 1/4 cup butter mixture and set aside.
Coat food rack with cooking spray; place rack on the grill over medium-high heat.
Place vegetables skewers on the rack.
Grill covered with grill lid 20-25 min. or until vegetables are tender. turning and basting with remaining butter mixture every 5 min.
Serve with reserved butter mixture.
Makes 4 servings.

title: german potato salad
directions: Brown bacon in pressure cooker.
Pour off excess drippings and add all other ingredients.
Cook 5 minutes.
Cool cooker at once.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Bring to a boil and simmer 20 minutes.
Place in hot, scalded jars.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cover top with grated cheese. Bake at 400° about 25 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbly all over.

title: baked apple supreme
directions: Wash apples and remove core, making a generous cavity in each apple.
Remove thin circle of Peel around cavity and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix together almonds, raisins, brown sugar, and cinnamon.
Fill cavities with mixture and place each apple in a 3 inch microproof custard cup.
Put 2 tablespoons of water in cup around apple.
Dot each apple with 1 tsp. butter.
Cook on Hi (max power) for ten minutes.
Serve warm with heavy cream or ice cream

title: easy italian dressing
directions: Combine all and chill.
Serve on green salad.

title: low-fat apple dessert with "creamy" topping(6 servings)
directions: Peel and core the apple then dice them.
Put them in a pot with the next five ingredients, cover and boil on medium heat 10 minutes, no more.
Don't overcook.
Chill.

title: old-fashioned beef stew
directions: Cut meat into 1-inch cubes.
Combine all ingredients except carrots and celery in a 4-quart Dutch oven; mix well.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 1 hour.
Add vegetables; continue cooking about 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Yields eight 1-cup servings.

title: peasant cabbage soup
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water.
Cook bacon and ham in large saucepan until bacon is crisp.
Add bouillon, cabbage, onions, carrots and seasonings.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes. Serve with cornbread.

title: nutty pie crust
directions: Blend flour, Crisco and sugar well; add nuts.
Press into a 9-inch pie pan by hand.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until it starts browning.
Cool and fill with your filling.

title: bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine bread and milk.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add raisins, if desired. Pour into glass baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan or dish at 350° for 10 minutes.
Mix next 4 ingredients and spread over pretzel crust.
Chill.
Mix jello and boiling water.
Add strawberries.
Spread over top.
Chill until firm.

title: paint additives
directions: By adding various materials listed to paint, new textures make painting more fun.
To make tempera lumpy, add flour; gritty, add sand; slippery, add glycerin; slimey, add liquid soap; sticky, add Karo syrup; rough, add sawdust; shiny, add sugar.

title: maple nut cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a mixing bowl. Add vanilla, maple flavoring and water. Beat for 8 minutes. Mix nuts, cinnamon and sugar in a small bowl. Layer batter and nut mixture in a greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Frost with store bought maple frosting or frosting of your choice.

title: grape salad
directions: Mix jello with hot water.
Cool.
Stir in pineapple and blueberry pie filling.
Set aside to chill.
Combine cream cheese with sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well; add nuts.
Spread over chilled jello mixture.
Refrigerate until topping is well set.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Slice zucchini 1/2 inch thick.
Thinly slice tomatoes, onion and pepper.
Layer 1/2 of above in buttered two quart casserole. Sprinkle with 1/2 of cheese.
Repeat and cover casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Remove cover and bake for 10 minutes longer.

title: orange fluff salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese with dry gelatin.
Blend in whipped topping, oranges and pineapple.
Decorate with cherries.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Combine ground beef, tomato sauce, onion, garlic, chili powder, salt, cumin and green pepper.
Layer 2 cups corn chips and half each of meat mixture, soup and cheese in 8-inch square glass baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven about 45 minutes to 1 hour, until hot. Makes 5 to 8 servings.

title: poor man's cookies
directions: Boil raisins and water for 5 minutes.
Add margarine and let cool in saucepan, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix and pour onto a greased jelly roll type pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 325°.
Cool for 5 minutes and then frost with thin icing.

title: adelle payne's ambrosia
directions: Mix fruit and coconut.
Sweeten with sugar to taste.
Chill at least 3 hours for flavors to blend.

title: curried orange chicken
directions: Rub chicken with curry.
Put in a baking dish.
Add orange juice, honey and mustard which have been blended, then pour over chicken.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°, then turn and bake 20 minutes more.
Remove chicken.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook elbow macaroni; rinse until cold and drain.
Add peppers, carrots, celery, onion, chopped hard-cooked eggs and salt.
Mix in a pan the sugar, mustard, egg, vinegar and water.
Stir until warm; thicken with a little flour and water.
Pour over macaroni; mix.
May be served warm or chilled.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Combine cream cheese, onion, mayonnaise and cream.
Mix until smooth.
Cut celery about 4 inches long.
Fill celery pieces with cheese mixture.
Chill and serve.

title: brownies
directions: Mix cake mix, brown sugar, water, and egg together.
Melt butter and put in mixture and mix well.
Add the rest of ingredients.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan and pour mixture into pan and bake at 350 degrees for 30 - 35 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter; add mushrooms, broccoli, stir in soup, eggs and half the almonds.
Add Accent, salt and pepper to taste. Pour in greased casserole and top with rest of almonds and grated cheese.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chocolate banana pudding
directions: Prepare dish as you would for vanilla banana pudding. Substitute chocolate for vanilla.

title: german potato salad
directions: Place potatoes, eggs and onions in a bowl.
Mix with salt, pepper and celery seed.
In hot bacon grease, stir in flour.
Add vinegar and sugar.
Cook until thickened.
Add coloring.
Mix this dressing into contents of bowl.
Crumble bacon on top and serve warm.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt oleo in large saucepan.
Add brown sugar and stir until dissolved.
Let cool until lukewarm.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla; combine dry ingredients and gradually mix into saucepan. Add chips and nuts.
Spread batter over greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Slice into brownies and enjoy.

title: old fashioned rice pudding
directions: Use heavy kettle or mixture will scorch.
Mix together milk, rice and sugar.
Add nutmeg prior to cooking.
Heat to boiling and cook very slowly for 45 minutes, stirring frequently.
Beat water and eggs until frothy.
Add vanilla.
Stir into hot rice mixture until well blended.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. When cool, sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: apple pie or cake
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon and apples together.
Put on crust. Beat egg and sour cream together.
Pour this mixture over apples and bake 25 minutes at 250°.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in one bowl.
Bake 1 hour in greased and floured Bundt pan at 350°.

title: black bean salad
directions: Mix everything together.
Eat chilled or hot as a soup or put into tortillas as a taco.
Serves 4.
Calories: 150.
Fat: .5 gm.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cook raisins in water for 10 minutes or until water has cooked down.
Cool raisins.
Mix butter and brown sugar; add yolks and raisins.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Saute
onions
in melted butter.
Combine eggs and sour cream, then add to onion mixture.
Add pepper.
Pour into pie shell; sprinkle
cheese
on
top.
Bake
in
450° oven for 20 minutes. Turn oven down to 325° and bake 20 minutes more.

title: corn bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil and salt; add mix, corn and sour cream. Mix well by hand. Bake in well greased 8 x 8-inch pan at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs, zucchini and vanilla; mix well.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Bake 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Take out of pan (9 x 5-inch pans).
Cool.

title: play-doh
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the flour.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Turn down heat and add flour; stir until thick.
Place dough on wax paper and knead until smooth.

title: tuna-on-bun
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put on bun and place in toaster oven until heated through and cheese melts.

title: banana bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In food processor or blender puree 2 bananas.
Measure out 2 cups puree; set aside.
Slice remaining banana; set aside.
Spray a 2 1/2-quart shallow baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Add bread cubes.
In small bowl combine banana puree, milk, sugar, egg substitute and vanilla. Pour banana mixture over bread cubes.
Stir in banana slices.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes until set.
Serve warm.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour and shortening until well blended.
Add egg, vinegar and ice water; mix well.
Form into a ball.
Roll out and put in pie pan.

title: texas meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, mash kidney beans.
Add all remaining ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Pack into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for about 1 1/4 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: apple nut ring
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In small bowl, combine sugar and cinnamon.
Separate biscuits and dip into butter; turn over to coat both sides.
Coat biscuits with sugar mixture; turn to coat completely.
Place 2 biscuits in center of greased 14-inch pizza pan.
Arrange remaining biscuits, edges touching, in rows around center biscuits.
Cut apple slices crosswise in half; place between biscuits.
In small bowl, combine walnuts, raisins and any remaining sugar mixture; sprinkle over apple.
Bake 15-20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: tuna summer sandwich
directions: Combine cream cheese, carrot, pineapple, walnuts and ginger. Spread 2 tablespoons of cheese mixture on each of 4 bread slices. Top with 2 tablespoons tuna and sprouts. Top with remaining slices.
Serves 4.

title: squash casserole
directions: Steam squash and onion until tender.
Drain water.
Mash and add cottage cheese, egg and salt.
Coat bottom of Pyrex dish with 1 teaspoon butter.
Pour mixture into dish.
Sprinkle top with cracker crumbs and Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: blueberry salad
directions: First Layer:
Take family size Jell-O and add 2 1/2 cups hot water.
Put in 8 x 13-inch baking dish and set gel real firm.

title: easy beef tips
directions: Put beef in 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with dried onion soup mix.
Spoon on mushroom soup.
Add the 7-Up.
Cover and bake 4 hours at 275°.
Don't open oven while cooking.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain fat.
Melt Velveeta in saucepan or slow cooker. Add ground beef and salsa.
Mix well. Serve hot as dip for tortilla corn chips.

title: hard cinnamon candy
directions: Heat sugar, syrup and water to 310°.
Add cinnamon and stir well.
Add food coloring; stir well.
Pour onto a well buttered cookie sheet.
Cut into small pieces when edges start getting firm.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar to prevent sticking together.
Store in an airtight container.

title: ambrosia mold jello
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add cold water to juice to measure 1 cup.
Stir.

title: wild rice dressing
directions: Prepare rice per instructions.
Meanwhile, saute onion and celery in margarine until golden.
Add mushroom pieces and saute a few minutes more.
Remove from pan; set aside.
In same pan, brown the sausage.
Drain well and put the onion mixture back into the pan.
Add rice and mix together well.
Cook in pan for 1/2 hour or bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(I normally double this recipe.)

title: preacher's delight
directions: Brown beef in butter; season to taste (noodles will make it salty).
Add all ingredients and mix.
Save 1/2 of Chinese noodles for topping.
Put into 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 250°.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground
beef and drain.
Add hominy and enchilada sauce. Season to	taste.	In casserole dish, put half of meat mixture, then taco chips and half of cheese.
Top with rest of meat mixture and cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: green shutters vidalia onion casserole
directions: Parboil onions for 15 minutes.

Melt butter. Stir in flour, broth and milk. Stir constantly until thickened. Add drained onions and seasonings. Layer in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Top with cheese and Ritz crackers crumbs. Dot with butter. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry bars
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and margarine.
Add flour.
Put in 1 cup of nuts, then mix in 1 cup cranberries.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 1 hour in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cynthia's chicken
directions: Brown chicken breasts in small amount of cooking oil, turning to cook and brown evenly.
Sprinkle with Italian seasonings, garlic powder, salt and pepper (amount to taste.)
Pour can of tomato sauce evenly over chicken.
Sprinkle sliced onion and green pepper strips over chicken.
Put lid on pan and cook over low heat approximately 30 to 35 minutes (or until done).

title: english toffee
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with waxed paper.
Sprinkle 1/3 cup nuts on bottom.
Cook butter and sugar until hard-crack stage (300°). Pour over pecans.
Top with chocolate chips.
Spread around.
Add remaining pecans.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Break into pieces.

title: chicken dish
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Combine chicken and eggs in bowl. Chill, covered, for 3 to 4 hours.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish sprayed with nonstick spray.
Pour broth over chicken.
Saute mushrooms in butter.
Spoon over chicken. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: cinder cake
directions: Mix crumbled Oreos and mix with melted butter.
Spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
(Reserve some crumbled Oreos for top of cake.)
Spread softened ice cream over Oreo cookie mixture.
Spoon and spread Cool Whip over ice cream.
Pour or drizzle desired amount of chocolate syrup on top.
Swirl with knife.
Freeze for 2 hours and cut into squares.
Sprinkle left over Oreos and pecan pieces on top.

title: cattleman's spread
directions: In a skillet, saute pecans in margarine until golden.
(Set aside.)
In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add sour cream and garlic powder.
Mix well.
Stir in beef and onion. Spread into a greased 8-inch baking dish.
Top with pecans.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 minutes or until heated through.
Serve with crackers and breadsticks.
Yield:
3 1/2 cups.

title: pinecrest chili
directions: Cook meat and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 4 to 6 hours.
Add liquid if chili thickens too much (juice or water).
Serves approximately 30.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix well.
Use 2 heaping teaspoonfuls with each cup of hot water.

title: ginger balls
directions: Crush gingersnaps not too fine; mix enough Cool Whip to form balls.
Use pecan half as a center; form ball around it with the gingersnap mixture.
Roll in confectioners sugar; chill overnight. Next morning, roll in sugar again if they look moist.

title: pineapple au gratin
directions: Mix together pineapple, juice, cheese, sugar and flour.
Put in baking dish.
Crush crackers and mix with melted margarine. Pour over top of mixture; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: toffee cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg yolk.
Add flour gradually, stirring until well blended.
Spread dough in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° in a preheated oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until medium brown.
After removing from oven, lay chocolate bars on top.
When melted, spread.
Sprinkle with nuts. Press down nuts slightly.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: blueberry or raspberry cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Break egg into measuring cup.
Add oil and milk to equal 1 cup.
Stir into dry ingredients.
Add vanilla; stir until just mixed (by hand).
Add berries.
Make topping.

title: almond joy cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in oblong pan and let cool.
Punch holes in cake with end of wooden spoon.
Combine 1 cup milk and 1 cup sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and add marshmallows and coconut.
Pour over cake while hot.

title: soft batch chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter, eggs, molasses, vanilla and water in a medium size bowl.
In a large bowl, sift together the sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt and flour.
Combine the moist mixture with the dry mixture.
Add the chocolate chips. Shape the dough into 1 inch balls, and place them 1 inch apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 minutes or until light brown around edges.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook pasta (fettuccine) as directed on package.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Combine pretzels, 3 tablespoons sugar and margarine.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese with 1 cup sugar until smooth.
Blend in 2 cups Cool Whip. Spread over cooled crust. Chill.
Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add strawberries until they're melted. Chill until slightly thickened.
When almost set pour over cream cheese. Chill until firm.
Serves 24.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Put on bottom of pan.
Chop up cabbage.
Place on top of potatoes.
Put sliced carrots on top of this.
Make hamburger patties and lay on top of vegetables. Slice an onion and lay on each hamburger patty.
Mix cream of mushroom soup with 1 cup milk; pour on top of all this.
Bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours in a 300° oven.

title: sweet and sour chicken(china)
directions: Bone chicken thighs.
Cut chicken into 3/4-inch pieces. Mix egg
yolk, 1 tablespoon of soy sauce, 1/2 teaspoon each of sugar and salt and the black pepper in a medium bowl.
Stir in chicken. Sprinkle
with
tablespoon of cornstarch; stir to mix well. Marinate at room temperature 30 minutes.

title: scratch cake
directions: If self-rising flour is used, omit baking powder and salt. Bake in 2 layers at 350° until cake springs back when touched.

title: chicken hot dish(microwave)
directions: Mix together and bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350° or microwave 15 to 20 minutes in lightly greased, covered casserole. Great dish to take to someone unmade.

title: mexican salad bowl
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients.
Cover; chill.
Drain and combine corn, beans and olives; spoon into lettuce lined bowl.
Serve with dressing.
Makes 6 servings.

title: soda cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites stiff.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Beat again. Stir in crackers and nuts.
Press this into a buttered pan and bake at 325° for 20 minutes. Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip after cooled.

title: cherry crunch delite
directions: Mix together Cool Whip, vanilla pudding (prepared using directions on box) and cream cheese.
Mix well, then add 1 1/2 cups nuts.
Use oblong pan and layer graham crackers, pudding mixture, crackers, mixture and crackers.
Then spread cherries on top and sprinkle with remaining nuts.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: Place hard butter on a breadboard; add sugar on top and then flour.
Knead the butter, sugar and flour together until it becomes crumbly (about the size of peas).
Still continue to knead until this all forms into a ball.
Pat to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Prick well with a fork, and then bake at 250° until light golden brown on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Place cookies about 1-inch apart, as they spread slightly when baked.

title: holiday cider
directions: Slice oranges into 6 wedges; stud wedges with cloves and set aside.
Combine cider and candies in a Dutch oven over medium heat; cook until candies are dissolved and mixture is thoroughly heated.
Pour cider mixture into a heatproof punch bowl.
Add clove studded wedges and cinnamon sticks.
Serve hot.
Yields 1 gallon.

title: green pea salad
directions: Pour into bowl the peas, grated pickles, egg and cheese.
Dice onions.
Mix together.
Add Miracle Whip; stir until well mixed.

title: mary's mexican dip
directions: Cook sausage and onion in skillet until well cooked.
Drain grease.
Combine sausage and all other ingredients in crock-pot. Heat until smooth.

title: special sauce for hamburgers
directions: Blend well and keep refrigerated in a covered container. Makes about 2 cups.
Spoon over piping hot hamburgers.

title: hamburger corn casserole
directions: Brown meat; add onions and cook until tender, but not brown. Add soups, corn, seasonings and mix well.
Stir in noodles.
Pour into 2 quart casserole dish.
Mix crumbs and butter; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° until heated through, about 30 minutes.

title: roast beef with onions
directions: Generously salt and pepper roast.
Cover roast with onion soup mix.
Place sliced onions over onion soup mix, securing with toothpicks.
Place roast in roasting pan with 1/2-inch of water in bottom of pan.
Place roast in preheated 450° oven for 30 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° for remainder of cooking time.

title: cheese drop biscuits
directions: Combine olive oil and milk.
Combine wet and dry ingredients and 1/2 cup of cheese.
Mix until just moist.
Drop in spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Bake for 10 minutes at 450°.

title: baked caesar zucchini
directions: Combine vegetables in an ovenproof baking dish: tomatoes (peeled and diced) and zucchini (diced or thinly sliced). Sprinkle with seasonings, cheese and seasoned salad croutons. Bake, uncovered, in 400° oven for 35 minutes or more or until top is well browned.
Serves 8; 40 calories each serving.

title: spedini or miniature bruscaloni
directions: Prepare one sheet of phyllo dough at a time!

title: pineapple olive nut salad
directions: Mix and let congeal.

title: crispy baked parmesan chicken
directions: Skin chicken and cut into pieces.
Spray jelly roll pans or baking pans with vegetable cooking spray.
Do not use foil or chicken will stick.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Cut pork into 1-inch cubes and coat with cornstarch.
Heat oil in skillet.
Add meat.
Saute, turning to brown meat.
Drain pineapple chunks, saving juice.
Add enough water to juice to make 1 cup.
Mix juice, pineapple, soy sauce, salt and sweet pickles to meat and continue to heat.
Mix cornstarch and vinegar.
Stir until smooth.
Add to hot mixture.
Boil, stirring constantly for 1 minute. Serve over rice.

title: more-more
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper in large skillet.
Drain excess fat.
Add seasonings and tomato sauce.
Add corn and green beans and simmer.
Cook noodles as directed.
Drain and add to meat mixture.
Pour into 3-quart casserole; top with cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Soak oats in buttermilk 1 hour.
Add beaten egg and brown sugar.
Sift flour, salt baking powder, soda and add to mixture. Then add melted shortening.
Do not beat to much.
Put in greased muffin pans and bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Can add 1 cup fresh or frozen blueberries.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; put in casserole.
Cut up cheese in small chunks and place on broccoli.
Mix melted oleo and crushed crackers; put over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Whisk milk and both packages of vanilla pudding mix until well blended.
Add Cool Whip and stir.
In a 9 x 13-inch (preferably glass Pyrex) pan, begin with a layer of graham cracker crumbs. Next, spread a layer of the Cool Whip mixture.
Continue this several times, ending with Cool Whip mixture.
Microwave chocolate icing for approximately 1 minute.
Pour on top and spread.
Chill in the refrigerator for 6 hours before serving or place in freezer for a little while if you can't wait.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, flour, butter and cinnamon.
Add rhubarb and stir.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: crock-pot teriyaki pork
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Put roast in crock-pot and pour mixture over it. Cook on low 6 to 8 hours.

title: green beans in sauce
directions: Heat olive oil and garlic in a skillet until garlic is lightly browned.
Add tomatoes
and water slowly.
Stir in 1/2 teaspoon salt, pepper, oregano and parsley. Bring to boiling. Cover and simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: pork chops and sauerkraut
directions: Brown chops in frying pan.
Remove and place in pan deep enough to accommodate amount of sauerkraut for as many people as you are feeding.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch ovenproof dish.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pat into a 4 x 8-inch loaf pan that has been greased.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: creamy rich chicken breast
directions: Pepper, but do not salt chicken breasts.
Wrap slice of bacon around each half of chicken breast.
Place layer of dried beef in bottom of baking dish.
Arrange bacon wrapped chicken on beef slices.
Cover with mixture of chicken soup, sour cream and cream cheese.
Cover pan tightly with foil.
Place in oven for 2 hours. When tender, remove foil and let brown slightly.
Serve on hot rice.

title: pudin-buding
directions: Soak bread in the milk and then mix them together in the blender, if there is milk left add it to the mixture.
Add eggs, cinnamon, vanilla, sugar and butter.
Pour mixture in a mould. Place in oven at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix the soup mix, sour cream and water chestnuts together. Fold thawed spinach in with the mixture.
Pour into a two quart dish and bake in a 325° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 6-8.

title: strawberry pizza i
directions: Combine flour and confectioners sugar with butter.
Mix until crumbly.
Press into 13-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden brown; cool.
Mix cream cheese with sugar. Spread over cooled crust.
Mix junket with 1 cup water in saucepan. Bring to boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; cool a few minutes and stir in strawberries.
Pour over pie.
Cool in refrigerator.
This will serve 8 to 12 and you can put a dollop of whipped cream or Cool Whip on each piece if desired.

title: sweet sour pork
directions: Drain pineapple for juice and set aside.
Brown pork in hot fat, cover with water, simmer 45 to 60 minutes.
In separate pan, combine cornstarch, salt, sugar, vinegar, pineapple juice and soy sauce.
Cook until thick stirring constantly.
Pour over hot pork. Let stand at least 10 minutes.
Add bell pepper, onion and pineapple chunks.
Heat 2 or 3 minutes.
Excellent over plain rice. Sauce may be used on other meats.

title: chicken and broccoli bake
directions: Boil chicken, onion and celery; debone chicken.
Cook broccoli.
Heat together soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Layer chicken mixture and broccoli, then pour soup mixture over top of broccoli.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: irish coffee pie
directions: Place gelatin, sugar and salt in saucepan; add milk and stir until well blended.
Place over low heat and cook, stirring constantly, until sugar and gelatin are dissolved.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain fruits; set aside.
Combine eggs, vinegar and sugar in heavy saucepan.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Cool.
Add Marshmallow Creme, pecans and whipped topping.
Add fruit and mix well.
Pour into individual molds.
Freeze for 24 hours.
Yields 9 to 12 servings.

title: tropical daze
directions: Combine all ingredients in an 8 ounce glass.
Fill with ice; shake.
Garnish with slice of orange and a cherry, if desired.

title: chinese pork salad
directions: In a large nonstick skillet, stir-fry pork over medium high heat about 4 to 5 minutes.
In a large bowl, toss pork with remaining ingredients.
Serves 4. Contains approximately per serving:
331 calories, 12 gm fat and 66 mg cholesterol.
